tember 10th, and be held every Tuesday and Thursday.\n\n====CAA vs Swift & Co.====\n{{AFB game box start\n|Title=CAA vs Swift & Co.\n|Visitor= Swift & Co. Stock Yarders\n|Host= Chicago AA\n|V1=10|V2=10\n|H1=0|H2=6\n|Date=September 15, 1895\n|Location= CAA Field, Thirty-Fifth Street and Wentworth Avenue, Chicago, Il.\n|TimeZone=CT\n|StartTime=\n|ElapsedTime=40 minutes (20 minute halves)\n|Attendance=\n|Weather=\n|Referee=\n}}\n{{AFB game box end}}\nChicago AA defeated the Swift & Co. Stock Yarders 28 to 0 at their own CAA field.  The game was an exhibition for the coming season, and so the Stock Yarders were given a chance to continue playing many times after fumbles and turnovers.  CAA played well, scoring six touchdowns, although there was an instance where Thompson, playing left tackle, accidently tackled Captain Camp, confusing him for a Stock-Yard player, and consequentially stopped a sure touchdown for the AA.<ref>https://www.newspapers.com/image/349466305/?terms=Chicago%2BAthletic%2BAssociation%2Bfootball</ref>\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 14\n| time = \n| w/l = exh.\n| opponent = [[JBS USA|Swift & Co.]]\n| site_stadium = CAA Field\n| site_cityst = [[Chicago, Illinois|Chicago, IL]]\n| score = 28-0\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 28\n| time = 3:30pm\n| w/l = l\n| opponent = [[1895 Chicago Maroons football team|Chicago]]\n| site_stadium = [[Marshall Field]]\n| site_cityst = Chicago, IL\n| score = 0-8\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 4\n| time = 3pm\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = Rush Medical\n| site_stadium = CAA Field\n| site_cityst = Chicago, IL\n| score = 30-0\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 12\n| time = 3:30pm\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = [[1895 Illinois Fighting Illini football team|Illinois]]\n| site_stadium = CAA Field\n| site_cityst = Chicago, IL\n| score = 8-0\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 19\n| time =\n| w/l =