 were torched in 'vast' unrest plot|date=27 November 2019|agency=Reuters|access-date=9 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191129003331/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-gasoline-protests-minister-idUSKBN1Y10GY|archive-date=29 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| casualties3  =\n|status= Over\n| arrests = 7,000+ arrested\n|place=Iran|goals=*Social and economic stability\n*Prosecution of corrupt government officials\n*Removal of [[Ali Khamenei]]\n*Regime change and removal of the [[Islamic Republic of Iran]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2019\u20132020 Iranian protests''' ({{lang-fa|\u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u0627\u062a \u0633\u0631\u0627\u0633\u0631\u06cc \u06f1\u06f3\u06f9\u06f8 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646}}) were a series of civil protests occurring nationwide across [[Iran]], initially caused by a 50%\u2013200% (approximately 6.5\u201319.5 cents US)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-iran-gasoline-rationing/iran-gasoline-rationing-price-hikes-draw-street-protests-idUKKBN1XO2ZE |title=Iran gasoline rationing, price hikes draw street protests |date=15 November 2019 |agency=[[Reuters]]  |access-date=8 December 2019 |url-status=live |quote=the price of a liter of regular gasoline was increased to 15,000 rials (12.7 U.S. cents) from 10,000 rials and the monthly ration for each private car was set at 60 litres. Additional purchases would cost 30,000 rials per liter. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209040233/https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-iran-gasoline-rationing/iran-gasoline-rationing-price-hikes-draw-street-protests-idUKKBN1XO2ZE |archive-date=9 December 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iranwatch.org/news-brief/iran-abruptly-raises-fuel-prices-protests-erupt |title=Iran Abruptly Raises Fuel Prices, and Protests Erupt |first=Farnaz|last=Fassihi|last2=Gladstone |first2=Rick |date=15 November 2019  |website=Iran Watch |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209032453/https://www.iranwatch.org/news-brief/iran-abruptly-raises-fuel-prices-protests-erupt |archive-date=8 December 2019 |quote=The changes increased the price of gas to 15,000 rials per liter (approximately 13 cents) from 10,000 rials, while limiting private cars to 60 liters per month with a price of 30,000 rials per liter for additional purchases. }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.presstv.com/Detail/2019/11/15/611285/gasoline-rationing-Iran- |title=Iran begins gasoline rationing, raises prices |date=15 November 2019 |publisher=[[Press TV]]  |access-date=8 December 2019 |url-status=live |quote=The National Iranian Oil Products Distribution Company (NIOPDC) said in a statement late Thursday that the price of a liter of regular gasoline had gone up to 15,000 rials (12.7 US cents) from 10,000 rials and the monthly ration for each private automobile was set at 60 liters per month. Additional purchases would cost 30,000 rials per liter. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191127040222/https://www.presstv.com/Detail/2019/11/15/611285/gasoline-rationing-Iran- |archive-date=27 November 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iranoilgas.com/news/details?id=20992 |title=Iran starts gasoline rationing, price hikes |date=16 November 2019  |website=IranOilGas  |access-date=8 December 2019 |url-status=live |quote=According to the report, the price of one liter of regular gasoline jumped to Rials 15,000 from Rials 10,000, while the monthly ration for each private car has been set at 60 liters per month. Additional purchases would cost Rials 30,000 per liter. }}</ref> increase in fuel prices, calling for the overthrow of the [[Government of the Islamic Republic of Iran|government in Iran]] and [[Supreme Leader of Iran|Supreme Leader]] [[Khamenei|Ali Khamenei]].<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%DA%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B4-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B6%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B2%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B4-%D9%82%DB%8C%D9%85%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D9%86%D8%B2%DB%8C%D9%86-%DB%8C%DA%A9-%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B6-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B3%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D8%B4%D9%84%DB%8C%DA%A9-%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%B4%D8%AF|title=\u06af\u0633\u062a\u0631\u0634 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u200c\u0647\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u0642\u06cc\u0645\u062a \u0628\u0646\u0632\u06cc\u0646: \u06cc\u06a9 \u0645\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0636 \u062f\u0631 \u0633\u06cc\u0631\u062c\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0627 \u0634\u0644\u06cc\u06a9 \u0645\u0627\u0645\u0648\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u06a9\u0634\u062a\u0647 \u0634\u062f|date=15 November 2019|website=[[Iran International]]|language=fa|access-date=16 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120102218/https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%DA%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B4-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B6%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B2%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B4-%D9%82%DB%8C%D9%85%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D9%86%D8%B2%DB%8C%D9%86-%DB%8C%DA%A9-%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B6-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B3%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D8%B4%D9%84%DB%8C%DA%A9-%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%B4%D8%AF|archive-date=20 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50444429|title=Protests erupt over Iran petrol rationing|date=16 November 2019|access-date=16 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116143154/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50444429|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The protests commenced in the evening of 15 November and within hours spread to 21 cities as videos of the protest began to circulate online.<ref>{{cite news |title=Amnesty International: Over 100 Killed in 21 Cities in Iran Protests |url=https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/iran/amnesty-international-over-100-killed-in-21-cities-in-iran-protests-1.8153333 |newspaper=Haaretz |date=19 November 2019 |access-date=25 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191125001205/https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/iran/amnesty-international-over-100-killed-in-21-cities-in-iran-protests-1.8153333 |archive-date=25 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"veconomist1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2019/11/17/hikes-in-the-cost-of-petrol-are-fuelling-unrest-in-iran|title=Hikes in the cost of petrol are fuelling unrest in Iran|date=17 November 2019|work=[[The Economist]]|access-date=18 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191118180140/https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2019/11/17/hikes-in-the-cost-of-petrol-are-fuelling-unrest-in-iran|archive-date=18 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-protests-fuel-price-hike/30274328.html|title=\u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u0642\u06cc\u0645\u062a \u0628\u0646\u0632\u06cc\u0646\u061b \u0634\u0647\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u062e\u062a\u0644\u0641 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0635\u062d\u0646\u0647 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u0627\u062a \u0634\u062f|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627|access-date=15 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116130231/https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-protests-fuel-price-hike/30274328.html|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Images of the violent protests were shared on the internet with protests reaching international levels.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/19/world/middleeast/iran-protests.html|title=Iran's 'Iron Fist': Rights Group Says More Than 100 Protesters Are Dead|last=Fassihi|first=Farnaz|date=19 November 2019|work=The New York Times|access-date=21 November 2019|issn=0362-4331|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120221614/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/19/world/middleeast/iran-protests.html|archive-date=20 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAlthough the protests began as peaceful gatherings, they soon turned into violent riots and revolt against the [[Government of the Islamic Republic of Iran|Iranian government]].<ref name=\"nytimes.com\">{{cite news |last1=Fassihi |first1=Farnaz |title=Iran Declares Protests Are Over, but the Evidence Suggests Otherwise |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/21/world/middleeast/iran-protests-internet.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=21 November 2019 |access-date=27 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191128005314/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/21/world/middleeast/iran-protests-internet.html |archive-date=28 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Iranian government-employed tactics to shut down the protests including a nationwide internet shutdown and, according to Amnesty international, shooting protesters dead from rooftops, helicopters, and at close range with machine gun fire. According to the residents, as reported by the New York Times, the government forces then proceeded to confiscate the bodies of the dead protesters and truck them away to mask the true casualty count and scale of the protests. Amnesty International wrote that the families of murdered protesters were threatened by the government from speaking to the media or holding funerals.<ref name=\"auto5\">{{cite web |last1=Gladstone |first1=Rick |title=With Brutal Crackdown, Iran Is Convulsed by Worst Unrest in 40 Years |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/01/world/middleeast/iran-protests-deaths.html |access-date=3 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202080816/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/01/world/middleeast/iran-protests-deaths.html |archive-date=2 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Swert |first1=Mia |title=Amnesty says at least 208 killed in Iran protests |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/amnesty-208-killed-iran-protests-191130151227593.html |access-date=3 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203143743/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/amnesty-208-killed-iran-protests-191130151227593.html |archive-date=3 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The government killed 1,500 [[Iranian peoples|Iranian]] citizens and tortures jailed protesters.<ref name=\"do whatever\" /><ref>{{cite web |last1=Williams |first1=Abigail |title=U.S. says Iran may have killed up to 1,000 protesters |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/u-s-says-iran-may-have-killed-1-000-protesters-n1096666 |publisher=NBC News |access-date=6 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191208235302/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/u-s-says-iran-may-have-killed-1-000-protesters-n1096666 |archive-date=8 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=McKenzie |first1=Sheena |title=One of the worst crackdowns in decades is happening in Iran. Here's what we know |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/12/03/middleeast/iran-protests-violent-crackdown-information-intl/index.html |publisher=CNN |access-date=3 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203233101/https://www.cnn.com/2019/12/03/middleeast/iran-protests-violent-crackdown-information-intl/index.html |archive-date=3 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The government crackdown prompted a violent reaction from protesters who destroyed 731 government banks including Iran's central bank, nine [[Islamic]] religious centres, tore down [[anti-American]] billboards, and posters and statues of the Supreme Leader [[Ali Khamenei]] as well as former leader [[Khomeini]]. 50 government military bases were also attacked by protesters. This series of protests have been categorized as the most violent and severe since the rise of [[Government of the Islamic Republic of Iran|Iran's Islamic Republic]] in 1979.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/11/iran-more-than-100-protesters-believed-to-be-killed-as-top-officials-give-green-light-to-crush-protests/|title=Iranian security forces are using lethal force to crush protests|publisher=Amnesty International|access-date=21 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122004735/https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/11/iran-more-than-100-protesters-believed-to-be-killed-as-top-officials-give-green-light-to-crush-protests/|archive-date=22 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=CASCHETTA |first1=A.J. |title=Iranian protests were not about the price of gas |url=https://thehill.com/opinion/international/472359-iranian-protests-were-not-about-the-price-of-gas |website=The Hill |access-date=4 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203070551/https://thehill.com/opinion/international/472359-iranian-protests-were-not-about-the-price-of-gas |archive-date=3 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n\nTo block the sharing of information regarding the protests and the deaths of hundreds of protesters on social media platforms, the government blocked the Internet nationwide, resulting in a near-total internet blackout of around six days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://netblocks.org/reports/internet-disrupted-in-iran-amid-fuel-protests-in-multiple-cities-pA25L18b|title=Internet disrupted in Iran amid fuel protests in multiple cities|date=15 November 2019|access-date=19 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116232625/https://netblocks.org/reports/internet-disrupted-in-iran-amid-fuel-protests-in-multiple-cities-pA25L18b|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/netblocks/status/1198215946286055424|title=Confirmed: Internet access is being restored in #Iran after a weeklong internet shutdown amid widespread protests; real-time network data show national connectivity now up to 64% of normal levels as of shutdown hour 163|last=NetBlocks.org|date=23 November 2019|website=@netblocks|access-date=24 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191123130736/https://twitter.com/netblocks/status/1198215946286055424|archive-date=23 November 2019|url-status=live}}{{Primary source inline|date=April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/11/23/iranian-masks-spiraling-protest-death-toll-stealing-bodies-morgues/|title=Iranian officials 'stealing bodies' from morgues to hide true scale of government crackdown|first1=Josie|last1=Ensor|first2=Ahmed|last2=Vahdat|date=23 November 2019|work=|newspaper=The Telegraph|access-date=24 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191123174900/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/11/23/iranian-masks-spiraling-protest-death-toll-stealing-bodies-morgues/|archive-date=23 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"albawaba.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.albawaba.com/node/mysterious-disappearances-iran-stealing-bodies-morgues-disguise-crackdown-protesters|title=Mysterious Disappearances: Is Iran Stealing Bodies From Morgues to Disguise Crackdown on Protesters?|website=Al Bawaba|access-date=24 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191129003221/https://www.albawaba.com/node/mysterious-disappearances-iran-stealing-bodies-morgues-disguise-crackdown-protesters|archive-date=29 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\n{{main|2018\u20132019 Iranian general strikes and protests}}\nAlthough sparked by the hike in oil prices the protests were widely seen as an outcry towards issues of government corruption and theft and had the goal of overthrowing the Iranian government. Government mismanagement led to rapid inflation which sent an additional 1.6&nbsp;million Iranians into poverty in just a single year prior to the protest.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Astaraki |first1=Roshanak |title=More Than Half a Million Iranian Families Forced into Poverty in 2019, Official Says |url=https://kayhanlife.com/news/iran/more-than-half-a-million-iranian-families-forced-into-poverty-in-2019-official-says/ |access-date=27 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191227042724/https://kayhanlife.com/news/iran/more-than-half-a-million-iranian-families-forced-into-poverty-in-2019-official-says/ |archive-date=27 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Batmanghelidj |first1=Esfandyar |title=Iran is losing sight of its 'developmental vision' |url=https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/iransource/iran-is-losing-sight-of-its-developmental-vision/|website=atlanticcouncil.org|access-date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIran has been experiencing continuous civil unrest since 2016 with numerous nationwide protests including the [[2016 Cyrus the Great Revolt]], [[2017\u20132018 Iranian protests]], [[2018\u20132019 Iranian general strikes and protests]], [[Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752 protests]].\n\n[[United States sanctions against Iran|Sanctions by the United States]] and [[Iran\u2013European Union relations#Sanctions|the European Union]], coupled with economic mismanagement, were factors involved in a severe economic crisis in Iran in the 2010s.<ref name=\"auto\" /> Prior to the November 2019 cycle of unrest, the [[President of Iran]] [[Hassan Rouhani]] said, \"Iran is experiencing one of its hardest years since the 1979 Islamic revolution\".<ref name=\"veconomist1\" /> \n\nMultiple protests and strikes took place in Iran in December 2017,<ref name=\"BBC_June_risingprices_demo\" /> throughout 2018<ref name=\"AlArabiya_4killed_July2018_Death2Khamenei\" /><ref name=\"BBC_2018nov_2nd_teachers_strike\" /> and in the first half of 2019.<ref name=\"RadioZamaneh_2019March_railway_workers\" /> Protest causes ranged from rising prices<ref name=\"BBC_June_risingprices_demo\" /> to teachers'<ref name=\"BBC_2018nov_2nd_teachers_strike\" /> and railway workers' rights.<ref name=\"RadioZamaneh_2019March_railway_workers\" />\n\nIn late 2019, anti-government protests took place in Iranian allies [[2019\u20132020 Lebanese protests|Lebanon]] and [[2019 Iraqi protests|Iraq]].<ref name=\"veconomist1\" />\n\nAt midnight on 15 November 2019, the Iranian government announced that they would increase the price on fuel.<ref name=\"veconomist1\" /> Prior to the price increase, drivers could buy up to {{convert|250|L|usgal}} each month for 10,000 [[Iranian rial]] per litre ($0.90 per US gallon).<ref name=\":0\" /> The new price structure had a similar monthly allotment for drivers but prices started at 15,000 rial per litre ($1.35 per US gallon) for the first {{convert|60|L|usgal}}, then 30,000 per litre ($2.70 per US gallon) after that, a price increase of 50% to 200%.<ref name=\":0\" /> An Iranian state-television programme described these measures as a way to help fund the subsidies of around 60 million Iranians.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/15/world/middleeast/iran-gasoline-prices-rations.html|title=Iran Abruptly Raises Fuel Prices, and Protests Erupt|last=Fassihi|first=Farnaz|date=15 November 2019|work=The New York Times|access-date=16 November 2019|last2=Gladstone|first2=Rick|issn=0362-4331|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191115221646/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/15/world/middleeast/iran-gasoline-prices-rations.html|archive-date=15 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBehzad Nabavi, a former member of Iran's Parliament, has said in an interview in September 2019, just two months before the uprising, that [[Astan Quds Razavi|Razavi Economic Foundation]], which contains several smaller entities, jointly with the [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps|Revolutionary Guards]] (IRGC) and the Ministry of Intelligence (MOIS) control about sixty per cent of Iran's economy. Supreme Leader, Ali Khamenei, presides over the foundation. None of these entities pay any taxes and no government organization is allowed to go through their books.<ref>[https://en.radiofarda.com/a/khamenei-s-men-run-reo-the-largest-economic-player-in-eastern-iran-/30303973.html Khamenei's Men Run REO, The Largest Economic Player In Eastern Iran] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203151709/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/khamenei-s-men-run-reo-the-largest-economic-player-in-eastern-iran-/30303973.html |date=3 December 2019 }}<blockquote></blockquote></ref>\n\nWhile Iranian people were suffering from the country's depressed economy, a decree issued by the Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei exempted some trustees from paying taxes. They included the giant organization Khatam al Anbiya Construction Headquarters, and many other smaller entities belonging to [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps]] (IRGC).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iranfocus.com/en/economy/34128-a-look-at-iran-s-2020-2021-budget |title=A Look at Iran's 2020\u20132021 Budget |access-date=14 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191214222306/https://www.iranfocus.com/en/economy/34128-a-look-at-iran-s-2020-2021-budget |archive-date=14 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Timeline==\n===November 2019===\n{{see also|Massacre of Mahshahr}}\nAfter the government announced the price increase in the early hours of 15 November, Iranians in various cities took to the streets to protest.\n\nOne protester was reportedly killed in Sirjan after security forces opened fire. Other demonstrators in the city set fire to a gas station, and chanted \"Rouhani, leave this country\".<ref name=\"auto1\" /> Protesters in [[Ahvaz]] demanded that people boycott fuel and stop their cars in the middle of the road as a sign of protest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-protests-fuel-price-hike/30274328.html|title=\u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u0642\u06cc\u0645\u062a \u0628\u0646\u0632\u06cc\u0646\u061b \u0634\u0647\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u062e\u062a\u0644\u0641 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0635\u062d\u0646\u0647 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u0627\u062a \u0634\u062f|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627|language=fa|access-date=16 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116130231/https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-protests-fuel-price-hike/30274328.html|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Mashhad]], Iran's second-largest city, demonstrators blocked traffic in the streets and highways.<ref name=\"auto\" /> Protesters gathered late into the night in [[Shahre qods|Qods]], a suburb of Tehran, and destroyed a police vehicle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ir.voanews.com/a/iran-fuel-price-protest/5168591.html|title=\u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u0627\u062a \u0628\u0647 \u06af\u0631\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u0628\u0646\u0632\u06cc\u0646 \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0647 \u062e\u0634\u0648\u0646\u062a \u06a9\u0634\u06cc\u062f\u0647 \u0634\u062f\u061b \u0645\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0636\u0627\u0646 \u062e\u06cc\u0627\u0628\u0627\u0646\u200c\u0647\u0627 \u0631\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0634\u0647\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u062e\u062a\u0644\u0641 \u0645\u0633\u062f\u0648\u062f \u06a9\u0631\u062f\u0646\u062f|website=\u0635\u062f\u0627\u06cc \u0622\u0645\u0631\u06cc\u06a9\u0627|access-date=16 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116115312/https://ir.voanews.com/a/iran-fuel-price-protest/5168591.html|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nProtests continued to expand for a second day on 16 November. Demonstrators gathered in over 50 cities and many major cities such as [[Tehran]], [[Tabriz]], [[Isfahan]], and [[Shiraz]] to protest the sudden price hike.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-fuel-hike-protests-ongoing/30275200.html|title=\u0627\u062f\u0627\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u200c\u200c\u0647\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u0642\u06cc\u0645\u062a \u0628\u0646\u0632\u06cc\u0646|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627|language=fa|access-date=16 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191117135101/https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-fuel-hike-protests-ongoing/30275200.html|archive-date=17 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Security forces shot at protesters with live bullets in an effort to disperse them, killing at least ten protesters in [[Isfahan]], [[Behbahan]], [[Kermanshah]], [[Karaj]], and [[Shiraz]].<ref name=\"auto2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-fuel-hike-protests-ongoing/30275215.html|title=\u0633\u0648\u0645\u06cc\u0646 \u0631\u0648\u0632 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u0627\u062a \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646\u061b \u0628\u06cc\u0634 \u0627\u0632 \u0647\u0632\u0627\u0631 \u0646\u0641\u0631 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u0634\u062f\u0647\u200c\u0627\u0646\u062f|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627|access-date=16 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116105033/https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-fuel-hike-protests-ongoing/30275215.html|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSeveral banks in [[Eslamshahr]], [[Behbahan]], and Tehran, and one religious school in Isfahan were burned down by protesters.<ref name=\"auto2\" /> In [[Shahriar, Tehran Province|Shahriar]] demonstrators burned down a monument depicting the ring of the [[Ruhollah Khomeini]], the founder of the Islamic Republic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/persian|title=\u0644\u062d\u0638\u0647 \u0628\u0647 \u0644\u062d\u0638\u0647 \u0628\u0627 \u062a\u062d\u0648\u0644\u0627\u062a \u06af\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0634\u062f\u0646 \u0628\u0646\u0632\u06cc\u0646\u061b \u0622\u0646\u0686\u0647 \u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a \u2013 BBC Persian|website=BBC News \u0641\u0627\u0631\u0633\u06cc|access-date=17 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191117163430/https://www.bbc.com/persian|archive-date=17 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 November, internet access across the country was reported to be in a near-total shutdown, with online activity estimated to be 7% of ordinary levels.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%D8%A7%D8%AE%D8%AA%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84-%DA%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B3%DB%8C-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%86%D8%AA-%D8%AF%D8%B1%D9%BE%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B6%E2%80%8C%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B2%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B4-%D9%82%DB%8C%D9%85%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D9%86%D8%B2%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86|title=\u0627\u062e\u062a\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u06af\u0633\u062a\u0631\u062f\u0647 \u062f\u0631 \u062f\u0633\u062a\u0631\u0633\u06cc \u0628\u0647 \u0627\u06cc\u0646\u062a\u0631\u0646\u062a \u062f\u0631\u067e\u06cc \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u200c\u200c\u0647\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u0642\u06cc\u0645\u062a \u0628\u0646\u0632\u06cc\u0646 \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646|date=16 November 2019|website=\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u06cc\u0646\u062a\u0631\u0646\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0644|access-date=17 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211013457/https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%D8%A7%D8%AE%D8%AA%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84-%DA%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B3%DB%8C-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%86%D8%AA-%D8%AF%D8%B1%D9%BE%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B6%E2%80%8C%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B2%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B4-%D9%82%DB%8C%D9%85%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D9%86%D8%B2%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86|archive-date=11 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2019/11/17/Iran-in-near-total-national-internet-shutdown-amid-ongoing-protests.html|title=Iran in 'near-total national internet shutdown' amid ongoing protests|publisher=Al Arabiya|access-date=17 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191117000529/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2019/11/17/Iran-in-near-total-national-internet-shutdown-amid-ongoing-protests.html|archive-date=17 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nState news agencies reported that over 1,000 people had been arrested so far and that the protests had spread to over 100 cities in Iran.<ref name=\"auto2\" />\n\nShop owners in Tehran and Isfahan closed the bazaars and went on strike in protest. While in Tabriz, students from the [[University of Tabriz]] left their classes and demonstrated at the university.<ref name=\"auto3\">{{Cite web|url=https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B2%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B4-%D8%B4%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D9%82%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B3%D9%88%D9%85%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B2-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B6%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%87%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%AF%D9%87%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D9%86%D9%81%D8%B1-%D8%B1%D8%B3%DB%8C%D8%AF|title=\u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u0634\u0645\u0627\u0631 \u0642\u0631\u0628\u0627\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0646 \u062f\u0631 \u0633\u0648\u0645\u06cc\u0646 \u0631\u0648\u0632 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u200c\u0647\u0627: \u062a\u0639\u062f\u0627\u062f \u06a9\u0634\u062a\u0647\u200c\u0647\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u062f\u0647\u200c\u0647\u0627 \u0646\u0641\u0631 \u0631\u0633\u06cc\u062f|date=17 November 2019|website=\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u06cc\u0646\u062a\u0631\u0646\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0644}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/persian|title=\u0644\u062d\u0638\u0647 \u0628\u0647 \u0644\u062d\u0638\u0647 \u0628\u0627 \u062a\u062d\u0648\u0644\u0627\u062a \u06af\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0634\u062f\u0646 \u0628\u0646\u0632\u06cc\u0646 \u2013 BBC Persian|website=BBC News \u0641\u0627\u0631\u0633\u06cc|access-date=17 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191117163430/https://www.bbc.com/persian|archive-date=17 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nStudents at the [[University of Tehran]] gathered for a second consecutive day to protest the current situation in the country and chanted \"Death to the dictator\", and \"Not Gaza, not Lebanon, my life only for Iran\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-fuel-hike-protests-ongoing/30275215.html|title=\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646\u062f\u0627\u0631 \u062a\u0647\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0632 \u0628\u0631\u0648\u0632 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u0627\u062a \u062f\u0631 \u0628\u06cc\u0634 \u0627\u0632 \u06f7\u06f0 \u062f\u0631\u0635\u062f \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u062e\u0628\u0631 \u062f\u0627\u062f|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627|access-date=16 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116105033/https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-fuel-hike-protests-ongoing/30275215.html|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Protests continued in the Sadeghiyeh neighbourhood of [[Tehran]], and the bazaar was packed with security forces attempting to prevent bazaar merchants from going on strike.<ref name=\"auto4\">{{Cite web|url=https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%D9%BE%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%85%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%86%D8%B4%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%AC%D9%88-%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%AA%DB%8C-%D8%AA%D8%A7-%D8%B4%D9%84%DB%8C%DA%A9-%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%82%DB%8C%D9%85-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B6%D8%A7%D9%86|title=\u067e\u06cc\u0627\u0645\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u0631\u062f\u0645\u06cc \u0628\u0647 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u06cc\u0646\u062a\u0631\u0646\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0644: \u0627\u0632 \u062c\u0648 \u0627\u0645\u0646\u06cc\u062a\u06cc \u062a\u0627 \u0634\u0644\u06cc\u06a9 \u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u06cc\u0645 \u0628\u0647 \u0645\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0636\u0627\u0646|date=18 November 2019|website=\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u06cc\u0646\u062a\u0631\u0646\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0644}}</ref> Citizens of Tehran reported that despite the internet shutdown, the protests gathered in intensity on Tuesday.<ref name=\"auto4\" />\n\nHeavy clashes were also reported in Shiraz, where the security forces fired directly at people.<ref name=\"auto4\" /> Authorities reported that nine Islamic seminaries and Friday prayer offices were burned by protesters across the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/ttack-on-kazeroon-seminary/30278787.html|title=\u062d\u0645\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0647 \u062f\u0633\u062a\u06a9\u0645 \u06f9 \u062d\u0648\u0632\u0647 \u0639\u0644\u0645\u06cc\u0647 \u0648 \u062f\u0641\u062a\u0631 \u0627\u0645\u0627\u0645 \u062c\u0645\u0639\u0647 \u062f\u0631 \u062c\u0631\u06cc\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u0627\u062a \u0628\u0647 \u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u0642\u06cc\u0645\u062a \u0628\u0646\u0632\u06cc\u0646|date=18 November 2019|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627|language=fa|url-status=live|access-date=19 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191123004240/https://www.radiofarda.com/a/ttack-on-kazeroon-seminary/30278787.html|archive-date=23 November 2019}}</ref> Protests continued for a fifth consecutive day on 19 November despite a heavy security presence the country. Gatherings were reported in [[Tehran]], [[Karaj]], [[Shiraz]] and [[Isfahan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%D9%BE%D9%86%D8%AC%D9%85%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B2-%D9%BE%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%BE%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B6%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%87-%D8%AF%D8%B1%DA%AF%DB%8C%D8%B1%DB%8C%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D9%88%D8%AC%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B2%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B4-%D8%AC%D9%88-%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%AA%DB%8C|title= \u067e\u0646\u062c\u0645\u06cc\u0646 \u0631\u0648\u0632 \u067e\u06cc\u0627\u067e\u06cc \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u200c\u0647\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646: \u0627\u062f\u0627\u0645\u0647 \u062f\u0631\u06af\u06cc\u0631\u06cc\u200c\u0647\u0627 \u0628\u0627 \u0648\u062c\u0648\u062f \u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u062c\u0648 \u0627\u0645\u0646\u06cc\u062a\u06cc|work=Iran International|date=19 November 2019|accessdate=21 November 2019|language=Persian}}</ref> The city of [[Shush, Iran|Shush]] in Khuzestan province, was effectively closed down as [[Haft Tappeh]] workers protested the current conditions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/30280867.html|title=\u0634\u0648\u0634 \u0628\u0647 \u062e\u0627\u0637\u0631 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06af\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0646\u06cc\u0634\u06a9\u0631 \u0647\u0641\u062a \u062a\u067e\u0647 \u062a\u0639\u0637\u06cc\u0644 \u0634\u062f\u0647 \u0627\u0633\u062a|work=Radio Farda|date=19 November 2019|accessdate=21 November 2019|language=Persian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120160257/https://www.radiofarda.com/a/30280867.html|archive-date=20 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Revolutionary Guards reportedly took the bodies of the dead protesters and the injured in hospitals, to hide to cover up the true death toll and downplay the protests. In some cases, government officials sold the bodies of the protesters.<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk\"/><ref name=\"albawaba.com\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=McKay |first1=Hollie |title=Brutal crackdown of Iran protesters points to increasing divide, leadership losing grip: 'The regime is afraid' |url=https://www.foxnews.com/world/iran-protest-crackdown-leadership |date=22 November 2019 |access-date=25 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191124163038/https://www.foxnews.com/world/iran-protest-crackdown-leadership |archive-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The protests reached 70% of provinces according to ''The Guardian''.<ref name=\"guardian crushed\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2019/nov/26/the-guardian-view-on-irans-protests-unrest-is-crushed-unhappiness-endures|title=The Guardian view on Iran's protests: unrest is crushed, unhappiness endures &#124; Editorial|date=26 November 2019|work=|newspaper=The Guardian|access-date=27 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191127052250/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2019/nov/26/the-guardian-view-on-irans-protests-unrest-is-crushed-unhappiness-endures|archive-date=27 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 November, Iran partially restored access to the internet. Residents of Tehran told the ''New York Times'' that the government had finished securing the northern area, but not the middle-class and working-class areas of the city.<ref name=\"nytimes evidence\"/> A 26 November ''Guardian'' editorial characterized the protests as \"crushed\".<ref name=\"guardian crushed\"/>\n\n===December===\nOn 7 December, coinciding with Students Day in Iran, students in Tehran and various other cities conducted demonstrations in support of the protests.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/fa-ir/%D8%AA%D8%AC%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA-%DB%B1%DB%B6-%D8%A2%D8%B0%D8%B1-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%AC%D9%88-%D9%85%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%85-%DA%A9%D8%A7%D8%B1%DA%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AF/a-51569800|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225193223/https://www.dw.com/fa-ir/%D8%AA%D8%AC%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA-%DB%B1%DB%B6-%D8%A2%D8%B0%D8%B1-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%AC%D9%88-%D9%85%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%85-%DA%A9%D8%A7%D8%B1%DA%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AF/a-51569800|url-status=dead|title=\u062a\u062c\u0645\u0639\u0627\u062a \u06f1\u06f6 \u0622\u0630\u0631\u061b \"\u062f\u0627\u0646\u0634\u062c\u0648 \u0645\u0639\u0644\u0645 \u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06af\u0631 \u0627\u062a\u062d\u0627\u062f \u0627\u062a\u062d\u0627\u062f\" &#124; 07.12.2019|first=Deutsche|last=Welle (www.dw.com)|archivedate=25 December 2019|website=DW.COM}}</ref> In the early hours of 17 December, students at [[Shahid Beheshti University]] in [[Tehran]] gathered outside the dormitories and protested the killing of protesters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiozamaneh.com/479862|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225193332/https://www.radiozamaneh.com/479862|url-status=dead|title=\u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636 \u0634\u0628\u0627\u0646\u0647 \u062f\u0627\u0646\u0634\u062c\u0648\u06cc\u0627\u0646 \u062e\u0648\u0627\u0628\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u06a9\u0648\u06cc \u0628\u0647\u0634\u062a\u06cc \u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u0639\u062f\u0627\u0644\u062a|date=17 December 2019|archivedate=25 December 2019|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0632\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0647}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 December, the day before the 40th day mourning procession of the protesters killed in the November protests, security forces arrested several members of [[Pouya Bakhtiari]]'s family.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A2%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%B1%DA%AF%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%85-%DA%86%D9%87%D9%84%D9%85-%D9%BE%D9%88%DB%8C%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%AA%DB%8C%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%8C%E2%80%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%B6%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%88-%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B4%D8%AA-%D8%B4%D8%AF%D9%86%D8%AF|title=\u062f\u0631 \u0622\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646\u0647 \u0628\u0631\u06af\u0632\u0627\u0631\u06cc \u0645\u0631\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0686\u0647\u0644\u0645 \u067e\u0648\u06cc\u0627 \u0628\u062e\u062a\u06cc\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u060c\u200c \u0627\u0639\u0636\u0627\u06cc \u062e\u0627\u0646\u0648\u0627\u062f\u0647 \u0627\u0648 \u0634\u0628\u0627\u0646\u0647 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f|date=24 December 2019|website=\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u06cc\u0646\u062a\u0631\u0646\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0644}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 December 2019, security forces attacked different cemeteries around Iran to prevent the families, of those killed in November uprising, from holding ceremonies in honour of the 40th day of the death of their loved ones. Some of the mourners were arrested and taken away. One month after Iranian rulers fears any anti-government gathering.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/fearing-fresh-protests-iran-security-forces-arrest-family-of-killed-protester-/30342176.html |title=Fearing Fresh Protests Iran Arrests Outspoken Family Of Slain Protester |access-date=30 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191228140533/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/fearing-fresh-protests-iran-security-forces-arrest-family-of-killed-protester-/30342176.html |archive-date=28 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2019/12/26/an-iranian-couple-wanted-mourn-son-killed-protests-now-they-are-jail/ |title=An Iranian couple wanted to mourn son killed in protests. Now they are in jail. |access-date=30 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191227143720/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2019/12/26/an-iranian-couple-wanted-mourn-son-killed-protests-now-they-are-jail/ |archive-date=27 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===January 2020===\n{{main|Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752 protests}}\n[[File:Gathering and protest rally outside Amir Kabir University 2020-01-11 10.jpg|thumb|250px|Protests at Tehran's [[:fa:\u062e\u06cc\u0627\u0628\u0627\u0646 \u062d\u0627\u0641\u0638|Hafez Street]], 11 January 2020]]\nOn 11 January 2020, after Iranian authorities had stated that [[Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752]] had been shot down by Iranian military forces, killing all 176 passengers and flight personnel,<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://edition.cnn.com/2020/01/11/middleeast/iran-shot-down-ukrainian-plane/index.html |title= Iranian protesters take to streets after Tehran admits Ukrainian plane was unintentionally shot down. }}</ref> three thousand people protested in Tehran, with chants including \"Death to the dictator\". Police used tear gas on the protestors.<ref name=\"ThomReut_protests_leaders2quit\" /> Officials reported that 82 Iranians among several other Iranians with dual citizenship were among the victims of the crash.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/iranian-protesters-demand-khamenei-quit-downing-plane-200111171757858.html|title=Protests in Tehran after Iran admits shooting down plane|publisher=Al Jazeera}}</ref> Hundreds of people protested in front of [[Amirkabir University of Technology]].<ref>[https://www.timesofisrael.com/hundreds-protest-against-regime-in-tehran-after-iran-admits-it-shot-down-plane/ \"Hundreds protest against regime in Tehran after Iran admits it shot down plane\"], ''[[The Times of Israel]]'', 11 January 2020.</ref> The protestors called for the Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei to resign, chanted \"Death to the liars\" and called \"for the IRGC to leave the country\".<ref name=\"AJE_demand_Khameini_quit\" /> Protests also took place at the [[Sharif University of Technology]] and in [[Isfahan]], [[Rasht]], [[Sari]], and [[Hamedan]]. Protesters chanted against the Revolutionary Guards, the Supreme Leader, and the entire political system of the [[Islamic Republic of Iran|Islamic Republic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/30371917.html|title=\u062a\u062c\u0645\u0639\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u06cc \u062f\u0631 \u0686\u0646\u062f \u0634\u0647\u0631 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646\u061b \u0634\u0644\u06cc\u06a9 \u062a\u06cc\u0631 \u0647\u0648\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u0648 \u06af\u0627\u0632 \u0627\u0634\u06a9\u200c\u0622\u0648\u0631 \u062f\u0631 \u062a\u0647\u0631\u0627\u0646|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627}}</ref> \n\nOn 12 January, similar protests took place around Iran. In the morning, students gathered at the dormitories of the [[University of Tehran]] and chanted against the Supreme Leader.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/persian/live/iran-51070107|title=\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0634\u0644\u06cc\u06a9 \u0628\u0647 \u0647\u0648\u0627\u067e\u06cc\u0645\u0627\u06cc \u0627\u0648\u06a9\u0631\u0627\u06cc\u0646\u06cc \u0631\u0627 \u067e\u0630\u06cc\u0631\u0641\u062a\u061b \u0628\u0631\u067e\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u062a\u062c\u0645\u0639\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u06cc \u2013 BBC Persian|website=BBC News \u0641\u0627\u0631\u0633\u06cc}}</ref> There were around 3,000 participants in the main demonstration in Tehran according to the ''[[Iranian Labour News Agency]]''.<ref name=\"ThomReut_protests_leaders2quit\" /> In [[Social networking service|online social media]] videos posted in the evening of a location near [[Azadi Square]] in Tehran, there were sounds of gunshots, pools of blood on the ground, wounded people being carried and security personnel with rifles. Hossein Rahimi of the Tehran police stated the following day that police had \"been given orders to show restraint\" and didn't shoot during the protests.<ref name=\"ThomReut_12Jan_shooting_denied\" /> The Iranian daily ''[[Etemad]]'' wrote \"Apologise and resign\" in a banner headline.<ref name=\"ThomReut_protests_leaders2quit\" /> The Iranian president described the missile attack as an unforgivable error.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51077897|title=Britain condemns Iran's arrest of UK ambassador|date=12 January 2020|via=bbc.com}}</ref>\n\nProtests continued in Tehran on 13 January, including 40 students at a Tehran university who chanted \"They killed our elites and replaced them with clerics\", in reference to the Iranian students who had died on flight AUI752.<ref name=\"ThomReut_13Jan_protests_Tehran\" />\n\nIn the video surfacing on the internet, many Tehran university students openly refused to walk over the [[Flag of the United States|American]] and [[Flag of Israel|Israeli flag]]s which was the symbol of the country's foreign policy of [[anti-Americanism]] and [[anti-Zionism]] since the inception of the Islamic Republic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/unwatch/status/1216350041193041921|title=Students in Tehran University take pains to avoid walking on the flags of U.S. & Israel\u2014as the regime forces people to do\u2014and when two Basiji regime agents then make a point of trampling the flags, the crowds shout \"Besharaf!\" #\u0628\u06cc\u200c\u0634\u0631\u0641 \u2014 the regime is shameless, dishonorable.pic.twitter.com/BLr5QKztr8|first=U. N.|last=Watch|date=12 January 2020}}{{Primary source inline|date=April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/iran-protests-crowds-tehran-refuse-walk-u-s-israeli-flags-n1114371|title=Iranians refuse to trample on U.S. and Israeli flags as protests flare|publisher=NBC News}}</ref> The flags had been painted so that protesters would walk over them as they marched.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Iran students refuse to walk over US and Israeli flags|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/av/world-middle-east-51084619/iran-students-refuse-to-walk-over-us-and-israeli-flags|website=BBC News}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 January, demonstrations took place in Iran for the fourth consecutive day. Students at various universities in [[Tehran]], and other Iranian cities continued protesting against the regime and [[Ali Khamenei]]. At [[Amir Kabir University]], protesters and the [[Basij]] clashed violently. Students at the [[University of Tehran]] chanted \"We will die to reclaim Iran\" and \"Death to the concept of a [Supreme Leader]\".<ref name=\"IranIntl_4thday_postAUI752_protests\">{{cite news | language =fa | title= \u0686\u0647\u0627\u0631\u0645\u06cc\u0646 \u0631\u0648\u0632 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u200c\u0647\u0627\u061b \u062d\u0645\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0633\u06cc\u062c\u06cc\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0647 \u062f\u0627\u0646\u0634\u062c\u0648\u06cc\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u06a9\u0628\u06cc\u0631 |trans-title = Fourth day of protests; the Basij attack Amir Kabir students<!-- trans-title is the English translation --> | date= 15 January 2020 |newspaper= [[Iran International]] | url= https://iranintl.com/\u0627\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646/\u0686\u0647\u0627\u0631\u0645\u06cc\u0646-\u0631\u0648\u0632-\u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636%E2%80%8C\u0647\u0627\u061b-\u062d\u0645\u0644\u0647-\u0628\u0633\u06cc\u062c\u06cc\u0627\u0646-\u0628\u0647-\u062f\u0627\u0646\u0634\u062c\u0648\u06cc\u0627\u0646-\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u06a9\u0628\u06cc\u0631 |accessdate=16 January 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200116010747/https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%DA%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B2-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B6%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%9B-%D8%AD%D9%85%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%B3%DB%8C%D8%AC%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%AC%D9%88%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%85%DB%8C%D8%B1%DA%A9%D8%A8%DB%8C%D8%B1 |archivedate= 16 January 2020 |url-status=live <!-- live|dead|unfit|usurped --> |url-access = <!-- (subscription/registration/limited) default=free -->}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 January 2020 students in Isfahan and other Iranian cities held their 5th day of protests, after the government of Ayatollah Khamenei admitted downing the Ukrainian passenger plane. Students held banners showing 1500+176 meaning 176 innocent passengers was added to the 1500 killed in November uprising.<ref name=\"auto10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.voanews.com/middle-east/voa-news-iran/tehran-rallies-blocked-students-take-protests-2nd-key-iran-city|title=Tehran Rallies Blocked, But Students Take Protests to 2nd Key Iran City|publisher=Voice of America}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 January 2020, protesters planned to head to the [[Islamic_Republic_of_Iran_Broadcasting|IRIB]] headquarters, however, due to a high persistence of the anti-riot police in the entire [[Valiasr Street]] which protesters planned to use as their main way to the headquarters, the demonstrations didn't take place. There was also a high persistence of police in several key points of the capital city of [[Tehran]], to prevent any gatherings to form due to the funerals that took place for those dead in the AUI752 flight, nevertheless, lots of people showed up at their funerals mourning for their dead.<ref name=\"auto10\"/>\n\n===February===\nOn the 40th day anniversary of the [[Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752]] victims memorial at [[Amir Kabir University]] on 16 February, students chanted against the ruling system and called for the boycott of the [[2020 Iranian legislative election|2020 parliamentary election]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/30436894.html|title=\u062a\u062c\u0645\u0639 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u06cc \u062f\u0627\u0646\u0634\u062c\u0648\u06cc\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u06a9\u0628\u06cc\u0631|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 February 2020, a human rights center in Iran announced that a court in Iran sentenced five persons arrested during November uprising to different prison terms from 18 months to eleven years. The five detainees, who aged between 29 to 51 years, also received different number of lashes. The state court charged them with \" collusion against national and international security\" and \"propaganda against the system\".<ref>[https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-courts-sentence-five-november-protesters-to-total-thirty-years-prison/30453121.html Iran Courts Sentence Five November Protesters To Total Thirty Years Prison]</ref>\n\nThe organization [[Human Rights Watch]] has called on the [[Geneva]] [[United Nations Human Rights Council]] to adopt \"Urgent action\" in regard to the \"brutal crackdown\" of the November protests in Iran. Michael Page, the organization's deputy director for the Middle East says, \"Iranian authorities are now confronting popular protests with an astonishing level of violence\".<ref>[https://www.rferl.org/a/hrw-calls-for-justice-for-deadly-crackdown-on-iranian-protesters/30453271.html HRW Calls For Justice For Deadly Crackdown On Iranian Protesters]</ref>\n\n== Internet shutdown ==\n{{Main|2019 Internet blackout in Iran}}\nOn the eve of the protests, Iranian authorities started disrupting internet connections and social media. The Internet was effectively blocked following Iran's [[Supreme National Security Council]] decision to shut it down for 24 hours.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/InternetIntel/status/1195986700880764929|title=Internet in Iran almost entirely offline as of 16:45 UTC on 16-Nov|last=InternetIntelligence|date=17 November 2019|website=@InternetIntel|access-date=19 November 2019}}{{Primary source inline|date=April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/11/18/middleeast/iran-protests-explained-intl/index.html|title=Iran's 'largest internet shutdown ever' is happening now. Here's what you need to know|first=Tamara |last=Qiblawi|publisher=CNN|access-date=19 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119012023/https://www.cnn.com/2019/11/18/middleeast/iran-protests-explained-intl/index.html|archive-date=19 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.macleans.ca/news/world/the-uprising-in-iran-these-people-have-nothing-to-lose-theyre-fearless-now/|title=The uprising in Iran: 'These people have nothing to lose. They're fearless now.' \u2013 Macleans.ca|website=Maclean's|access-date=19 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119055446/https://www.macleans.ca/news/world/the-uprising-in-iran-these-people-have-nothing-to-lose-theyre-fearless-now/|archive-date=19 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Iranian government and the Islamic Revolutionary Guards [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps|Sepah]] have always opposed joining popular [[social networks]] in Iran such as Facebook, Twitter and ... and blocking them in [[Iran]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2019/11/23/irans-internet-blackout/4268948002/|title='Tool of repression': Iran and regimes from Ethiopia to Venezuela limit Internet, go dark online|last=Hjelmgaard|first=Kim|website=USA Today|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/iransource/iranians-fear-a-permanent-internet-blackout-is-in-the-making/|title=Iranians fear a permanent internet blackout is in the making|date=12 December 2019|website=Atlantic Council|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/iran-internet-blackout-2019-11|title=Iran has been cut off from the internet for almost 72 hours|last=Hamilton|first=Isobel Asher|website=Business Insider|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref> But now they have decided to internet blackout in Iran.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://netblocks.org/reports/internet-restored-in-iran-after-protest-shutdown-dAmqddA9|title=Internet being restored in Iran after week-long shutdown|date=23 November 2019|website=NetBlocks|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/iran-internet-shutoff/|title=How Iran's Government Shut Off the Internet|work=Wired|access-date=12 January 2020|issn=1059-1028}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/11/22/how-did-iran-s-government-pulled-the-plug-on-the-internet|title=How did Iran's government pull the plug on the Internet?|last=Skinner|first=Helena|date=22 November 2019|website=euronews|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs per NetBlocks, users first reported outages in Mashhad on 15 November. The disruptions increased in extent and severity with impact also visible on overall connectivity charts. Iran's largest mobile network operators, including MCI, Rightel and IranCell, fell offline on the evening of 16 November 2019. By 20 November, national connectivity was at 5% of ordinary levels, making it difficult to monitor human rights violations and cover incidents on the ground.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://netblocks.org/reports/internet-disrupted-in-iran-amid-fuel-protests-in-multiple-cities-pA25L18b|title=Internet disrupted in Iran amid fuel protests in multiple cities|date=15 November 2019|website=NetBlocks|access-date=19 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116232625/https://netblocks.org/reports/internet-disrupted-in-iran-amid-fuel-protests-in-multiple-cities-pA25L18b|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe government has also jammed satellite TV connections and sent anonymous messages to people near protest sites reading: \u201cWe know you are here.\u201d<ref name=\"veconomist2\" >{{cite news|title= Rises in the price of petrol are fueling unrest in Iran|url= https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2019/11/23/rises-in-the-price-of-petrol-are-fuelling-unrest-in-iran|work= [[The Economist]]|date= 23 November 2019|access-date= 22 November 2019|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20191121180438/https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2019/11/23/rises-in-the-price-of-petrol-are-fuelling-unrest-in-iran|archive-date= 21 November 2019|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 November 2019, a small return of connectivity was tracked by NetBlocks, along with reports that some users had come online; national connectivity was up to 8%.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://netblocks.org/reports/internet-disrupted-in-iran-amid-fuel-protests-in-multiple-cities-pA25L18b|title=Internet disrupted in Iran amid fuel protests in multiple cities|date=15 November 2019|website=NetBlocks|access-date=22 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116232625/https://netblocks.org/reports/internet-disrupted-in-iran-amid-fuel-protests-in-multiple-cities-pA25L18b|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Slogans and tactics==\n===Slogans===\nChants by demonstrators targeted the government and its leaders with people chanting, \"[[Mohammad Reza Pahlavi|Shah of Iran]], return to Iran!\", \"Clerics must get lost\", \"No to Gaza, no to Lebanon. We sacrifice our lives for Iran,\" \"Death to the dictator\", \"Death to the Islamic Republic\", \"Our military brothers, why do you kill your brother?\", \"Bless your soul [[Reza Shah]]\", \"Not Gaza, not Lebanon, my life only for Iran\", \"Oil money has been lost, it has all been spent on [[Palestinian territories|Palestine]]\", \"They have brought up Islam, but trampled the people\", \"The supreme leader lives like a God. We, the people live like beggars.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%DA%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B4-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B6%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B4%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%87%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%9B-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%87%E2%80%8C%D8%B4%D8%AF%D9%86-%D8%A8%DB%8C%D8%B4-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%DB%B1%DB%B0-%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B6|title=\u06af\u0633\u062a\u0631\u0634 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u200c\u0647\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0634\u0647\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646\u061b \u06a9\u0634\u062a\u0647\u200c\u0634\u062f\u0646 \u0628\u06cc\u0634 \u0627\u0632 \u06f1\u06f0 \u0645\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0636|date=16 November 2019|website=\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u06cc\u0646\u062a\u0631\u0646\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0644|access-date=17 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211013454/https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%DA%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B4-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B6%E2%80%8C%D9%87%D8%A7-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B4%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%87%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%9B-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%87%E2%80%8C%D8%B4%D8%AF%D9%86-%D8%A8%DB%8C%D8%B4-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%DB%B1%DB%B0-%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B6|archive-date=11 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Iranians expressed their opposition to the Islamic Republic's anti-Israel efforts by chanting \"We have no money or fuel, to hell with Palestine.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sidman |first1=David |title=Mass Protests Erupt Throughout Iran, Central Bank Burned Down |url=https://www.breakingisraelnews.com/140061/mass-protests-erupt-throughout-iran-burn-down-central-bank/ |access-date=3 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203224707/https://www.breakingisraelnews.com/140061/mass-protests-erupt-throughout-iran-burn-down-central-bank/ |archive-date=3 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nChants became even more radical in the January protests, with demonstrators calling for a revolution and chanting, \"This is your last month, [Khamenei] it is time to go\", \"Clerics must get lost\", \"No reforms, no referendum, just strikes and revolution\", \"Sepah commits murders, and the Supreme Leader supports it\", \"You killed our elites, and replaced them with clerics\", and \"Death to Khamenei\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/slogans_iran_protests_leader_revolutionary_guards/30373178.html|title=\u0627\u0632 \"\u0627\u06cc\u0646 \u0645\u0627\u0647 \u0645\u0627\u0647 \u0622\u062e\u0631\u0647\"\u200c \u062a\u0627 \"\u0641\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646\u062f\u0647 \u06a9\u0644 \u0642\u0648\u0627\u060c \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0639\u0641\u0627\u060c \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0639\u0641\u0627\"|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627|language=fa|access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Tactics and methods ===\nProtesters began by organizing rallies in protest of Iran's government resulting in police gunfire. As protests were met with government crackdowns, protesters began to block streets and highways. The protests intensified with Iranians burning pictures and banners of the supreme leader [[Ali Khamenei]] and burning government banks. Many protest chants and slogans were directed at expressing discontent with the Iranian government's spending on conflicts in Gaza, Iraq, Syria, Lebanon, and Yemen. Other chants praised the late [[Mohammad Reza Pahlavi|Shah of Iran]] calling for his return.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/iran-rocked-by-protests-as-images-of-khamenei-set-on-fire-and-banks-burned-go-viral-1.8135607|title=Iran Rocked by Protests as Images of Khamenei Set on Fire and Banks Burned|website=Haaretz|access-date=19 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120120344/https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/iran-rocked-by-protests-as-images-of-khamenei-set-on-fire-and-banks-burned-go-viral-1.8135607|archive-date=20 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Support for former monarchy===\nOne common protest slogan was \"Oh [[Mohammad Reza Pahlavi|Shah of Iran]] return to Iran.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=CASCHETTA |first1=A.J. |title=Iranian protests were not about the price of gas |url=https://thehill.com/opinion/international/472359-iranian-protests-were-not-about-the-price-of-gas |website=The Hill}}</ref>\nMany protest chants praised the former Pahlavi Dynasty and its two leaders. Monarchist groups supporting the former Pahlavi monarchy were targeted and arrested by authorities across multiple cities. It was reported that some members in a monarchist organization had gone as far as infiltrating the government. During the protest the Iranian Revolutionary Guards had openly admitted the Pahlavi dynasty was popular among much of Iran's population.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/police-arrests-members-of-monarchist-network-in-iran-qom/30350324.html|title=Police Arrests Members Of 'Monarchist Network' In Iran's Religious Capital|website=RFE/RL}}</ref>\n\n== Detainees ==\n[[File:Iranian_protesters_in_November_of_2019._Isfahan.jpg|thumb|250px|November 2019 demonstrations [[Isfahan]]]]\nOn 10 December 2019 the [[Committee to Protect Journalists]] (CPJ), which is a human rights organization based in New York City, put Iran among the countries with the highest number of imprisoned journalists.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-is-among-one-of-the-top-jailers-of-journalists-in-the-world---cpj/30320648.html |title=Iran Is Among One Of the Top Jailers Of Journalists in the World \u2013 CPJ |access-date=11 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211231356/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-is-among-one-of-the-top-jailers-of-journalists-in-the-world---cpj/30320648.html |archive-date=11 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe Kurdistan Human Rights Network has stated that many detained protesters, some of them underage, are held under gruelling conditions. In addition, sources have characterized conditions in the [[Greater Tehran Central Penitentiary]] as \"unbearable\".<ref>{{cite news |title=Overcrowded Prisons And Child Prisoners in Wake Of Iran Protests |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/overcrowded-prisons-and-child-prisoners-in-wake-of-iran-protests/30303369.html |accessdate=6 December 2019 |work=[[Radio Farda]] (RFE/RL)  |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204134705/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/overcrowded-prisons-and-child-prisoners-in-wake-of-iran-protests/30303369.html |archive-date=4 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/overcrowded-prisons-and-child-prisoners-in-wake-of-iran-protests/30303369.html|title=Overcrowded Prisons And Child Prisoners in Wake Of Iran Protests|website=RFE/RL|access-date=4 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204134705/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/overcrowded-prisons-and-child-prisoners-in-wake-of-iran-protests/30303369.html|archive-date=4 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nMany observers are worried that some of those arrested have undergone severe torture and may face execution.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://iranhr.net/en/articles/4020/|title=Iran: Arrested Protesters Are In Grave Danger Of Torture And Execution|website=iranhr.net|access-date=9 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204132858/https://iranhr.net/en/articles/4020/|archive-date=4 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Arrest of journalists and lawyers ===\nThe European Parliament condemned the government of Iran for harassment of lawyers and journalists, and for denying legal assistance to the large number of protesters already in jail.<ref name=\"auto9\">{{Cite web |url=https://iranintl.com/en/world/members-eu-parliament-condemn-violent-crackdown-protesters-iran |title=Members of EU parliament condemn violent crackdown on protesters in Iran |access-date=21 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221132318/https://iranintl.com/en/world/members-eu-parliament-condemn-violent-crackdown-protesters-iran |archive-date=21 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== International organizations warn about torture ===\nIn a new statement Amnesty International has spoken about constant torture exerted on thousands arrested during November Uprising. The statement says, \"they have been beaten, punched, kicked and flogged by security forces\". Detainees include children of 15 and younger.\n\nOn 28 December 2019, international human rights watchdog has warned prisoners in Iran's jails \"are at risk of being tortured\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/amnesty-international-concerned-over-torture-of-detainees-in-iran-issues-petition/30349915.html |title=Amnesty International Concerned Over 'Torture' Of Detainees in Iran, Issues Petition |access-date=30 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230191231/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/amnesty-international-concerned-over-torture-of-detainees-in-iran-issues-petition/30349915.html |archive-date=30 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Assault on women=== \nAmnesty International's investigator on Iran, Raha Bahreini, says he has received reports that a woman protester, detained during anti- government demonstrations following the downing of Ukrainian passenger plane, has been taken to a police station and sexually assaulted by security forces.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/amnesty-says-security-agent-sexually-assaulted-a-detained-female-protester-in-iran/30385341.|title=Amnesty Says Security Agent Sexually Assaulted A Detained Female Protester in Iran}}</ref>\n\n== Deaths and casualties ==\n=== Government responsibility ===\nIran's supreme leader, Ali Khamenei, and President Hassan Rouhani ordered deadly weapons be used against the Iranians protesting the blatant rise in gasoline prices.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-protests-specialreport-idUSKBN1YR0QR|title=Special Report: Iran's leader ordered crackdown on unrest \u2013 'Do whatever it takes to end it'|date=23 December 2019|agency=Reuters|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref> Above all government entities, it is the \"Supreme National Security Council\" that makes decisions on how to deal with such demonstrations and deal with the political crisis. The Council is presided by the president. Iran's constitution prescribes that all decisions taken by the Council should be approved by Khamenei.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/joint-responsibility-of-khamenei-rouhani-for-deaths-of-iran-protesters/30293290.html|title=The Joint Responsibility Of Khamenei And Rouhani For Deaths Of Iran Protesters|website=RFE/RL|access-date=26 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191127234440/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/joint-responsibility-of-khamenei-rouhani-for-deaths-of-iran-protesters/30293290.html|archive-date=27 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> who is also [[Commander-in-Chief of the Iranian Armed Forces]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aei.org/articles/commander-of-iranian-armed-forces-khamenei-is-the-ultimate-authority/|title=Commander of Iranian armed forces: Khamenei is the ultimate authority &#124; AEI}}</ref>\n\nThe government agents in Iran were accused of stealing the bodies of the dead protesters from morgues, and arresting the injured from hospitals, to give the uprising a lower profile.<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk\"/><ref name=\"albawaba.com\"/>\n\n=== Death count estimates ===\n{{See also|Casualty recording|2019 Iraqi protests#Assassination and intimidation campaign}}\n[[File:People-died-in-iran-2019-protesters.svg|thumb|Deaths numbers by provinces<ref>{{cite web |title=World must condemn use of lethal force in Iran |url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/11/iran-world-must-strongly-condemn-use-of-lethal-force-against-protesters-as-death-toll-rises-to-143/ |publisher=Amnesty International  |access-date=6 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206083424/https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/11/iran-world-must-strongly-condemn-use-of-lethal-force-against-protesters-as-death-toll-rises-to-143/ |archive-date=6 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n{{legend|#7f0000|40 or more people killed}}\n{{legend|#bf0000|Between 30\u201339 people killed}}\n{{legend|#ff0000|Between 20\u201329 people killed}}\n{{legend|#ff5656|Between 10\u201319 people killed}}\n{{legend|#ffaaaa|Between 1\u20139 people killed}}\n{{legend|#d3d3d3|No Data}}]]\n\nOn 23 December, Reuters reported that a death toll provided by three unnamed Iranian interior ministry officials was \"about 1,500\" including \"at least 17 teenagers and about 400 women\". These numbers were described as \"fake news\" by a government spokesman.<ref>{{cite news |title=Special Report: Iran's leader ordered crackdown on unrest \u2013 'Do whatever it takes to end it' |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-protests-specialreport/special-report-irans-leader-ordered-crackdown-on-unrest-do-whatever-it-takes-to-end-it-idUSKBN1YR0QR |agency=Reuters News Agency |access-date=23 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223095916/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-protests-specialreport/special-report-irans-leader-ordered-crackdown-on-unrest-do-whatever-it-takes-to-end-it-idUSKBN1YR0QR |archive-date=23 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nA man in [[Sirjan]] was killed and several others were injured after security forces opened fire on protesters on 15 November.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.gooya.com/2019/11/post-32125.php|title=\u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u0642\u06cc\u0645\u062a \u0628\u0646\u0632\u06cc\u0646\u061b \u0634\u0647\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u062e\u062a\u0644\u0641 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0635\u062d\u0646\u0647 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u0627\u062a \u0634\u062f|website=news.gooya.com|access-date=16 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116114533/https://news.gooya.com/2019/11/post-32125.php|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/2062e5a7e6b3447d9af1b42141661f01|title=Protests grip major Iran cities over gas prices; 1 killed|date=16 November 2019|website=AP NEWS|access-date=16 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116112820/https://apnews.com/2062e5a7e6b3447d9af1b42141661f01|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The following day, ten protesters were killed during demonstrations.<ref name=\"auto2\" />\n\nThe BBC has reported that there is a huge variance in the number of people killed. Unofficial reports from various sources say that from 15 to 19 November, about 200 people were killed and 3,000 injured. UN Human Rights said \"dozens of people may have been killed\" while Amnesty International places the number at \"at least 106\". Iranian authorities say \"only a few people have been killed\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50474405|title=UN fears dozens of deaths at Iranian protests|date=19 November 2019|access-date=19 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119204532/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50474405|archive-date=19 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 November, Amnesty International claimed that around 16 people were killed in [[Kermanshah]], 14 each in [[Bandar-e Mahshahr]] and in [[Javanroud]], 9 in [[Mariwan]], 8 in [[Behbahan]], 6 each in [[Ramhormoz]], [[Sadra, Fars|Sadra]] and in [[Shiraz]], 4 each in [[Bukan]], [[Karaj]] and in [[Robatkarim]], 3 in [[Khorramshahr]], 2 each in [[Abadan]], [[Ahvaz]] and in [[Bumahen]], and 1 each in [[Tehran]], [[Isfahan]], [[Eslamshahr]], [[Sanandaj]], [[Shahriar, Tehran Province|Shahriar]] and in Sirjan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/11/iran-more-than-100-protesters-believed-to-be-killed-as-top-officials-give-green-light-to-crush-protests/|title=Iranian security forces are using lethal force to crush protests|date=19 November 2019|publisher=Amnesty International|url-status=live|access-date=19 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122004735/https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/11/iran-more-than-100-protesters-believed-to-be-killed-as-top-officials-give-green-light-to-crush-protests/|archive-date=22 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/11/iran-more-than-100-protesters-believed-to-be-killed-as-top-officials-give-green-light-to-crush-protests/|title=At least 106 protesters in 21 cities have been killed, according to credible reports received by Amnesty International. The organization believes that the real death toll may be much higher, with some reports suggesting as many as 200 have been killed.|date=|publisher=Amnesty International|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122004735/https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/11/iran-more-than-100-protesters-believed-to-be-killed-as-top-officials-give-green-light-to-crush-protests/|archive-date=22 November 2019|access-date=}}</ref> According to witness evidence reported in mid-late December, the [[Massacre of Mahshahr|Bandar-eMahshar death toll]] was much higher than initially estimated. The Iranian government brought in tanks to the streets of the city and security forces and the IRGC used heavy machine guns against unarmed people, leading to the death of 40\u2013100 people.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/exclusive-eyewitness-describes-brutal-attack-on-iran-protesters-in-mahshahr/30319712.html |title=Exclusive: Eyewitness Describes Brutal Attack On Iran Protesters In Mahshahr |access-date=18 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212144159/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/exclusive-eyewitness-describes-brutal-attack-on-iran-protesters-in-mahshahr/30319712.html |archive-date=12 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/u-s-says-iran-may-have-killed-1-000-protesters-n1096666 |title=U.S. says Iran may have killed up to 1,000 protesters |access-date=6 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191208235302/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/u-s-says-iran-may-have-killed-1-000-protesters-n1096666 |archive-date=8 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.startribune.com/with-brutal-crackdown-iran-convulsed-by-worst-unrest-in-40-years/565669582/ |title=With brutal crackdown, Iran convulsed by worst unrest in 40 years |access-date=18 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218003223/http://www.startribune.com/with-brutal-crackdown-iran-convulsed-by-worst-unrest-in-40-years/565669582/ |archive-date=18 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAs of 26 November, Amnesty International reported that over 100 people had been killed during the protests, including accounts of wounded or dead protesters removed by government authorities to hide the magnitude of the crackdown on protesters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/11/25/iran-crackdown-protesters-revealed-new-videos-internet-blackout/|title=Iran crackdown on protesters revealed in new videos after internet blackout lifted|website=The Telegraph|access-date=26 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191128185037/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/11/25/iran-crackdown-protesters-revealed-new-videos-internet-blackout/|archive-date=28 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> According to the BBC Persian, the number of deaths has exceeded 200.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50562584|title=Videos reveal brutal crackdown in Iran|first=Jiyar|last=Gol|date=27 November 2019|via=bbc.com|access-date=27 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191205103408/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50562584|archive-date=5 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to a report by ''[[TheGuardian.com|The Guardian]]'' from [[Shiraz]] on 1 December, \"those on the ground\" in the city say the death toll is much higher than the 15 confirmed deaths counted by Amnesty International.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/01/iran-fuel-protest-crackdowns-revealed-on-social-media/|title=Blocked roads then bullets: Iran's brutal crackdown in its City of Roses|website=The Guardian|access-date=3 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203023343/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/01/iran-fuel-protest-crackdowns-revealed-on-social-media|archive-date=3 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Amnesty International]] reported that the [[Iranian government]] threatened families of the killed protestors against talking to the press. The families were forced to not arrange any funerals and to instead to carry out secret burials.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/12/03/iran-acknowledges-first-time-security-forces-have-killed-protesters/|title=Iran acknowledges for first time that security forces have killed protesters|first=Associated|last=Press|date=3 December 2019|work=The Daily Telegraph|access-date=5 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203212144/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/12/03/iran-acknowledges-first-time-security-forces-have-killed-protesters/|archive-date=3 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSpeaking at a news conference at the State Department on 5 December, U.S. Special Representative for Iran Brian Hook stated that Iranian government forces killed more than 1,000 protesters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-protests-usa-idUSKBN1Y926W|title=U.S. says Iran may have killed more than 1,000 in recent protests|date=5 December 2019|agency=Reuters|access-date=9 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210010247/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-protests-usa-idUSKBN1Y926W|archive-date=10 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ncr-iran.org/en/?start=6|title=What's Happening in Iran Today &#124; Iran Freedom News Now|website=Official Website of the Foreign Affairs Committee of the National Council of Resistance of Iran. NCRI is a broad coalition of democratic Iranian organizations and personalities founded in 1981 in Tehran by Massoud Rajavi.}}</ref> There were reports by US-backed [[Radio Farda]] that by 5 December 18 children had been killed by the Iranian government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-activists-declare-mourning-days-for-protesters-killed-in-november/30309217.html|title=Iran Activists Declare Mourning Days For Protesters Killed in November|website=RFE/RL|access-date=6 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206232729/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-activists-declare-mourning-days-for-protesters-killed-in-november/30309217.html|archive-date=6 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/us-envoy-says-iran-killed-at-least-1-000-protesters/30309961.html|title=US Envoy Says Iran Might Have Killed at Least 1,000 Protesters|website=RFE/RL|access-date=6 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206163448/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/us-envoy-says-iran-killed-at-least-1-000-protesters/30309961.html|archive-date=6 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 December 2019, [[Amnesty International]] reported that at least 304 people had been killed in the protests, and described the security forces' actions as [[massacre|massacring]] the unarmed demonstrators.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://trendynewstoday.com/vicious-crackdown-iran-protest-death-toll-at-304-amnesty-says/|title='Vicious crackdown': Iran protest death toll at 304, Amnesty says|accessdate=16 December 2019|website=Trendy News Today|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219090637/https://trendynewstoday.com/vicious-crackdown-iran-protest-death-toll-at-304-amnesty-says/|archive-date=19 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 December, [[Reuters]] reported that 1,500 people, including 400 women and 17 teenagers, had been killed in the protests over the preceding month.<ref>{{citation|website=Mirror|title=Iran protests: '1,500 people, including 400 women, dead' after weeks of violence|date=23 December 2019|author=Sam Elliot|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/iran-protests-1500-people-including-21151602|access-date=23 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223201844/https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/iran-protests-1500-people-including-21151602|archive-date=23 December 2019|url-status=live}} {{citation|website=The Times of Israel|title=1,500 people said killed by Iranian security forces in protests|date=23 December 2019|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/1500-people-said-killed-by-iranian-security-forces-in-protests/|access-date=23 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223201840/https://www.timesofisrael.com/1500-people-said-killed-by-iranian-security-forces-in-protests/|archive-date=23 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAs Reuters has reported, on the second day of Iran protest, in the presence of president Hassan Rouhani, some of his ministers and commanders of the security forces, asserting the government was in total danger, Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei called to crush the demonstrators, stating \"You have my order [...] Do whatever it takes to end it\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-protests-specialreport/special-report-irans-leader-ordered-crackdown-on-unrest-do-whatever-it-takes-to-end-it-idUSKBN1YR0QR |title=Special Report: Iran's leader ordered crackdown on unrest \u2013 'Do whatever it takes to end it' |access-date=23 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223095916/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-protests-specialreport/special-report-irans-leader-ordered-crackdown-on-unrest-do-whatever-it-takes-to-end-it-idUSKBN1YR0QR |archive-date=23 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iranintl.com/en/iran/1500-protesters-killed-irans-november-uprising-khamenei%E2%80%99s-direct-order-reuters|title=1500 protesters killed in Iran's November uprising by Khamenei's direct order: Reuters|date=23 December 2019|website=Iran International}}</ref>\nAt least 1500 people, including 400 women and 17 teenagers, were killed in the uprising. Many were shot directly in the head.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://women.ncr-iran.org/2019/12/16/1500-protesters-killed-during-iran-uprising-29-women-confirmed-dead/ |title=1,500 protesters killed during Iran Uprising, 29 women confirmed dead |access-date=24 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191224140456/https://women.ncr-iran.org/2019/12/16/1500-protesters-killed-during-iran-uprising-29-women-confirmed-dead/ |archive-date=24 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.express.co.uk/news/world/1220560/URL-iran-protests-latest-november-protests-death-toll-iran-news |title=Iran protests latest: Supreme Leader's BRUTAL crackdown killed 1,500 \u2013 including 17 teens |access-date=24 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191224141346/https://www.express.co.uk/news/world/1220560/URL-iran-protests-latest-november-protests-death-toll-iran-news |archive-date=24 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Death of injured protesters ===\nHuman Rights organizations, including [[Amnesty International]], report that many Iranian protesters wounded in November demonstrations, still cannot use hospital attention as they may get arrested. Two injured protesters, Mohammad Maleki, 23 and Amir Ojani, 43 years old, died in last days of January, of acute infection and [[respiratory diseases]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/two-november-protesters-in-iran-die-of-their-gunshot-wounds/30405752.html|title=Two November Protesters in Iran Die Of Their Gunshot Wounds|website=RFE/RL}}</ref>\n\n=== Killing of children ===\nOn 3 March 2020, [[Amnesty International]] announced that security forces in Iran killed at least 23 children during November uprising in this country. The victims were 22 boys of age 12 to 17 and a girl who was under 12 years old.<ref name=\":1\">[https://www.amnestyusa.org/press-releases/at-least-23-children-killed-in-iran-by-security-forces-during-november-protests-new-evidence/ NEW EVIDENCE SHOWS AT LEAST 23 CHILDREN KILLED IN IRAN BY SECURITY FORCES DURING NOVEMBER PROTESTSSHARE]</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\nIranian news agency claimed that starting from 19 November 2019, thousands of people in cities across Iran participated in separate pro-government rallies in condemnation of the riots and showed support for the [[Supreme Leader of Iran|Iran supreme leadership]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.farsnews.com/news/13980829000504|title=From north to south of Iran against the \"rioters\"|accessdate=23 November 2019}}</ref> On 20 November 2019, Iranian President Hassan Rouhani declared victory against the \"enemy\". Iran started gradually restoring internet connection the following day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50486646|title=Iran claims victory after deadly protest crackdown|date=20 November 2019|via=bbc.com|access-date=24 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191124064813/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50486646|archive-date=24 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/iran-loosens-internet-restrictions-protest-shutdown-191121195539005.html|title=Iran loosens internet restrictions after protest shutdown|publisher=Al Jazeera|access-date=24 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191124235535/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/iran-loosens-internet-restrictions-protest-shutdown-191121195539005.html|archive-date=24 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Many supporters (including IRGC leader [[Hossein Salami]]) also called for the death penalty on anti-government protesters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/irans-guard-threatens-us-allies-over-protests/2019/11/25/87ebdb90-0f89-11ea-924c-b34d09bbc948_story.html|title=Iran's Guard threatens US, allies over protests|website=The Washington Post|access-date=25 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191127233301/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/irans-guard-threatens-us-allies-over-protests/2019/11/25/87ebdb90-0f89-11ea-924c-b34d09bbc948_story.html|archive-date=27 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Amnesty International]] stated on 16 December that one month after the uprising, Iranian security forces are still arresting people and especially youth. Prisons, such as Fashafouyeh prison near the capital [[Tehran]], are overcrowded with detainees, among them [[Minor (law)|juveniles]] of 15 and younger. Prisoners are faced with daily torture and harassment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/amnesty-says-iran-is-continuing-vicious-crackdown-on-protesters/30327845.html |title=Iran Is Continuing 'Vicious Crackdown' On Protesters, Journalists, Amnesty Says |access-date=19 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219131420/https://www.rferl.org/a/amnesty-says-iran-is-continuing-vicious-crackdown-on-protesters/30327845.html |archive-date=19 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Impacts ===\nThe savings from the fuel price rises are planned to be distributed to 18 million poor families, representing 75% of Iran's population.<ref name=\"veconomist2\" /><ref name=\"veconomist1\" /> However, with inflation already at 40% and a plummeting currency, according to ''[[The Economist]]'', \"the inflationary effects of the price rise risk wiping out most of the benefit.\"<ref name=\"veconomist1\" /> This inflationary threat has been acknowledged by Khamenei.<ref name=\"veconomist1\" />\n\n=== Debate in the Iranian parliament ===\nSeveral criticisms of the Iranian authorities were made in December 2019 by members of the [[Islamic Consultative Assembly]], the Iranian parliament. On 9 December 2019, Parvaneh Salahshouri, a female member of the parliament spoke against the country's top officials accusing them of not understanding the griefs of the low-income people and ignoring the deep-seated glitches of the country.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/outspoken-female-lawmaker-delivers-fiery-speech-in-iran-against-grim-despotism-/30316016.html |title=Outspoken Female Lawmaker Delivers Fiery Speech in Iran Against 'Grim Despotism' |access-date=12 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212230132/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/outspoken-female-lawmaker-delivers-fiery-speech-in-iran-against-grim-despotism-/30316016.html |archive-date=12 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 10 December 2019, Ali Motahari, a member of Iran's parliament spoke out against the policies of the Supreme Leader and that entities under Khamenei's control have created a stalemate in the parliament. In return another hardliner has asked the [[Guardian Council]] to disqualify Motahari as a candidate for the upcoming elections for his \"accuses the Supreme Leader in the gasoline issue\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/outspoken-iran-lawmaker-harshly-attacks-khamenei-controlled-bodies/30318288.html |title=Outspoken Lawmaker in Iran Harshly Attacks Khamenei-Controlled Bodies |access-date=12 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191214061925/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/outspoken-iran-lawmaker-harshly-attacks-khamenei-controlled-bodies/30318288.html |archive-date=14 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nFears that mass uprising could ignite again created conflicts within the Iranian ruling system. In early December 2019, Mahmood Alavi, the [[Intelligence]] Minister, has sent a letter to the speaker of the parliament asking him to stop Mahmood Sadeghi, a member of Parliament, acting \"against national interests\". Since the protests began in November, Sadeghi continued his attacks against some government entities, including the intelligence system. Sadeghi has also spoken against the [[forced confessions]] run by the Ministry of Intelligence and shown on state television.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/intelligence-min-demands-outspoken-lawmaker-not-to-go-against-national-interest-/30338999.html |title=Intelligence Min Demands Outspoken Lawmaker Not To Go Against 'National Interest' |access-date=23 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223131257/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/intelligence-min-demands-outspoken-lawmaker-not-to-go-against-national-interest-/30338999.html |archive-date=23 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n== Reactions ==\n=== National ===\n* Supreme Leader of Iran, [[Ali Khamenei]]\n**At the beginning of Dars-e Kharej on 17 November, he remarked that he was not an expert in this regard, but this policy had been adopted by the heads of the country, based on expert opinion. Therefore, this decision should be acted on. He said that in any case, some people had become displeased, but setting fire to such and such a bank was not the action of the people; rather it was the action of thugs. Such actions were not carried out by ordinary people, Khamenei claimed. \"Of course, officials should also pay attention and decrease the problems associated as much as they can.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Khamenei's stance on recent events in Iran |url=http://english.khamenei.ir/news/7183/Imam-Khamenei-s-stance-on-recent-events-in-Iran |website=khamenei.ir |accessdate=19 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206163140/http://english.khamenei.ir/news/7183/Imam-Khamenei-s-stance-on-recent-events-in-Iran |archive-date=6 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Iran Supreme Leader Backs Govt's Petrol Price Hike |url=https://www.news18.com/news/world/iran-supreme-leader-backs-govts-petrol-price-hike-warns-thugs-bandits-amid-violent-protests-2389905.html |accessdate=19 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191118140446/https://www.news18.com/news/world/iran-supreme-leader-backs-govts-petrol-price-hike-warns-thugs-bandits-amid-violent-protests-2389905.html |archive-date=18 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Khamenei also blamed the protests on \"all of the centres of villainy around the world that oppose us.\"<ref name=\"veconomist1\" />\n**Also at a meeting with producers, economic activists and entrepreneurs on 19 November he stated: \"Both friends and foes should know that we have repelled the enemy in the war in military, political and security issues. The recent actions were security issues, not from the people. We have repelled the enemy in various areas, and by God's grace, we will also definitely repel the enemy in the economic war.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Friends and foes should know that in the recent security issues we have repelled the enemy |url=http://english.khamenei.ir/news/7189/Friends-and-foes-should-know-that-in-the-recent-security-issues |accessdate=20 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120112913/http://english.khamenei.ir/news/7189/Friends-and-foes-should-know-that-in-the-recent-security-issues |archive-date=20 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Friends, foes should know enemy repelled by Iran |url=https://en.irna.ir/news/83561918/Supreme-Leader-Friends-foes-should-know-enemy-repelled-by |accessdate=20 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120053221/https://en.irna.ir/news/83561918/Supreme-Leader-Friends-foes-should-know-enemy-repelled-by |archive-date=20 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Iran Successfully Tackles Security Issues, Will 'Repel Enemy in Economic War |url=https://sputniknews.com/middleeast/201911201077354265-iran-successfully-tackles-security-issues-will-repel-enemy-in-economic-war---khamenei/ |accessdate=20 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120115605/https://sputniknews.com/middleeast/201911201077354265-iran-successfully-tackles-security-issues-will-repel-enemy-in-economic-war---khamenei/ |archive-date=20 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*[[Reza Pahlavi, Crown Prince of Iran|Reza Pahlavi]], the son of Iran's deposed Shah, tweeted that the Islamic Republic had brought only poverty and suffering to the Iranian people. He also said that the only thing offered for free by the Islamic Republic was oil to its allies in the region, a reference to [[Syria]]'s president [[Bashar Assad]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-s-exiled-prince-calls-for-overthrow-of-regime-amid-protests/30275155.html|title=Iran's Exiled Prince Calls For Overthrow Of Regime Amid Protests|website=RFE/RL|access-date=16 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116152307/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-s-exiled-prince-calls-for-overthrow-of-regime-amid-protests/30275155.html|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Parvaneh Salahshouri]], a member of parliament, stated that the decision to increase the price of fuel was not made by the [[Islamic Consultative Assembly|Majles]] and had been made by the heads of the three branches. Salahshouri stated, \"It has been a while now that parliament is not involved in the decision-making process.\" She continued and, referring to the parliament, said, \"The last semblance of a democracy we had is no more. Shut down the next parliament, it is an act of economic resistance\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilna.news/\u0628\u062e\u0634-%D8%B3%DB%8C%D8%A7%D8%B3%DB%8C-3/835056-%D8%AE%DB%8C%D9%84%DB%8C-%D9%88%D9%82%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA-%DA%A9%D9%87-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%84%D8%B3-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B1%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B1-%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%84%D8%B3-%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%B7%DB%8C%D9%84-%DA%A9%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%AF|title=\u062e\u06cc\u0644\u06cc \u0648\u0642\u062a \u0627\u0633\u062a \u06a9\u0647 \u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633 \u062f\u0631 \u0631\u0623\u0633 \u0627\u0645\u0648\u0631 \u0646\u06cc\u0633\u062a/ \u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633 \u0628\u0639\u062f\u06cc \u0631\u0627 \u062a\u0639\u0637\u06cc\u0644 \u06a9\u0646\u06cc\u062f|website=\u062e\u0628\u0631\u06af\u0632\u0627\u0631\u06cc \u0627\u06cc\u0644\u0646\u0627}}</ref>\n*Grand Ayatollah [[Mohammad Alavi Gorgani]] asked the government to \"change their decision to increase fuel prices before it is too late\".<ref name=\"auto2\" />\n* Abolfazl Bahrampour, prominent Iranian [[Quran]] scholar, stated that the arrested protesters are [[Muharib]] and do not deserve normal execution, but must be tortured to death by [[mutilation]] of their right hands and left feet. He made these comments in the Iranian state-sponsored [[IRIB TV1]] citing the 33rd [[Ayah]] of [[Al-Ma'ida]] [[Surah]]: \"... The only punishment of those who wage war against [[Allah]] and [[Muhammad|His Messenger]] and strive to make mischief in the land is that they should be murdered, or [[crucification|crucified]], or their hands and their feet should be cut off on opposite sides ...\".<ref>{{cite web |title=\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0633 \u0635\u062f\u0627\u0648\u0633\u06cc\u0645\u0627 \u062e\u0648\u0627\u0647\u0627\u0646 \u0632\u062c\u0631\u06a9\u0634 \u06a9\u0631\u062f\u0646 \u0648 \u0642\u0637\u0639 \u062f\u0633\u062a \u0648 \u067e\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0636\u0627\u0646 \u0634\u062f.|url=https://iranintl.com/%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/%DA%A9%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B4%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%B3-%D8%B5%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%88%D8%B3%DB%8C%D9%85%D8%A7-%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%87%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%B2%D8%AC%D8%B1%DA%A9%D8%B4-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86-%D9%88-%D9%82%D8%B7%D8%B9-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D9%88-%D9%BE%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%B6%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%B4%D8%AF|accessdate=29 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0633 \u062f\u06cc\u0646\u06cc \u062f\u0631 \u062a\u0644\u0648\u06cc\u0632\u06cc\u0648\u0646 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u062e\u0648\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0631 \"\u0632\u062c\u0631\u06a9\u0634\" \u06a9\u0631\u062f\u0646 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u200c\u0634\u062f\u06af\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0636\u0627\u062a \u0634\u062f|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/bahrampour-tv-protests/30296208.html|accessdate=29 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191128182028/https://www.radiofarda.com/a/bahrampour-tv-protests/30296208.html|archive-date=28 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\"Religious Expert\" Advocates Torturing Protesters On State Television|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/religious-expert-advocates-torturing-protesters-on-state-television/30297307.html|accessdate=30 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191129165356/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/religious-expert-advocates-torturing-protesters-on-state-television/30297307.html|archive-date=29 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Dozens of artists living inside Iran published a statement in support of protesters, saying they will not forget the young faces of the dead, who were killed and then ignored by associating them with \"foreigners\". The statement condemned the violation of the people's \"most basic human rights\" and their \"most apparent needs\", and warned that people's voices \"will remain in history\". Prominent filmmakers including two-time Oscar winner [[Asghar Farhadi]] and Berlinale-winner [[Jafar Panahi]], as well as well-known musicians [[Hossein Alizadeh]] and [[Kayhan Kalhor]], are among the signatories of the statement. The statement also ridicules speeches by Iranian officials who have blamed protesters as being agents of foreign states, saying \"the regime is trying to justify killing them\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/in-sympathy-with-mourning-iranians-film-director-not-celebrating-80th-birthday-/30314154.html|title=In Sympathy With Mourning Iranians Film Director Not Celebrating 80TH Birthday|website=RFE/RL|access-date=8 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191208223253/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/in-sympathy-with-mourning-iranians-film-director-not-celebrating-80th-birthday-/30314154.html|archive-date=8 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Golshifteh Farahani]], an Iranian actress who has been living in exile in France for the past decade, also carried out an extensive interview about the violent response to protests and the high number of people killed, wounded, or arrested. Speaking to Brut America, Farahani explained that many protesters started demonstrating because of a hike in gas prices, but \"never came back home\". In the video, the actress stated that the killed protesters were \"son of some people\", \"fathers of some people\", \"daughters of some people\", and \"they are dead now\".<ref name=\"auto7\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/politics/iran-protests-latest-artists-directors-musicians-asghar-farhadi-jafar-panahi-golshifteh-farahani-a9246216.html |title=Iranian artists speak up against deadly crackdown of protests |access-date=22 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221214426/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/politics/iran-protests-latest-artists-directors-musicians-asghar-farhadi-jafar-panahi-golshifteh-farahani-a9246216.html |archive-date=21 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*[[Hichkas]], Iranian rapper released a song about the recent protests and the inequality that plagues the Iranian society. In the song, titled \"Clenched His Fists\", the exiled rapper states the various grievances that led to the demonstrations and describes the brutality of the security forces. The song is in the spoken word format and includes audio snippets recorded by protesters on the street, where voices can be heard saying \"they are shooting people\".<ref name=\"auto7\"/>\n\n==== University students ====\nOn 7 December 2019, commemorating the student's day. university students in various parts of Iran organized rallies shouting slogans against Hassan Rouhani and chief Justice Ebrahim Raeesi. Students also condemned the government for shooting and killing people during recent demonstrations.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/students-in-iran-hold-anti-government-rallies-chanting-freedom-unity-/30312954.html |title=Students in Iran Hold Anti-Government Rallies Chanting 'Freedom', 'Unity' |access-date=9 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209153126/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/students-in-iran-hold-anti-government-rallies-chanting-freedom-unity-/30312954.html |archive-date=9 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==== Bus drivers ====\nOn 2 December 2019, the Tehran bus drivers' trade union called for the trial of those who ordered the shooting of the protesters. The union described the government's actions as a \"massacre and bloody suppression\". The statement by the Syndicate of Tehran and Suburbs Bus Company, also expressed concern about the situation of the thousands of detained protesters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/tehran-bus-company-workers-condemn-iran-crackdown-demand-trials/30301871.html|title=Tehran Bus Company Workers Condemn Iran Crackdown, Demand Trials|website=RFE/RL|access-date=2 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202135107/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/tehran-bus-company-workers-condemn-iran-crackdown-demand-trials/30301871.html|archive-date=2 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Lawyers ====\nOn 10 December 2019, 160 Iranian lawyers called for an investigation into the November killings. The lawyers also called for information regarding the several thousand detained protestors.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/iranian-lawyers-call-for-probe-into-deadly-crackdown-on-protests/30318670.html |title=Iranian Lawyers Call For Probe into Deadly Crackdown On Protests |access-date=12 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212152209/https://www.rferl.org/a/iranian-lawyers-call-for-probe-into-deadly-crackdown-on-protests/30318670.html |archive-date=12 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==== Mournings ====\nIranian regime threatens the families of those killed in recent protests not to talk to reporters or others. Nevertheless, families of young people killed by the regime's security forces are not giving in. Mother of Pooya Bakhtiari, killed by government agents, says her son was a \"national hero\". She continued that her son pursued \"freedom, justice and truth\", something that Iran's authorities will not grant to the people.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/mother-of-young-protester-killed-in-iran-says-she-will-not-accept-blood-money-/30309908.html |title=Exclusive: Mother Of Young Protester Killed In Iran Rejects 'Blood Money' |access-date=9 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209153126/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/mother-of-young-protester-killed-in-iran-says-she-will-not-accept-blood-money-/30309908.html |archive-date=9 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== International ===\n==== States ====\n*{{flagicon|USA}} United States:\n**U.S. President of the United States [[Donald Trump]] announced his support for the protests stating \"Iran has become so unstable that the government has shut down their entire Internet System so that the Great Iranian people cannot talk about the tremendous violence taking place within the country....\"<ref name=\"nytimes.com\"/>\n**U.S. Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]] supported the demonstrations and stated that \"The United States is with [the Iranian people]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.trust.org/item/20191116211712-2i1ij/|title=Iran's protests against gasoline price hike turn political \u2013 media|first=Thomson Reuters|last=Foundation|website=news.trust.org|access-date=17 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116224052/http://news.trust.org/item/20191116211712-2i1ij/|archive-date=16 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n**The [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] Presidential candidate [[Bernie Sanders]] criticized the [[Government of Iran|Iranian government]] for not letting its civilians protest for a \"better future\" and to stop \"showing violence against demonstrators.\"{{cn|date=December 2019}}\n** On 3 December, US President [[Donald Trump]], while attending NATO summit in London, said, \"Iran is killing perhaps thousands and thousands of people right now as we speak\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://aawsat.com/english/home/article/2018671/trump-accuses-iran-%E2%80%98killing-thousands%E2%80%99-protesters|title=Trump Accuses Iran of 'Killing Thousands' of Protesters|website=Asharq AL-awsat|access-date=5 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191205152348/https://aawsat.com/english/home/article/2018671/trump-accuses-iran-%25E2%2580%2598killing-thousands%25E2%2580%2599-protesters|archive-date=5 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n** The United States said that the Iranian government had committed \"gross human rights violations\" during the protests.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/iran-protests-state-departments-brian-hook-says-iran-could-have-murdered-over-a-thousand-protesters/|title=U.S. says Iran \"could have murdered over a thousand\" citizens during protests|publisher=CBS News|access-date=9 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207081533/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/iran-protests-state-departments-brian-hook-says-iran-could-have-murdered-over-a-thousand-protesters/|archive-date=7 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|European Union}} [[European Union]]:\n**[[Josep Borrell]], European Union's new High Representative for Foreign Affairs has condemned the use of deadly force by the Iranian regime against peaceful demonstrators.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/new-eu-foreign-policy-chief-condemns-iran-s-disproportionate-use-of-force-in-protests/30315654.html |title=New EU Foreign Policy Chief Condemns Iran's 'Disproportionate' Use Of Force in Protests |access-date=10 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210225252/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/new-eu-foreign-policy-chief-condemns-iran-s-disproportionate-use-of-force-in-protests/30315654.html |archive-date=10 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n**Almost all political groups and tendencies in the [[European Parliament]] voted in favour of a resolution which condemned the Iranian government for its extensive use of force against peaceful protesters in November uprising.  European lawmakers called for an independent investigation into atrocities including direct shooting at demonstrators. The resolution calls on the Iranian government \"to announce the total number of detainees\".<ref name=\"auto8\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.europarl.europa.eu/news/en/press-room/20191217IPR69210/meps-condemn-violent-crackdown-on-the-recent-protests-in-iran |title=MEPs condemn violent crackdown on the recent protests in Iran |access-date=21 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221143937/https://www.europarl.europa.eu/news/en/press-room/20191217IPR69210/meps-condemn-violent-crackdown-on-the-recent-protests-in-iran |archive-date=21 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"auto6\">{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/european-parliament-deplores-iran-use-of-force-against-protesters-/30334343.html |title=European Parliament Deplores Iran's 'Widespread' Use Of Force Against Protesters |access-date=21 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220213815/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/european-parliament-deplores-iran-use-of-force-against-protesters-/30334343.html |archive-date=20 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The European parliament condemned the government of Iran for harassment of lawyers and journalists, and for denying legal assistance to the large number of protesters already in jail.<ref name=\"auto9\"/>\n*{{flagicon|Germany}} Germany: Chancellery urged Iran to respect the \"legitimate\" protests against a petrol price hike and open talks with the demonstrators: \"It is legitimate and deserving of our respect when people courageously air their economic and political grievances, as is currently happening in Iran,\" said Chancellor Angela Merkel's spokeswoman, Ulrike Demmer.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2019/11/18/germany-urges-iran-to-respect-legitimate-protests |title=Germany urges Iran to respect 'legitimate' protests |access-date=22 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222102219/https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2019/11/18/germany-urges-iran-to-respect-legitimate-protests |archive-date=22 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|France}} France: The French government said on Wednesday it was deeply concerned about reports of many deaths during protests in Iran and called on Tehran to respect its international human rights duties. France \"expresses its deep concern over reports of the deaths of many demonstrators in recent days,\" Foreign ministry spokeswoman Agnes von der Muhll told reporters in a daily online briefing. \"France calls on Iran to respect its international human rights obligations.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-gasoline-protests-france/france-says-concerned-by-reports-of-many-deaths-in-iran-protests-idUSKBN1XU1Y8 |title=France says concerned by reports of many deaths in Iran protests |access-date=22 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120200603/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-gasoline-protests-france/france-says-concerned-by-reports-of-many-deaths-in-iran-protests-idUSKBN1XU1Y8 |archive-date=20 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|Sweden}} Sweden: Foreign Minister [[Ann Linde]] wrote on Twitter: \"Terrible casualties in Iran. Nothing can justify this violence. Today's ambassador to Sweden from Our view is informed.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mbs.news/2019/11/swedens-foreign-minister-has-responded-to-the-protests-in-iran.html |title=Sweden's foreign minister has responded to the protests in Iran |access-date=22 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222103721/https://www.mbs.news/2019/11/swedens-foreign-minister-has-responded-to-the-protests-in-iran.html |archive-date=22 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==== Supernationals ====\n* {{flagicon|UN}} United Nations: The [[UN High Commissioner for Human Rights]] [[Michelle Bachelet]] expressed her \"deep concern\" about the treatment of the large number of people arrested in the demonstrations. She also expressed concern about torture or execution of detainees.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.un.org/en/story/2019/12/1052911|title=UN rights chief 'extremely concerned' over deadly crackdown on protesters in Iran|date=6 December 2019|website=UN News|access-date=6 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206230203/https://news.un.org/en/story/2019/12/1052911|archive-date=6 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* [[Amnesty International]] started a petition in which human rights organisations asked United Nations (UN) member states to condemn the Iranian government for the crackdown on the unarmed protesters in the November uprising. The signatories include [[International Federation for Human Rights]] (FIDH), [[Human Rights Watch]] (HRW), [[Justice for Iran]] and Amnesty International.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/rights-organizations-urge-un-members-to-condemn-iran-human-rights-violations/30318461.html |title=Rights Organizations Urge UN Members To Condemn Iran Human Rights Violations |access-date=11 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211231408/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/rights-organizations-urge-un-members-to-condemn-iran-human-rights-violations/30318461.html |archive-date=11 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> \"There must be independent and impartial investigations into these killings, and those suspected of ordering and carrying them out must be prosecuted in fair trials,\" said Philip Luther, Research and Advocacy Director for the Middle East and North Africa at Amnesty International, in response to the killing of at least 23 children by security forces.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n=== Sanctions after November uprising  ===\nThe United States implemented sanctions on [[Mohammad-Javad Azari Jahromi]], Iran's communications minister, following the deactivation of internet servers inside Iran.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/ajimpact/sanctions-iran-information-minister-internet-blackout-191122172936019.html|title=US sanctions Iran's information minister over internet blackout|publisher=Al Jazeera|access-date=24 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191124195937/https://www.aljazeera.com/ajimpact/sanctions-iran-information-minister-internet-blackout-191122172936019.html|archive-date=24 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 December 2019, the United States Government enforced sanctions on two Iranian judges, Abolghassem Salavati and Mohammad Moghisseh, for suppressing \"freedoms of speech and assembly\".\nThousands of people are now in Iran's jails just for participating in November uprising. They may face torture or even execution. The two judges have long records of issuing long term prison sentences or death penalties<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://justice4iran.org/9603/ |title=Human rights violator: Mohammad Moghisseh (Nasserian) |access-date=20 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220110937/https://justice4iran.org/9603/ |archive-date=20 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ipa.united4iran.org/en/judge/5/ |title=JUDGEABOLGHASEM SALAVATI |access-date=20 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220110936/https://ipa.united4iran.org/en/judge/5/ |archive-date=20 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> for Iranians longing for democracy and opposed to the rule of the Supreme Leader, Ali Khamenei.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/u-s-imposes-sanctions-on-two-iranian-judges-for-oppression-/30334404.html |title=U.S. Imposes Sanctions On Two Iranian Judges For 'Oppression' |access-date=20 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220110213/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/u-s-imposes-sanctions-on-two-iranian-judges-for-oppression-/30334404.html |archive-date=20 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[2017\u20132018 Iranian protests]]\n* [[2018\u20132019 Iranian general strikes and protests]]\n* [[Iraqi protests (2019\u2013present)|2019\u20132020 Iraqi protests]]\n* [[Protests of 2019]]\n* [[2019\u20132020 Lebanese protests]]\n* [[2019\u20132020 Persian Gulf crisis|2019\u20132020 Persian Gulf crisis]]\n* [[Human rights in Iran]]\n* [[Internet censorship in Iran]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<!-- also: late Dec 2017/early Jan 2018 \"large-scale anti-gov economic demos\" -->\n<ref name=\"BBC_June_risingprices_demo\">{{cite news | title= Iran economic protests shut Tehran's Grand Bazaa |trans-title = <!-- trans-title is the English translation --> | date= 25 June 2018 |newspaper= [[BBC News]] | url= https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-44602189 |accessdate=11 January 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20180701072618/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-44602189 |archivedate=1 July 2018 |url-status=live <!-- live|dead|unfit|usurped -->}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AlArabiya_4killed_July2018_Death2Khamenei\">{{cite news | title= Four protesters killed in southwestern Iran after security forces open fire |trans-title = <!-- trans-title is the English translation --> | date= 1 July 2018 |publisher= [[Al Arabiya]] | url= https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2018/07/01/Four-protesters-killed-in-southwestern-Iran-after-security-forces-open-fire.html |accessdate=11 January 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20180630213729/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2018/07/01/Four-protesters-killed-in-southwestern-Iran-after-security-forces-open-fire.html |archivedate= 30 June 2018 |url-status=live <!-- live|dead|unfit|usurped -->}}</ref>\n\n<!-- second 2018 teachers' strike in November 2018 -->\n<ref name=\"BBC_2018nov_2nd_teachers_strike\">{{cite news | language =fa | title= \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0635\u0627\u0628 \u0645\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0646\u061b \u0645\u0639\u062a\u0631\u0636\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u0648 \u0627\u062d\u0636\u0627\u0631 \u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f |trans-title = Teachers' strike; protesters were arrested<!-- trans-title is the English translation --> | date= 24 November 2018 |newspaper= [[BBC News]] | url= https://www.bbc.com/persian/iran-46225416 |a