all players at the 1982 NCAA Men's Division I Final Four]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1983 Pan American Games]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1984 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Basketball players from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Basketball players from North Carolina]]\n[[Category:Birmingham Barons players]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Illinois]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from New York City]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from North Carolina]]\n[[Category:Charlotte Bobcats executives]]\n[[Category:Charlotte Bobcats owners]]\n[[Category:Charlotte Hornets executives]]\n[[Category:Chicago Bulls draft picks]]\n[[Category:Chicago Bulls players]]\n[[Category:FIBA Hall of Fame inductees]]\n[[Category:McDonald's High School All-Americans]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1984 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame inductees]]\n[[Category:National Basketball Association All-Stars]]\n[[Category:National Basketball Association players with retired numbers]]\n[[Category:North Carolina Tar Heels men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for the United States in basketball]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games gold medalists for the United States]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games medalists in basketball]]\n[[Category:Parade High School All-Americans (boys' basketball)]]\n[[Category:People from Highland Park, Illinois]]\n[[Category:Presidential Medal of Freedom recipients]]\n[[Category:Scottsdale Scorpions players]]\n[[Category:Shoe designers]]\n[[Category:Shooting guards]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Wilmington, North Carolina]]\n[[Category:United States men's national basketball team players]]\n[[Category:Washington Wizards executives]]\n[[Category:Washington Wizards players]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{short description|American basketball player and businessman}}\n{{about-otherpeople|the American basketball player}}\n{{Use American English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{pp-semi-blp|small=yes}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Michael Jordan\n| image = Michael Jordan in 2014.jpg\n| caption = Jordan in 2014\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1963|2|17}}\n| birth_place = [[New York City, New York]]<!---Check Infobox basketball biography template style--->\n| league          = [[NBA]]\n| team            = Charlotte Hornets\n| position        = Owner\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 6\n| weight_lbs = 216\n| nationality = American\n| high_school = [[Emsley A. Laney High School|Emsley A. Laney]]<br />([[Wilmington, North Carolina]])\n| college = [[North Carolina Tar Heels men's basketball|North Carolina]] (1981\u20131984)\n| draftyear = 1984\n| draftround = 1\n| draftpick = 3\n| draftteam = [[Chicago Bulls]]\n| career_start = 1984\u20131993, 1995\u20131998, 2001\n| career_end = 2003\n| career_position = [[Shooting guard]] / [[Small forward]]<ref name=\"BBRMJ\"/>\n| career_number = 23, 12,{{efn|Jordan wore a nameless No. 12 jersey in a February 14, 1990 game against the [[Orlando Magic]] because his No. 23 jersey had been stolen.<ref>Strauss, Chris. \"[https://www.usatoday.com/story/gameon/2012/12/12/nba-jordan-bulls-12/1763265/ The greatest No. 12 that no one is talking about]\", ''USA Today'', December 12, 2012. Retrieved December 12, 2012.</ref> Jordan scored 49 points, setting a franchise record for players wearing that jersey number.<ref>Smith, Sam (February 15, 1990). \"Magic has the Bulls' number: Catledge leads rally; Jordan scores 49 points\", ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'', p. A1.</ref>}} 45\n| years1 = {{nbay|1984|start}}\u2013{{nbay|1992|end}},<br />{{nbay|1994|end}}\u2013{{nbay|1997|end}}\n| team1 = [[Chicago Bulls]]\n| years2 = {{nbay|2001|start}}\u2013{{nbay|2002|end}}\n| team2 = [[Washington Wizards]]\n| highlights = \n* 6\u00d7 [[List of NBA champions|NBA champion]] ({{n