160805230646/http://www.style.it/vanitypeople/show/musica/2010/10/04/tiziano-ferro-fa-due-con-laura-pausini.aspx#?refresh_ce|archivedate=5 August 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[Rai Due]]\n|Music TV show \u2013 1 episode as main performer and presenter, shared with [[Tiziano Ferro]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2014\n!scope=\"row\"|''Laura Pausini 20 \u2013 My Story''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://skyuno.sky.it/skyuno/news/2013/12/12/laura_pausini_vent_anni_carriera_sky_uno_intervista.html|publisher=[[Sky Uno]]|language=Italian|accessdate=4 April 2016|title=Vent'anni di Laura Pausini, una storia speciale|author=Fabrizio Basso|date=10 January 2010}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[Sky Italia]]\n|Autobiographical documentary \u2013 1 episode\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Stasera Laura: ho creduto in un sogno''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panorama.it/musica/stasera-laura-pausini-raiuno/|work=[[Panorama (magazine)|Panorama]]|language=Italian|accessdate=5 April 2016|title=Stasera Laura su Raiuno. La Pausini, le emozioni|author=Alessandro Alicandri|date=21 May 2014}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[Rai Uno]]\n|Music TV show & concert \u2013 1 episode, main performer and presenter\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2014, 2017\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[La Voz... M\u00e9xico]]''<ref name=\"La Voz Mexico\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/espectaculos/television/la-voz-mexico-se-va-la-segura-y-retoma-viejos-coaches|work=[[El Universal (M\u00e9xico)|El Universal]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=6 October 2017|title=La voz M\u00e9xico se va a la segura y retoma a viejos coaches|date=26 August 2017|author=Ariel Le\u00f3n}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[Canal de las Estrellas]]\n|[[Talent show]] \u2013 series 4 and series 6 judge and coach\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2015\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[La Voz (Spanish TV series)|La Voz]]''<ref name=\"La Voz Spain\"/>\n|Herself\n|[[Telecinco]]\n|Talent show \u2013 series 3 judge and coach\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''La meraviglia di essere simili''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sorrisi.com/tv/news-e-anticipazioni/laura-pausini-la-meraviglia-di-essere-simili-in-onda-21-novembre-2015/|work=[[TV Sorrisi e Canzoni]]|language=Italian|accessdate=5 April 2016|title=Laura Pausini, \"La meraviglia di essere Simili\" in onda il 21/11|author=Antonio Mustara|date=17 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170929044355/http://www.sorrisi.com/tv/news-e-anticipazioni/laura-pausini-la-meraviglia-di-essere-simili-in-onda-21-novembre-2015/|archive-date=29 September 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|Rai Uno\n|Documentary \u2013 1 episode, TV special documenting her twelfth studio album, ''[[Simili (album)|Simili]]''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2015\u20132016\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[La Banda (TV series)|La Banda]]''<ref name=\"La Banda\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latintimes.com/la-banda-2-judges-univision-reveals-which-two-artists-join-laura-pausini-reality-show-392403|work=[[Latin Times]]|accessdate=26 November 2016|title=La Banda 2 Judges: Univision Reveals Which Two Artists Join Laura Pausini In Reality Show|author=Jessica Lucia Roiz|date=30 June 2016}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[Univision]]\n|Talent show \u2013 series 1 and series 2 judge\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2016\n!scope=\"row\"|''Laura & Paola''<ref name=\"Laura e Paola\"/>\n|Herself\n|Rai Uno\n|[[Variety show]] \u2013 3 episodes, main presenter and performer, shared with [[Paola Cortellesi]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|2018\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Lo Nuestro Awards]]<ref name=\"Lo Nuestro 2018\"/>\n|Herself\n|Univision\n|Music gala \u2013 co-host and performer\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Factor X (Spanish TV series)|Factor X]]''<ref name=\"Factor X\"/>\n|Herself\n|Telecinco\n|Talent show \u2013 series 3 judge\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Laura Pausini}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n|- style=\"background:#ddd;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[Grammy Awards]]'''\n{{s-bef|before= [[Marc Anthony]]<br />for ''[[Amar Sin Mentiras|Amar sin mentiras]]''}}\n{{s-ttl|title = [[Grammy Award for Best Latin Pop Album]]|years = 2006<br />'''for ''[[Resta in ascolto|Escucha]]'' '''}}\n{{s-aft|after = [[Ricardo Arjona]] for ''[[Adentro]]''<br/>joint with<br/>[[Julieta Venegas]] for ''[[Lim\u00f3n y sal]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#ddd;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[Latin Grammy Awards]]'''\n{{succession box\n| title  = [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album, Female]]\n| years  = 2005<br/>'''for ''[[Resta in ascolto|Escucha]]'' '''\n| before = [[Rosario Flores]]<br/>for ''[[De mil colores (Rosario Flores album)|De mil colores]]''\n| after  = [[Shakira]]<br/>for ''[[Fijaci\u00f3n Oral Vol. 1]]''\n}}\n{{succession box\n| title  = Latin Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album, Female\n| years  = 2007<br/>'''for ''[[Io canto|Yo canto]]'' '''\n| before = Shakira<br/>for ''Fijaci\u00f3n Oral Vol. 1''\n| after  = [[Kany Garc\u00eda]]<br/>for ''[[Cualquier D\u00eda]]''\n}}\n{{succession box\n| title  = Latin Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album, Female\n| years  = 2009<br/>'''for ''[[Primavera in anticipo|Primavera anticipada]]'' '''\n| before = Kany Garc\u00eda<br/>for ''Cualquier D\u00eda''\n| after  = [[Nelly Furtado]]<br/>for ''[[Mi Plan]]''\n}}\n{{succession box\n| title  = [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Traditional Pop Vocal Album]]\n| years  = 2018<br/>'''for ''[[Fatti sentire|Hazte sentir]]'' '''\n| before = [[Lila Downs]]<br/>for ''Sal\u00f3n, L\u00e1grimas y Deseo''\n| after  = [[Fonseca (singer)|Fonseca]]<br/>for ''Agust\u00edn''\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{refbegin}}\n<ol class=\"references\" style=\"list-style-type:upper-alpha;\">\n<li id=\"notea\">'''[[#inlinea|^]]''' Sources indicate different locations for Pausini's birth\u2014The Comunes of [[Faenza]] and [[Solarolo]], [[Province of Ravenna|Ravenna]], Italy. One state source, The Presidency of the Italian Republic, cites Faenza as the location of her birth.<ref>{{in lang|it}} Italy. Presidency of the Republic. \"[http://www.quirinale.it/elementi/DettaglioOnorificenze.aspx?decorato=173657 Le onorificenze] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605221939/http://www.quirinale.it/elementi/DettaglioOnorificenze.aspx?decorato=173657 |date= 5 June 2011 }}\", ''Presidenza della Repubblica'', February 2006.</ref> In media interviews, however, Pausini consistently names Solarolo as her birthplace. Solarolo is located 5 miles from Faenza.<ref>Bottomley, Charles. \"[http://www.vh1.com/artists/interview/1458838/20021122/pausini_laura.jhtml Laura Pausini: All about diva]\", ''VH1.com'', 22 November 2002.</ref><ref>{{in lang|es}} EFE. \"[http://www.emol.com/noticias/todas/detalle/detallenoticias.asp?idnoticia=31263 Laura Pausini: 'Hay d\u00edas en que quiero matar a mi productor']\", ''El Mercurio'' [Santiago de Chile], 31 August 2000.</ref><ref>{{in lang|es}} Pausini, Laura. Interview. ''Nadie se duerma'', Host Beto Ortiz, Frecuencia Latina [Peru], 2 November 2001.</ref><ref>{{in lang|es}} Pausini, Laura. Interview. ''Las hijas'', Hosts Monserrat Olivier and Yolanda Andrade, Unicable [Mexico], 27 January 2007.</ref></li>\n</ol>\n{{refend}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category|Laura Pausini}}\n*{{Official website|http://www.laurapausini.com/}}\n*{{IMDb name|1306128|Laura Pausini}}\n*[http://www.allmusic.com/artist/laura-pausini-mn0000138235 Laura Pausini] at [[Allmusic]]\n*[http://www.artistdirect.com/artist/laura-pausini/513702 Laura Pausini] at [[Artistdirect]]\n*[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=laura pausini|bio=true}} Laura Pausini] at ''[[Billboard magazine|Billboard]]''\n*[http://www.discogs.com/artist/80894-Laura-Pausini Laura Pausini] at [[Discogs]]\n*[http://musicbrainz.org/artist/472b9953-1f10-4aed-b1ec-d0c23ffb2cf1 Laura Pausini] at [[Musicbrainz]]\n\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Italy|Latin music|Pop music}}\n{{Laura Pausini}}\n{{Laura Pausini singles}}\n{{La Voz (Spanish TV series)}}\n{{Best-selling albums by year in Italy}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pausini, Laura}}\n[[Category:Laura Pausini| ]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Italian pop singers]]\n[[Category:Italian female singers]]\n[[Category:Italian record producers]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language singers of Italy]]\n[[Category:English-language singers from Italy]]\n[[Category:French-language singers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Portuguese-language singers of Italy]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Ravenna]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records artists]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Latin Grammy Award winners]]\n[[Category:World Music Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Latin pop singers]]\n[[Category:Italian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:LGBT rights activists from Italy]]\n[[Category:Sanremo Music Festival winners of the newcomers section]]\n[[Category:Warner Music Latina artists]]\n[[Category:Italian women record producers]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the singer\u2013songwriter|her self-titled albums|Laura Pausini (1993 album){{!}}her 1993 album|and|Laura Pausini (1994 album){{!}}her 1994 album|and|Laura Pausini (1995 album){{!}}her 1995 album}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name = Laura Pausini\n| honorific_suffix = [[Order of Merit of the Italian Republic|OMRI]]\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image = Laura Pausini 19 - Bercy - Avril 2012 (6930185910).jpg\n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = Pausini in 2012\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1974|5|16}}\n| baptism_date = \n| birth_place = [[Faenza]], [[Province of Ravenna|Ravenna]], Italy\n| disappeared_date = <!-- {{Disappeared date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (disappeared date then birth date) -->\n| disappeared_place = \n| disappeared_status = \n| death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date