|[[Lara Fabian]]|[[Johnny Hallyday]]|[[Sandy (singer)|Sandy]]}}\n}}\n| module2 = \n| module3 = \n| module4 = \n| module5 = \n| module6 = \n| website = {{URL|laurapausini.com}}\n| footnotes = \n| box_width = \n}}\n'''Laura Pausini''' {{postnominals|post-noms=[[Order of Merit of the Italian Republic|OMRI]]}} ({{IPA-it|\u02c8laura pau\u02c8zi\u02d0ni|lang}}; born 16 May 1974) is an Italian singer-songwriter, record producer and television personality. As a child, she was encouraged by her father to join him during his performances in local [[piano bar]]s. After competing in local singing contests, Pausini signed her first recording contract. She rose to fame in 1993, winning the newcomer artists' section of the 43rd [[Sanremo Music Festival]] with her debut single \"[[La solitudine]]\",<ref name=\"Sanremo1993\">{{cite web|url= http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1993/marzo/01/aria_nuova_Sanremo_per_ora_co_0_93030110053.shtml|accessdate=8 September 2013|title=Aria nuova a Sanremo? Per ora solo spifferi|author = Mario Luzzatto Fegiz, Gloria Pozzi|date = 1 March 1993|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|language=Italian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130723011723/http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1993/marzo/01/aria_nuova_Sanremo_per_ora_co_0_93030110053.shtml|archivedate=23 July 2013}}</ref> which became an Italian standard<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.it/musica/artisti/archivio/artista.asp?idArt=5906#biografia |publisher=[[MTV Italy]] |language=Italian |accessdate=22 July 2011 |title=Laura Pausini: La biografia |archivedate= 20 September 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120920025157/http://www.mtv.it/musica/artisti/archivio/artista.asp?idart=5906 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> and an international hit, topping the [[Musica e dischi|charts in Italy]], [[Dutch Top 40|the Netherlands]], and [[Ultratop 50|Belgium]].<ref name=\"LaSolitudineNumberOne\">{{cite web | url = http://it-charts.150m.com/numeriuno-1990.htm | publisher =it-charts.150m.com | title = Singoli \u2013 I numeri uno (1959\u20132006) \u2013 Parte 4: 1990\u20131996 | accessdate = 1 September 2012 | language = Italian | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110707055417/http://it-charts.150m.com/numeriuno-1990.htm | archivedate = 7 July 2011}}</ref><ref name=DutchTop40LaSolitudine>{{cite web|url=http://www.top40.nl/index.aspx?week=2&jaar=1994 |publisher=[[Dutch Top 40]] |accessdate=1 September 2012 |title=Top40 week 2 van 1994 (08-01-1994) |language=Dutch |archivedate= 1 September 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120901165352/http://www.top40.nl/top40/1994/week-2 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref><ref name=VRTTop30>{{cite web | url = http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Laura+Pausini&titel=La+solitudine&cat=s | publisher = [[Ultratop]]. Hung Medien | language = Dutch | accessdate = 7 September 2013| title = Charts Vlaanderen \u2013 Laura Pausini \u2013 La solitudine}}</ref> Her [[Laura Pausini (1993 album)|self titled debut album]] was released in Italy on 23 April 1993<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wuz.it/disco/0745099238520/pausini-laura/laura-pausini.html |publisher=Wuz.it |language=Italian |accessdate=6 August 2012 |title=Scheda Disco \u2013 Laura Pausini \u2013 Laura Pausini |archivedate= 18 February 2013 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130218120532/http://www.wuz.it/disco/0745099238520/pausini-laura/laura-pausini.html |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> and later became an international success, selling two million copies worldwide.<ref name=\"SalesFirstAlbum\">{{cite web|url=http://www.italica.rai.it/eng/principal/topics/bio/pausini.htm |publisher=[[RAI]] |accessdate=1 September 2012 |title=Biography of Laura Pausini |archivedate= 15 March 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120315153244/http://www.italica.rai.it/eng/principal/topics/bio/pausini.htm |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\nIts follow-up, ''[[Laura (Laura Pausini album)|Laura]]'', was released in 1994 and confirmed her international success, selling three million copies worldwide.<ref name=\"LauraSales\">{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2000/settembre/15/Laura_Pausini_alla_moda_del_co_0_0009159171.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | accessdate =8 September 2013 | language = Italian | date = 15 September 2000 | author = Mario Luzzatto Fegiz | title = Laura Pausini: no alla moda del pop latino|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130722232616/http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2000/settembre/15/Laura_Pausini_alla_moda_del_co_0_0009159171.shtml|archivedate=22 July 2013}}</ref> During the same year, she released her first Spanish-language album, ''[[Laura Pausini (1994 album)|Laura Pausini]]'', composed of ten adapted songs originally included in her previous works. The album was certified diamond by the [[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|Association of Phonographic and Videographic of Spain]],<ref name=Diamond1994Album>{{cite web|title=Laura Pausini actuar\u00e1 en Madrid y Barcelona para presentar su und\u00e9cimo disco, luego ir\u00e1 a la capital de colombia (Soledad) a comer butifarra baranoera |url=http://www.republica.com/2011/05/17/laura-pausini-actuara-en-madrid-y-barcelona-para-presentar-su-undecimo-disco_336295/ |language=Spanish |accessdate=1 September 2012 |date=17 May 2011 |publisher=Rep\u00fablica.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120806201205/http://www.republica.com/2011/05/17/laura-pausini-actuara-en-madrid-y-barcelona-para-presentar-su-undecimo-disco_336295/ |archivedate= 6 August 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> making her the first non-Spanish artist to sell more than one million copies in Spain.<ref name=\"RepubblicaArticle\">{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2002/02/14/intrigante-soul-della-regina-del-pop.html | archive-url = https://archive.today/20120518050924/http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2002/02/14/intrigante-soul-della-regina-del-pop.html | url-status = dead | archive-date = 18 May 2012 | work = [[la Repubblica]] | accessdate =29 July 2011 | title = L'intrigante soul della regina del pop | date = 14 February 2002 | author = Ernesto Assante }}</ref>\n\nAs of 2017, Pausini has released twelve studio albums, two international [[greatest hits album]]s and two compilation albums for the Hispanic and Anglophone market only, respectively. She mostly performs in Italian and Spanish, but she has also recorded songs in English, French, Portuguese and more recently, Catalan.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.elperiodico.com/es/noticias/tele/laura-pausini-canta-lamarato-tv3-solidaridad-3641722 | work = [[El Peri\u00f3dico de Catalunya]] | accessdate = 20 December 2014 | title = Laura Pausini canta por 'La Marat\u00f3' de TV-3 | date = 28 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=MQ8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA48#v=onepage&q&f=false | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate = 1 September 2012 | title = Laura Pausini Tenth Anniversary \u2013 Italy's Multilingual Star Serenades The World | page = 48 | date = 15 March 2003 | author = Mark Worden}}</ref> Her sole English-language album of original songs, ''[[From the Inside (Laura Pausini album)|From the Inside]]'', was released in 2002, but failed to satisfy commercial expectations both in North America and in the rest of the world. In 2006, her record ''[[Io canto]]'' was the best-selling album of the year in Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fimi.it/dett_comunicatistampa.php?id=15|publisher=[[Federation of the Italian Music Industry]]|date=10 January 2008|title=Classifiche Annuali 2007 FIMI-AC Nielsen: al primo posto Eros Ramazzotti con E2|accessdate=19 January 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120506002747/http://www.fimi.it/dett_comunicatistampa.php?id=15|archivedate=6 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, [[Allmusic]]'s Jason Birchmeier considered Pausini's sales \"an impressive feat for someone who'd never really broken into the lucrative English\u2013language market\".<ref name=allmusic /> [[FIMI]] certified Pausini's sales of more than 70 million records with a FIMI Icon Award.<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204205948/http://www.webl0g.net/2014/07/07/icon-award-per-laura-pausini-e-il-world-tour-in-ottobre-sbarca-negli-stati-uniti/ |url=http://www.webl0g.net/2014/07/07/icon-award-per-laura-pausini-e-il-world-tour-in-ottobre-sbarca-negli-stati-uniti/ |publisher=Fimi & Italian Trade |accessdate=27 November 2014 |archivedate= 4 December 2014 |title=Laura Pausini: Icon Award by Fimi & Italian Trade for her sales of more than 75 million records worldwide |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nPausini appeared as a coach on both [[La Voz... M\u00e9xico|the Mexican]] and [[La Voz (Spanish TV series)|Spanish versions]] of international reality television singing competition franchise ''[[The Voice (TV series)|The Voice]]'', was a judge on the first and second series of ''[[La Banda (TV series)|La banda]]'', and is likewise a judge on [[Factor X (Spanish TV series)|the Spanish version]] of international franchise ''[[The X Factor]]''. In 2016, she also debuted as a variety show presenter, hosting the television show ''Laura & Paola'', with actress [[Paola Cortellesi]].\n\nThroughout her career, she has won numerous music awards in Italy and internationally.\nShe has earned the first and third place at the [[Sanremo Music Festival]], two \"Lunezia Awards\", ten [[Wind Music Awards]], four awards at the [[Festivalbar]], seven [[Telegatti]], and an [[MTV Italian Music Awards|MTV Italian Music Award]]. Internationally, she has won four awards at the [[Vi\u00f1a del Mar International Song Festival]], three [[Lo Nuestro Awards]], four [[Latin Grammy Awards]], a [[Billboard Latin Music Award]], and six [[World Music Award]]s. In 2006, she also became the first Italian female artist to win a [[Grammy Award]],<ref name=\"RepubblicaGrammy\">{{cite web | url = http://www.repubblica.it/2006/b/sezioni/spettacoli_e_cultura/pausinigrammy/pausinigrammy/pausinigrammy.html?ref=search | work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | accessdate =8 September 2013| title = Laura Pausini vince il Grammy. Premiata per il pop latino | date = 9 February 2006|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022123627/http://www.repubblica.it/2006/b/sezioni/spettacoli_e_cultura/pausinigrammy/pausinigrammy/pausinigrammy.html?ref=search|archivedate=22 October 2012}}</ref> receiving the accolade for [[Grammy Award for Best Latin Pop Album|Best Latin Pop Album]] for the record ''[[Resta in ascolto|Escucha]]''.<ref name=\"GrammyAward\">{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees/search?artist=laura+pausini&title=escucha&year=All&genre=All |publisher=Grammy.com |accessdate=8 September 2013 |title=Past Winners Search \u2013 Laura Pausini \u2013 Escucha |archivedate=25 September 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120925205633/http://www.grammy.com/nominees/search?artist=laura%2Bpausini&title=escucha&year=All&genre=All |url-status=dead }}</ref> She has been honoured as a [[Order of Merit of the Italian Republic|Commander Order of Merit of the Italian Republic]] by President [[Carlo Azeglio Ciampi]] and as a [[Ambassador|World Ambassador]] of [[Emilia Romagna]].\n\n==Biography==\n===Childhood and early beginnings===\nThe elder of two daughters,<ref name=Family/> Laura Pausini was born in [[Faenza]], in the [[Province of Ravenna]], Italy,<ref name=Commander>{{cite web | url = http://www.quirinale.it/elementi/DettaglioOnorificenze.aspx?decorato=173657 | publisher = Quirinale.it | language = Italian | title = Pausini Sig.ra Laura \u2013 Commendatore Ordine al Merito della Repubblica Italiana | accessdate = 1 September 2012 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110605221939/http://www.quirinale.it/elementi/DettaglioOnorificenze.aspx?decorato=173657 | archivedate = 5 June 2011}}</ref> to Fabrizio Pausini<ref name=Family>{{Cite journal | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=MQ8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA43#v=onepage&q&f=false | journal = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | date = 15 March 2003 | accessdate = 1 September 2012 | title = Italy's multilingual star serenades the world | author = Mark Worden}}</ref> and Gianna Ballardini. She grew up in [[Solarolo]], a small ''[[comune]]'' in the same region.<ref name=\"FirstAlbum\">{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1993/maggio/25/Laura_Pausini_Sanremo_primo_disco_co_0_93052512464.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | language = Italian | accessdate =29 July 2011 | date = 25 May 1993 | title = Laura Pausini da Sanremo al primo disco}}</ref><sup id=\"inlinea\" class=\"reference\">[[#notea|[A]]]</sup>\nHer father is a former pianist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.lesoir.be/pausini-d-oiseau-le-rossignol-de-ravenna-veut-tout-et-t_t-19961002-Z0CPDF.html |work=[[Le Soir]] |language=French |accessdate=8 September 2013 |archivedate= 7 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130907220601/http://archives.lesoir.be/pausini-d-oiseau-le-rossignol-de-ravenna-veut-tout-et-t_t-19961002-Z0CPDF.html |title=Pausini d'oiseau, le rossignol de Ravenna veut tout et tou |date=2 October 1996 |page=47 |author=Thierry Coljon |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> who also played as a [[sessionman]] for [[ABBA]]'s [[Frida Lyngstad]] and entered a band whose members later founded the Italian pop group [[Pooh (band)|Pooh]].<ref name=Family/> After becoming a [[piano bar]] artist, he encouraged Pausini to start performing as a singer.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.corriere.it/Primo_Piano/Spettacoli/2006/02_Febbraio/08/grammy.html | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 1 September 2012 | title = Grammy, trionfa Laura Pausini | date = 9 February 2006 | archivedate = 4 April 2006 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060404132741/http://www.corriere.it/Primo_Piano/Spettacoli/2006/02_Febbraio/08/grammy.html}}</ref>\nHer first live performance was on 16 May 1985, when she sang together with her father in a restaurant in [[Bologna]].<ref name=\"GianniMin\u00e0\">{{cite web | url = http://www.giannimina.it/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=177&Itemid=53 | publisher = Giannimina.it | author = Gianni Min\u00e0 | accessdate = 1 September 2012 | title = Laura Pausini: una ragazza di provincia con un respiro mondiale | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110716010503/http://www.giannimina.it/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=177&Itemid=53 | archivedate = 16 July 2011}}</ref>\nSince then, her father started giving her singing lessons<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1994/maggio/26/imparato_papa_cantando_piano_bar_co_10_9405261778.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | language = Italian | date = 26 May 1994 | author = Sandra Cesarale | title = Ho imparato da pap\u00e0 cantando al piano bar}}</ref> and she continued to perform alongside him in local piano bars. In the meanwhile, she also started singing in a [[church choir]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1084008 | work = [[La Stampa]] | accessdate = 29 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini. Maturit\u00e0 e poi tourne\u00e9. \"Son studiosa e devota\" | date = 23 April 1993 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20111005080709/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1084008 | archivedate = 5 October 2011 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nIn 1987 she recorded her first [[Demo (music)|demo album]], produced by her father and released to promote her live shows.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2009/11/25/laura-live-pausini-la-voce-del-pop.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 1 September 2012 | title = Laura live Pausini, la voce del pop successi intorno al mondo | author = Gino Castaldo | date = 25 November 2009 | page = 15}}</ref> Titled ''I sogni di Laura'', it consisted of eight covers and five new songs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockit.it/album/15647/laura-pausini-i-sogni-di-laura |publisher=Rockit.it |language=Italian |accessdate=8 September 2013 |title=Laura Pausini \u2013 I sogni di Laura |date=11 April 2011 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130907220752/http://www.rockit.it/laurapausini/album/i-sogni-di-laura/15647 |archivedate= 7 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> In 1991 she participated in the [[Castrocaro Music Festival]] singing [[Liza Minnelli]]'s \"[[Theme from New York, New York|New York, New York]]\", but she failed to reach the final stage of the competition.<ref name=\"GianniMin\u00e0\"/> During the same year, she took part in another singing competition, Sanremo Famosi, which should have served as a selection for the newcomers' of the following [[Sanremo Music Festival]].<ref name=RepubblicaSanremo1993>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1993/02/28/sanremo-vince-ruggeri.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 1 September 2012 | date = 28 February 1993 | title= Sanremo: vince Ruggeri | author = Maria Pia Fusco|page=25}}</ref> Despite being declared joint winner with another contestant,<ref name=\"GianniMin\u00e0\"/><ref name=RepubblicaSanremo1993/> Pausini was not allowed to compete in the [[Sanremo Music Festival]] 1992.<ref name=\"GianniMin\u00e0\"/>\n\n===1993: Career breakthrough===\nThanks to her performances in local singing competitions, Pausini was noticed by Italian producer and songwriter Angelo Valsiglio, who introduced her to manager Marco Marati.<ref name=\"GianniMin\u00e0\"/> Valsiglio suggested to her \"[[La solitudine]]\", a song he wrote with Pietro Cremonesi and Federico Cavalli. Pausini's rendition convinced Valsiglio and Marati, who wanted Pausini to audition for some major labels.<ref name=\"GianniMin\u00e0\"/> During one of the auditions, she met Fabrizio Giannini of [[Warner Music Italy]]'s [[Compagnia Generale del Disco]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=MQ8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA46#v=onepage&q&f=false | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate = 2 September 2012 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 The Billboard Interview | author = Mark Worden | date = 15 March 2003 | page = 46}}</ref> After impressing him with a performance of an unreleased [[Mia Martini]] song, Pausini obtained her first recording contract, becoming one of the first artists discovered by Giannini, who later launched the careers of several Italian acts, including [[Irene Grandi]].<ref name=\"GianniMin\u00e0\"/>\n\n[[File:Sanremo0006.jpg|thumb|Pausini rose to fame in 1993, after winning the 43rd [[Sanremo Music Festival]], annually held at the [[Teatro Ariston]] in [[Sanremo]], Italy]]\n\"La solitudine\" was selected as one of the entries in the newcomer artists' section of the 43rd [[Sanremo Music Festival]]. Pausini performed it for the first time on 23 February 1993, during the first semifinal of the contest.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1993/02/23/il-programma-delle-tre-serate.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 23 September 2011 | date = 23 February 1993 | title = Il programma delle tre serate}}</ref> After being admitted to the final, held on 27 February 1993, she won the competition, receiving 7,464 votes from the juries and beating [[Gerardina Trovato]] with \"Ma non ho pi\u00f9 la mia citt\u00e0\", who took second place with 7,209 votes.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.hitparadeitalia.it/sanremo/edizioni/1993.htm | publisher = Hitparadeitalia.it | title = Sanremo 1993 (43a Edizione) \u2013 Canzoni in gara e Classifica finale | accessdate = 8 September 2013 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100607084650/http://www.hitparadeitalia.it/sanremo/edizioni/1993.htm|archivedate=7 June 2010 | language = Italian}}</ref>\nThe song also became a commercial success in Italy, peaking at number one on the Italian ''[[Musica e dischi]]'' singles chart in March 1993 and maintaining the top spot for three consecutive weeks,<ref name=\"LaSolitudineNumberOne\"/> and it is still one of Pausini's best-known hits.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2005/06/30/la-regina-della-canzone-amore.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | date = 30 June 2005 | accessdate =29 July 2011 | title = La regina della canzone d' amore | author = Giusy La Piana}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the success obtained with her debut single, Pausini started working on her first professional album, ''[[Laura Pausini (1993 album)|Laura Pausini]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://warnermusic.it/artista/laura-pausini/?s=read-all |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320053811/http://warnermusic.it/artista/laura-pausini/?s=read-all|archivedate=20 March 2012| publisher = [[Warner Music Group]] | language = Italian | accessdate =8 September 2013 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 Biografia}}</ref>\nThe album was recorded while Pausini was still a high school student<ref name=\"Repubblica15092000\"/> at the \"Gaetano Ballardini\" Institute of Ceramics in [[Faenza]], Italy,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.istitutoarteceramicafaenza.com/arch/docs/50/Il%20Resto%20del%20Carlino%20-%20Maturi.pdf |format=PDF |publisher=[[Il Resto del Carlino]] / Istituto Arte Ceramica Faenza |language=Italian |accessdate=2 September 2012 |title=Istituto d'Arte per la Ceramica Ballardini |archivedate= 25 October 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101025220901/http://www.istitutoarteceramicafaenza.com/arch/docs/50/Il%20Resto%20del%20Carlino%20-%20Maturi.pdf |year=2010 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> where she got her [[High school diploma|diploma]] a few months after the release of her debut studio set.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1993/ottobre/06/Pausini_macche_solitudine_fans_assaltano_co_0_9310062804.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | language = Italian | date = 6 October 1993 | title = La Pausini: macch\u00e8 solitudine, i fans mi assaltano | page = 33 | author = Gloria Pozzi}}</ref>\nReleased by [[CGD Records]] in May 1993,<ref name=\"FirstAlbum\"/> it reached the sixth position on the Italian ''Musica e dischi'' albums chart,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.hitparadeitalia.it/hp_yenda/lpe1993.htm | publisher = Hitparadeitalia.it | accessdate = 23 July 2011 | title = Gli album pi\u00f9 venduti del 1993}}</ref> selling 400,000 copies in Italy.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.elmundo.es/larevista/num157/textos/amore1.html | work = [[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]] | language = Spanish | accessdate =24 July 2011 | title = La Revista: Desde Italia con Amore \u2013 Laura Pausini, La voz bonita | archivedate = 2 January 2008 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080102113555/http://www.elmundo.es/larevista/num157/textos/amore1.html}}</ref>\nThe album was also promoted through an Italian outdoor tour during the summer of 1993.<ref name=laRepubblica14Dec1995/> In September 1993, Pausini received a [[Telegatto]] for Revelation of the Year.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1993/settembre/21/Canale_sfilano_nuovi_Telegatti_musicali_co_0_93092114005.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | language = Italian  | title = Su Canale 5 sfilano i nuovi Telegatti musicali: Vasco, Eros, la Nannini | accessdate = 1 August 2011| date = 21 September 1993}}</ref>\n\nIn late 1993, the album was released in the rest of Europe, peaking at number three on the [[Dutch Albums Chart]]<ref name=\"DutchAlbumsChart\">{{cite web  | url = http://www.dutchcharts.nl/search.asp?cat=a&artist=Laura+Pausini&artist_search=starts&title=&title_search=starts | title = Dutch Albums Chart \u2013 Laura Pausini | language = Dutch | accessdate =28 July 2011 | publisher = dutchcharts.nl }}</ref> and reaching the top spot in Belgium.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=NQgEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA57#v=onepage&q&f=false | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate = 2 September 2012 | page = 57 | title = Hits of the World Continues \u2013 Belgium | date = 26 March 1994}}</ref> It also achieved commercial success in South America, being certified gold in Brazil<ref name=BrazilianCertifications>{{cite web|url=http://www.abpd.org.br/certificados_interna.asp?sArtista=Laura+Pausini |publisher=[[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira dos Produtores de Discos]] |accessdate=2 September 2012 |archivedate=15 August 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120815184801/http://abpd.org.br/certificados_interna.asp?sArtista=Laura+Pausini |language=Portuguese |title=Certificados \u2013 Laura Pausini |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> and Argentina.<ref name=\"Argentina Certification\">{{cite web | url = http://www.capif.org.ar/Default.asp?PerDesde_MM=0&PerDesde_AA=0&PerHasta_MM=0&PerHasta_AA=0&interprete=&album=&LanDesde_MM=1&LanDesde_AA=1980&LanHasta_MM=12&LanHasta_AA=2010&Galardon=O&Tipo=1&ACCION2=+Buscar+&ACCION=Buscar&CO=5&CODOP=ESOP | publisher = [[Argentine Chamber of Phonograms and Videograms Producers]] | language = Spanish | accessdate = 15 August 2012 | archivedate = 6 July 2011 | archiveurl = https://archive.today/20110706084844/http://www.capif.org.ar/Default.asp?PerDesde_MM=0&PerDesde_AA=0&PerHasta_MM=0&PerHasta_AA=0&interprete=&album=&LanDesde_MM=1&LanDesde_AA=1980&LanHasta_MM=12&LanHasta_AA=2010&Galardon=O&Tipo=1&ACCION2=+Buscar+&ACCION=Buscar&CO=5&CODOP=ESOP | title = Discos de Oro y Platino}}</ref>\nWorldwide sales of Pausini's debut studio album exceed two million units.<ref name=\"SalesFirstAlbum\"/>\nMoreover, \"La solitudine\" became a radio hit in Belgium and the Netherlands,<ref name=BillboardTenthAnniversary>{{Cite journal | journal = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | author = Mark Worden | title = Laura Pausini tenth anniversary | pages = 46\u201347 | date = 15 March 2003 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=MQ8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA48#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref> it peaked at number five on the [[French Singles Chart]] and it reached the top spot of the [[Dutch Top 40]]<ref name=DutchTop40LaSolitudine/> and of the Flemish [[Ultratop 50]].<ref name=VRTTop30/>\nThe album also spawned the singles \"[[Non c'\u00e8]]\" and \"[[Perch\u00e9 non torna pi\u00f9]]\".\n\n===1994\u20131995: Spanish-language debut and international success===\nIn February 1994, Pausini participated for the second time in the Sanremo Music Festival, competing in the \"Big Artists\" section with her entry \"[[Strani amori]]\".\nThe song ranked third in the competition, behind [[Aleandro Baldi]]'s \"Passer\u00e0\" and [[Giorgio Faletti]]'s \"Signor tenente\",<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1994/02/27/vincono-baldi-bocelli.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Vincono Baldi e Bocelli  | language = Italian | date = 27 February 1994 | author = Maria Pia Fusco | page = 28}}</ref> and became a hit in Italy,<ref>{{cite web | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=NQgEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA56#v=onepage&q&f=false | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | page = 56 | date = 26 March 1994 | publisher = [[Nielsen Business Media, Inc]] | accessdate = 9 August 2012|title = Hits of the World \u2013 Italy}}</ref> in the Netherlands<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.top40.nl/top40/1994/week-19 |publisher=[[Dutch Top 40]] |language=Dutch |accessdate=9 August 2012 |title=Top40 week 19 van 1994 (07-05-1994) |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130611075632/http://www.top40.nl/top40/1994/week-19 |archivedate= 11 June 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> and in Flanders.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Laura+Pausini&titel=Strani+amori&cat=s | publisher = [[Ultratop]] | language = Dutch | accessdate = 8 September 2013 | title = Charts Vlaanderen Laura Pausini \u2013 Strani amori}}</ref> The single launched Pausini's second studio album, ''[[Laura (Laura Pausini album)|Laura]]'', released in February 1994. According to CGD Records, the album sold 150,000 copies in Italy in its first week, with initial shipments of 200,000 units.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1219412 | work = [[La Stampa]] | title = Le vendite per una volta danno ragione alla classifica. Festival, i conti tornano. Premiati dal pubblico Pausini, Baldi, Trovato e i primi tra i Giovani | date = 8 March 1994 | page = 21 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20111005080727/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1219412 | archivedate = 5 October 2011 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> It also peaked at number one on the Dutch Albums Chart and entered the charts in Belgium and Switzerland,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Laura+Pausini&titel=Laura&cat=a | publisher = dutchcharts.nl | language = Dutch | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 Laura (album)}}</ref> selling three million copies worldwide<ref name=\"LauraSales\"/> and achieving gold and platinum status in Brazil and Argentina, respectively.<ref name=BrazilianCertifications/><ref name=\"Argentina Certification\"/> Other singles from the album were \"[[Gente (song)|Gente]]\", \"Lui non sta con te\" and \"[[Lettera]]\". During the summer of 1994, Pausini took part in the Italian itinerant TV show [[Festivalbar]], reaching the final stage of the music competition<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1994/agosto/06/Festivalbar_quattro_finalisti_co_0_9408068004.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | language = Italian | title = Festivalbar: quattro finalisti | date = 6 August 1994 | accessdate = 2 September 2012 | page = 22}}</ref> and receiving the Premio Europa for her international success.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1994/settembre/04/Festivalbar_dopo_anni_Tozzi_trionfa_co_0_94090411455.shtml | title = Festivalbar, dopo 17 anni Tozzi trionfa di nuovo | date = 4 September 1994 | accessdate = 2 September 2012 | language = Italian | page = 27}}</ref> In 1994 she was also awarded with her second [[Telegatto]], receiving the prize for Best Female Artist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1301159 |work=[[La Stampa]] |language=Italian |accessdate=1 August 2011 |title=Su Canale 5 I Telegatti di Red e di Alba |date=14 September 1994 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314004234/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1301159 |archivedate=14 March 2012 }}</ref> In the meanwhile, she started an Italian tour to promote her album.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1994/05/27/dolce-laura-aiuto-il-successo-costa.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | title = Dolce Laura: Aiuto, il successo costa caro | date = 27 May 1994 | accessdate = 2 September 2012}}</ref>\n\nDuring the same year, Pausini released her first Spanish-language album, ''[[Laura Pausini (1994 album)|Laura Pausini]]'', a compilation of ten adapted versions of hits from her previous albums, issued by [[Dro Records]].<ref name=BillboardTenthAnniversary/> The record became the best-selling album of 1994 in Spain,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.elpais.com/especiales/2001/25aniversario/especial/05/musica/p1.html | title = El chaval de barrio que rompi\u00f3 | author = Ana Alfageme | language = Spanish | accessdate =30 July 2011 | work = [[El Pa\u00eds]] | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070528185122/http://www.elpais.com/especiales/2001/25aniversario/especial/05/musica/p1.html | archivedate = 28 May 2007}}</ref><ref name=Anuario1999>{{cite web|url=http://www.anuariossgae.com/1999/pdfs/grabada/grabada%20anexos.pdf |publisher=[[Sociedad General de Autores y Editores]] |language=Spanish |format=PDF |title=Anuario SGAE 1999 \u2013 Anexo 6 \u2013 Los 50 titulos con mayores ventas en las listas de ventas de AFYVE en 1996 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120818120257/http://www.anuariossgae.com/1999/pdfs/grabada/grabada%20anexos.pdf |archivedate=18 August 2012 }}</ref> where it was later certified diamond by the [[PROMUSICAE|Association of Phonographic and Videographic of Spain]] for sales exceeding one million units.<ref name=Diamond1994Album/> Pausini was the first non-Spanish artist to achieve this result.<ref name=\"RepubblicaArticle\"/> Following the commercial success obtained in the country, the Spanish Institute of Italian Culture awarded her a \"Globo de Platino\" for contributing in the spread of Italian culture in Spain.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elcivico.com/notas/2012/5/16/laura-pausini-cumple-celebramos-grandes-exitos-86478.asp |work=El Civico |accessdate=2 September 2012 |date=16 May 2012 |title=Laura Pausini cumple 38 a\u00f1os y lo celebramos con sus grandes \u00e9xitos |language=Spanish |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103020000/http://www.elcivico.com/notas/2012/5/16/laura-pausini-cumple-celebramos-grandes-exitos-86478.asp |archivedate= 3 January 2015 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\nThe album was successful in Latin America too, being certified platinum by the [[Argentine Chamber of Phonograms and Videograms Producers]],<ref name=\"Argentina Certification\"/> the [[Asociaci\u00f3n Colombiana de Productores de Fonogramas]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.eltiempo.com/archivo/documento/MAM-849605 | work = [[El Tiempo (Colombia)|El Tiempo]] | language = Spanish |accessdate =8 September 2013 | title = Laura Pausini y su brillante carrera | date = 21 November 1998|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121005002731/http://www.eltiempo.com/archivo/documento/MAM-849605|archivedate=5 October 2012}}</ref> and the Chilean division of the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=ZQgEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA70#v=onepage&q&f=false | author = John Lannert | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | title = ABCs of Latin America \u2013 Record Biz Tries To Warm A Chilly Market | date = 10 December 1994 | accessdate = 18 March 2012}}</ref>\nMoreover, the first four singles from the album, \"La soledad\", \"Se fue\", \"Amores extra\u00f1os\" and \"Gente\", entered the top 30 on the [[Hot Latin Songs]] chart compiled by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url = {{BillboardURLbyName|artist=laura pausini|chart=Latin Songs C}} | title = Laura Pausini Song & Chart History \u2013 Latin Songs | work =[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate =28 July 2011}}</ref> Thanks to these results, ''Billboard'' ranked Pausini the second female revelation of 1994, after [[Mariah Carey]].<ref name=\"RAI Bio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.italica.rai.it/eng/principal/topics/bio/pausini.htm |publisher=[[RAI|Radiotelevisione Italiana]] |accessdate=30 July 2011 |title=Biography of Laura Pausini |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120315153244/http://www.italica.rai.it/eng/principal/topics/bio/pausini.htm |archivedate= 15 March 2012 }}</ref><ref name=SunSentinel1997>{{cite web | work = [[South Florida Sun-Sentinel|Sun-Sentinel]] | accessdate=30 July 2011 | title = Italian Singer A Spanish Hit | author = David Cazares | date = 25 June 1997 | url = http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/1997-06-25/lifestyle/9706240220_1_laura-pausini-wea-latina-record-label}}</ref> In 1995 Pausini also received the [[World Music Award]] for Best Selling Italian Recording Artist<ref>{{cite web|title=Pausini, best seller all'estero |url=http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1396684 |date=18 April 1995 |language=Italian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005080802/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1396684 |archivedate=5 October 2011 }}</ref> and the [[Lo Nuestro Awards|Lo Nuestro Award]] for Best New Artist of the Year.<ref name=\"RAI Bio\"/><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo474610.shtml | work = [[TGCOM]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Il Premio Lo Nuestro alla Pausini | date = 22 February 2010 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100330014822/http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo474610.shtml | archive-date = 30 March 2010 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\nPausini's first record for the British market was a [[Laura Pausini (1995 album)|self-titled compilation album]] released in 1995, including nine Italian-language hits and an [[English-language]] version of her first single, \"La solitudine (Loneliness)\",<ref>{{cite web | url = {{Allmusic|class=album|id=r298755|pure_url=yes}} | work = [[Allmusic]] | accessdate =27 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini [English<nowiki>]</nowiki>}}</ref> whose lyrics were adapted by [[Tim Rice]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1994/12/22/la-pausini-in-inghilterra-tradotta-da-tim.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = La Pausini in Inghilterra tradotta da Tim Rice | date = 22 December 1994}}</ref> \"La solitudine (Loneliness)\" was initially set to be released as a single in the United Kingdom on 19 June 1995,<ref>{{cite web | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=zwsEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA54#v=onepage&q&f=false | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate = 2 September 2012 | date = 24 June 1995 | page = 54 | author = Thom Duffy | title = McKennitt's Italian sojourn; Stones start European tour}}</ref> but it was postponed and released in September of the same year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adnkronos.com/Archivio/AdnAgenzia/1995/11/13/Spettacolo/MUSICA-LAURA-PAUSINI-NON-PARLA-INGLESE-2_154900.php |publisher=[[Adnkronos]] |language=Italian |date=13 November 1995 |title=Musica: Laura Pausini non parla inglese (2) |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130101222817/http://www.adnkronos.com/Archivio/AdnAgenzia/1995/11/13/Spettacolo/MUSICA-LAURA-PAUSINI-NON-PARLA-INGLESE-2_154900.php |archivedate= 1 January 2013 |accessdate=8 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> Both the album and the single obtained a very poor commercial reception, failing to enter the charts in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adnkronos.com/Archivio/AdnAgenzia/1995/11/13/Spettacolo/MUSICA-LAURA-PAUSINI-NON-PARLA-INGLESE_154200.php |work=[[Adnkronos]] |language=Italian |title=Musica: Laura Pausini non parla inglese |date=13 November 1995 |accessdate=8 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130306094954/http://www.adnkronos.com/Archivio/AdnAgenzia/1995/11/13/Spettacolo/MUSICA-LAURA-PAUSINI-NON-PARLA-INGLESE_154200.php |archivedate= 6 March 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\n=== 1996\u20131997: ''Le cose che vivi'' and World Wide Tour 1997 ===\nFollowing the success obtained by Pausini's debut Spanish album, her third studio set was released on 12 September 1996 both in Italian and Spanish, under the titles ''[[Le cose che vivi]]'' and ''Las cosas que vives'', respectively.<ref name=LaStampaLeCoseCheVivi>{{cite web | url =http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1611453 | work = [[La Stampa]] | date = 19 July 1996  |accessdate = 8 September 2013 | page = 25 | title = Pausini e soci: i nuovi dischi|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314004144/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1611453|archivedate=14 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=AdnkronosLeCoseCheVivi>{{cite web | url = http://www.adnkronos.com/Archivio/AdnAgenzia/1996/08/26/Spettacolo/MUSICA-ESCE-IN-32-PAESI-IL-DISCO-DELLA-PAUSINI_190600.php | publisher = [[Adnkronos]] | language = Italian | date = 26 August 1996 | title = Musica: esce in 32 Paesi il disco della Pausini | accessdate = 20 September 2012}}</ref>\nStarting from that moment, Pausini has recorded most of her songs both in her native language and in Spanish, in a practice that, according to [[Allmusic]]'s Jason Birchmeier, has \"come to define her career and compound her success\".<ref name=allmusic>{{cite web | url = http://www.allmusic.com/artist/laura-pausini-mn0000138235 |work = [[Allmusic]] | title = Laura Pausini: Biography | date = October 2009 | author = Jason Birchmeier|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021160045/http://www.allmusic.com/artist/laura-pausini-mn0000138235|archivedate=21 October 2012|accessdate=7 September 2013}}</ref>\nA special edition of the album was also released in Brazil, featuring three additional bonus tracks in Portuguese.<ref name=AdnkronosLeCoseCheVivi/>\n\nThe album was preceded by the single \"[[Incancellabile]]\", released to Italian radio stations on 26 August 1996<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1996/agosto/27/Laura_Pausini_settembre_alla_conquista_co_0_9608275922.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 20 September 2012 | title = Laura Pausini da settembre alla conquista di 32 Paesi | page = 33 | date = 27 August 1996}}</ref> and titled \"Inolvidable\" in its version for the Hispanic market. Other singles from the album include the title-track \"[[Le cose che vivi (song)|Le cose che vivi]]\", whose Spanish-language version topped the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Latin Pop Songs]] chart,<ref>{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=laura pausini|chart=Latin Pop Songs C}} |work=[[Billboard.com]] |accessdate=20 September 2012 |title=Laura Pausini Album & Song Chart History \u2013 Latin Pop Songs |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100622085225/http://www.billboard.com/ |archivedate=22 June 2010 }}</ref> \"[[Ascolta il tuo cuore]]\", \"Seamisai\" and \"Dos enamorados\", which was not released in its Italian-language version. The album sold 3,500,000 copies worldwide<ref name=\"LauraSales\"/> and was certified Platinum by the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]], for European sales exceeding 1,000,000 units.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ifpi.org/content/section_news/plat1997.html | publisher = [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = IFPI Platinum Europe Award \u2013 1997}}</ref>\nAt the [[Premio Lo Nuestro 1997|9th Lo Nuestro Awards for Latin Music]], Pausini was nominated for Pop Female Singer and Video of the Year for the Spanish-language version of \"[[Le cose che vivi (song)|Le cose che vivi]]\".<ref name=\"eltiempo\">{{cite news|url=http://www.eltiempo.com/archivo/documento/MAM-545706|title=Premios a Lo Mejor De La M\u00fasica Latina|language=Spanish|work=[[El Tiempo (Colombia)|El Tiempo]]|publisher=Casa Editorial El Tiempo S.A.|date=8 April 1997|accessdate=10 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn December 1996, Pausini was among the artists singing for [[Pope John Paul II]] during the Natale in Vaticano concert, a Christmas show held at the [[Paul VI Audience Hall]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1996/12/17/ron-una-canzone-regalo-per-il.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | date = 17 December 1996 | title = Ron: una canzone-regalo per il Papa | page = 45}}</ref> During the event, she performed a cover of [[John Lennon]]'s \"[[Happy Xmas (War Is Over)]]\" and the song \"Il mondo che vorrei\".<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1685874 | work = [[La Stampa]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 20 September 2012 | title = Canale 5, Concerto di Natale. L'Orchestra Filarmonica protagonista in Vaticano | date = 20 December 2012 | page = 104 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://archive.today/20120709100522/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1685874 | archivedate = 9 July 2012 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\nIn February 1997 she was also invited as a guest to the [[Vi\u00f1a del Mar International Song Festival]] in Chile.<ref>{{cite web | url= http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1997/febbraio/23/Ambra_vortice_erotico_Vina_del_co_0_97022311528.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | date = 23 February 1997 | language = Italian | title = Ambra vortice erotico a Vina del Mar. E Laura Pausini canta in spagnolo | page = 32}}</ref>\nOn 1 March 1997, she launched from [[Geneva]] the World Wide Tour in support of the album, giving concerts in Italy, Switzerland,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1721619 | title = A Ginevra l'apertura del tour mondiale. Pausini, una voce per il made in Italy | author = Marinella Venegoni | work = [[La Stampa]] | date = 3 March 1997 | language = Italian | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131018123513/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1721619 | archivedate = 18 October 2013 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> Belgium, the Netherlands, Portugal,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1997/marzo/03/Pausini_tour_effetto_speciale_sono_co_0_9703039566.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | accessdate = 20 September 2012 | date = 3 March 1997 | title = Pausini in tour: l' effetto speciale sono io | author = Mario Luzzatto Fegiz | language = Italian}}</ref> Spain,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://elpais.com/diario/1997/04/24/madrid/861881069_850215.html | work = [[El Pa\u00eds]] | language = Spanish | title = Pausini, diva y correcta como una madonna | date = 24 April 1997 | author = Fernando I\u00f1iguez | accessdate = 20 September 2012}}</ref> France,<ref name=AdnkronosTour1997>{{cite web |url = http://www.adnkronos.com/Archivio/AdnAgenzia/1997/02/05/Spettacolo/MUSICA-LAURA-PAUSINI-ARTISTA-DA-ESPORTAZIONE-2_174600.php | publisher = [[Adnkronos]] | date = 5 February 1997 | language = Italian | accessdate = 20 September 2012 | title = Musica: Laura Pausini artista da esportazione}}</ref> as well as in the United States,<ref name=SunSentinel1997/> Canada and many American countries, including Venezuela, Brazil, Uruguay, Argentina, Paraguay, Colombia and Mexico.<ref name=AdnkronosTour1997/> It was Pausini's first international tour, during which she gave concerts in [[indoor arenas]] for the first time.<ref>{{Cite book | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=b-6Y0YZ38z0C&pg=PT658#v=onepage&q&f=false | title = Mille concerti che ci hanno cambiato la vita | chapter = Laura Pausini, una ragazza normale alla conquista del mondo | author = Ezio Guaitamacchi | editor = [[RCS MediaGroup|Rizzoli]] | year = 2010 | language = Italian | isbn = 9788817042222}}</ref>\nIn August of the same year, during the last night of the [[Festivalbar]], she received the International Award for the success she achieved abroad.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1997/08/31/daniele-re-del-festivalbar.html| work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 20 September 2012 | date = 31 August 1997 | author = Eleonora Bertolotto | page = 39 | title = Daniele re del Festivalbar}}</ref>\n\n===1998\u20131999: ''La mia risposta'' / ''Mi respuesta'' and second World Tour===\nIn 1998, Pausini released her fourth studio album, ''[[La mia risposta]]'', together with its Spanish-language counterpart, ''Mi respuesta''. The album, which included a song penned by [[Phil Collins]],<ref name=\"StampaMiaRisposta\">{{cite web|url=http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=2250188 |work=[[La Stampa]] |language=Italian |accessdate=30 July 2011 |title=Dopo l'adolescenziale \"La solitudine\", un disco maturo con venature soul. Pausini, la metamorfosi: Canta Phil Collins, pensa agli Usa |author=Marinella Venegoni |date=15 October 1998 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005080920/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=2250188 |archivedate=5 October 2011 }}</ref> was dubbed by Italian music critics as a mature work, with influences from [[soul music]],<ref name=\"StampaMiaRisposta\"/> but, despite reaching the top spot of the [[Italian Albums Chart]],<ref>{{cite web | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=IQoEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA50#v=onepage&q&f=false | publisher = [[Nielsen Business Media, Inc.]] | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate = 8 August 2012 | title = Hits of the World \u2013 Italy | page = 50 | date = 7 November 1998}}</ref> it was a moderate commercial success, selling two million copies worldwide.<ref name=\"LauraSales\"/>\nThe lead single from the album, \"[[Un'emergenza d'amore]]\", was released in September 1998,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adnkronos.com/Archivio/AdnAgenzia/1998/09/10/Spettacolo/LAURA-PAUSINI-EMERGENZA-DAMORE-DA-DOMANI-NELLE-RADIO_201100.php|publisher=[[Adnkronos]]|language=Italian|date=10 September 1998|title=Laura Pausini: Emergenza d'amore da domani nelle radio|accessdate=8 September 2013}}</ref> and was followed by \"[[In assenza di te]]\" and \"[[La mia risposta (song)|La mia risposta]]\", the latter being performed during the [[Festivalbar]] in 1999.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adnkronos.com/Archivio/AdnAgenzia/1999/06/21/Spettacolo/ITALIA-1-FESTIVALBAR_152900.php|publisher=[[Adnkronos]]|language=Italian|accessdate=8 September 2013|date=21 June 1999|title=Italia 1: Festivalbar}}</ref>\n\nTo promote the album, Pausini began in early 1999 the [[La Mia Risposta World Tour '99]], during which she performed in theatres throughout Europe.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1999/marzo/02/Pausini_conquista_Firenze_Canto_anche_co_0_9903021395.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | language = Italian | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = La Pausini conquista Firenze \"Canto anche Madre Teresa\" | author = Emilia Costantini | date = 2 March 1999}}</ref>\nOn 1 June 1999, she was one of the artists performing along with Italian [[tenor]] [[Luciano Pavarotti]] in [[Modena]] during his annual \"Pavarotti and Friends\" concert.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1999/maggio/01/Gianni_Morandi_detto_Festival_Pavarotti_co_0_9905016308.shtml | newspaper = [[Corriere della Sera]] | date = 1 May 1999 | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Gianni Morandi ha detto s\u00ec al Festival di Pavarotti | language = Italian}}</ref> Pavarotti and Pausini duetted in the Italian version of the [[aria]] \"[[Dein ist mein ganzes Herz]]\", titled \"Tu che m'hai preso il cuor\", from [[Franz Leh\u00e1r]]'s [[operetta]] ''[[Das Land des L\u00e4chelns]]''. The live performance was later included in the album ''Pavarotti & Friends for the Children of Guatemala and Kosovo''.<ref name=\"PavarottiAndFirends\">{{cite web | url = http://www.pop24.de/musik/musik-detail/product/73954/pavarotti-und-friends-for-the-children-of-guatemala-and-kosovo/| publisher = Pop24.de | accessdate =8 September 2013 | title = Pavarotti & Friends \u2013 Pavarotti & Friends for the Children of Guatemala And Kosovo | language = German|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111001162952/http://www.pop24.de/musik/musik-detail/product/73954/pavarotti-und-friends-for-the-children-of-guatemala-and-kosovo/|archivedate=1 October 2011}}</ref>\nIn 1999 she also contributed the [[Richard Marx]] composition \"[[One More Time (Laura Pausini song)|One More Time]]\" to the ''[[Message in a Bottle (film)|Message in a Bottle]]'' soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.rockol.it/news-5843/c-e-anche-la-voce-di-laura-pausini-nel-nuovo-film-di-kevin-costner | publisher = Rockol.it | accessdate =8 September 2013| title = C'\u00e8 anche la voce di Laura Pausini nel nuovo film di Kevin Kostner|date=2 April 1999}}</ref> The track was produced by [[David Foster]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ultratop.be/fr/showitem.asp?interpret=Laura+Pausini&titel=One+More+Time&cat=s | publisher = [[Ultratop]] | language = French | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 One More Time (chanson)}}</ref> who was featured on piano.\n\n===2000\u20132001: ''Tra te e il mare'' / ''Entre t\u00fa y mil mares'' and greatest hits album===\nIn 2000, she recorded the song \"The Extra Mile\" for the soundtrack of the movie ''[[Pok\u00e9mon: The Movie 2000|Pok\u00e9mon 2000: The Power of One]]''.<ref name=\"Repubblica15092000\">{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2000/09/15/laura-pausini-canta-in-inglese-comincia-con.html | work = [[La Repubblica]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini canta in inglese e comincia con Pokemon | date = 15 September 2000 | author = Giacomo Pellicciotti | language = Italian}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | journal = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | date = 15 July 2000 | url = https://books.google.com/?id=-g8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA21&lpg=PA21&dq=pausini+pokemon+soundtrack+billboard#v=onepage&q&f=false | title = Soundtracks and film score news | author = Charles Karel Bouley | accessdate =30 July 2011}}</ref> The song was included in the album ''[[Tra te e il mare]]'', released on 11 September 2000 and preceded by the [[Tra te e il mare (song)|homonymous]] single, written by Italian pop singer [[Biagio Antonacci]].<ref name=TraTeEIlMareRelease>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2000/agosto/22/Esce_singolo_Laura_Pausini_firmato_co_0_0008228258.shtml | publisher = 30 July 2011 | title = Esce il singolo di Laura Pausini firmato da Biagio Antonacci | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | language = Italian}}</ref> Other singles from the album include \"[[Il mio sbaglio pi\u00f9 grande]]\", which was a top 20 hit in Italy,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://italiancharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Laura+Pausini&titel=Il+mio+sbaglio+pi%F9+grande&cat=s|publisher=Italiancharts.com. Hung Medien|title=Italian Charts \u2013 Laura Pausini \u2013 Il mio sbaglio pi\u00f9 grande (song)|accessdate=8 September 2013}}</ref> and \"Volevo dirti che ti amo\", whose Spanish-language version \"Quiero decirte que te amo\" peaked at number 15 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Latin Pop Songs]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/306634/laura%2Bpausini/chart?page=1&f=372 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=8 September 2013 |title=Laura Pausini Album & Song Chart History \u2013 Latin Pop Songs |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130908161519/http://www.billboard.com/artist/306634/laura%2Bpausini/chart?page=1&f=372 |archivedate= 8 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\nThe album also features the songs \"Viaggio con te\", which was composed by her father and which was awarded in 2001 with an Italian Lunezia Award for Best Songwriter of the Year,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.premiolunezia.it/albo/index.htm | publisher = Premiolunezia.it | language = Italian| title = Premio Lunezia \u2013 Albo d'oro | accessdate =8 September 2013|archivedate=12 February 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080212003147/http://www.premiolunezia.it/albo/index.htm}}</ref><ref name=FamigliaCristiana2000>{{cite web|url=http://www.stpauls.it/fc00/0039fc/0039fc96.htm |work=[[Famiglia Cristiana]] |language=Italian |accessdate=8 September 2013 |author=[[Gigi Vesigna]] |title=Spettacolo: Laura Pausini presenta il suo nuovo disco. Quella passione che ci unisce |date=1 October 2001 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130908160148/http://www.stpauls.it/fc00/0039fc/0039fc96.htm |archivedate= 8 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> and \"Per vivere\", written from the point of view of a homeless child Pausini met in [[Rio de Janeiro]] and dedicated to two Brazilian children [[Child sponsorship|sponsored]] by her.<ref name=FamigliaCristiana2000/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.corriere.it/spettacoli/soundsandsummers/schede_artisti/pausini_1f61cba0-b7d2-11e1-a264-b99bbdd148d8.shtml|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|language=Italian|accessdate=8 September 2013|title=Laura Pausini|date=16 June 2012}}</ref>\n\n''Tra te e il mare'' received a nomination for Album of the Year at the Premio Italiano della Musica, while Pausini was nominated for Best Female Artist during the same award ceremony,<ref name=\"PIM2001\">{{cite web | url = http://www.rockol.it/news-28857/Rese-note-le-nominations-per-il-Premio-Italiano-della-Musica  | language = Italian | publisher = Rockol.it | accessdate = 28 October 2011 | title = Rese note le nominations per il Premio Italiano della Musica | date = 16 February 2001}}</ref> as well as in the first edition of the [[Italian Music Awards]], held in February 2001.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.rockol.it/news-27502/Le-nomination-agli-Italian-Music-Awards--quasi-un-plebiscito-per-i-L%C3%B9napop | publisher = Rockol.it | accessdate =8 September 2013| title = Le nomination agli Italian Music Awards: quasi un plebiscito per i L\u00f9napop | date = 12 January 2001|archivedate=7 July 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120707210924/http://www.rockol.it/news-27502/Le-nomination-agli-Italian-Music-Awards--quasi-un-plebiscito-per-i-L%C3%B9napop}}</ref>\nA Spanish-language version of the album, titled ''Entre t\u00fa y mil mares'', was released shortly before the Italian-language edition, on 11 September 2000.<ref name=TraTeEIlMareRelease/> At the [[Latin Grammy Awards of 2001|2001 Latin Grammy Awards]], the record received two nominations for [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Female Pop Vocal Album|Best Female Pop Vocal Album]] and [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Engineered Album|Best Engineered Album]], while Pausini and Alfredo Cerruti were in the shortlist for [[Latin Grammy Award for Producer of the Year|Producer of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://articles.latimes.com/2001/jul/18/entertainment/ca-23444 | work = [[Los Angeles Times]] | title = The Full List of Nominations | date = 18 July 2001|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026135501/http://articles.latimes.com/2001/jul/18/entertainment/ca-23444|archivedate=26 October 2012}}</ref><ref name=LatinGrammys2001>{{cite web | url = http://articles.latimes.com/2001/jul/18/entertainment/ca-23444/3 | work = [[Los Angeles Times]] | date = 18 July 2001 | accessdate = 1 September 2012 | title = The Full List of Nominations (part 3)|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114011007/http://articles.latimes.com/2001/jul/18/entertainment/ca-23444/3|archivedate=14 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nPausini's first international [[greatest hits album]] was released in 2001, both in an Italian-language version and in a Spanish-language edition, titled ''[[The Best of Laura Pausini: E ritorno da te]]'' and ''Lo mejor de Laura Pausini: Volver\u00e9 junto a ti'', respectively. The first single, \"[[E ritorno da te (song)|E ritorno da te]]\"\u2014\"Volver\u00e9 junto a ti\" in Spanish\u2014was accompanied by a music video shot by Italian film director [[Gabriele Muccino]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.rockol.it/news-36261/Laura-Pausini,-il-suo-%27Best-of%27-esce-il-12-ottobre | publisher = Rockol.it | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini, il suo 'Best of' esce il 12 ottobre | date = 16 September 2001 | language = Italian}}</ref> The album also includes the single \"Una storia che vale\" and features guest appearances by Brazilian singer [[Gilberto Gil]] in \"Seamisai\"<ref name=\"LaStampa9October2001\">{{cite web | url = http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=3303853 | work = [[La Stampa]] | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Anche un CD in inglese con l'aiuto di Santana. Pausini: canto e non m'arrendo | author = Marinella Venegoni | date = 9 October 2001 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20111005080939/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=3303853 | archivedate = 5 October 2011 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> and by Italian singer [[Nek]], who plays bass in \"[[Non c'\u00e8]]\".<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.rockol.it/vetrina-529/Laura-Pausini-E-RITORNO-DA-TE---THE-BEST-OF-LAURA-PAUSINI| publisher = Rockol.it | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 E Ritorno da Te \u2013 The Best of Laura Pausini | language = Italian}}</ref>\n\nSupported by the [[2001/2002 World Tour]], which started in Miami on 19 October 2001,<ref name=\"LaStampa9October2001\"/> the greatest hits became one of Pausini's biggest commercial successes, selling 700,000 copies in Italy and 800,000 copies in France.<ref name=\"Sales\">{{Cite journal | journal = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | title = Laura Pausini matures with new studio set | accessdate =27 July 2011 | url = https://books.google.com/?id=nRMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA57&dq=shipped+laura+pausini#v=onepage&q=shipped%20laura%20pausini&f=false | author = Mark Worden | date = 23 October 2003}}</ref>\nDuring the concert she gave in [[Milan]] on 2 December 2001 as part of the tour, Pausini also recorded her first live [[video album]], titled ''[[Live 2001-2002 World Tour]]'' and released on 30 November 2002.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2003/gennaio/06/Boom_del_rock_vedere_Raddoppia_co_0_0301061855.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Boom del rock da vedere Raddoppia il mercato Dvd | author = Andrea Laffranchi | date = 6 January 2003 | language = Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.musicafilm.it/music-dvds/live-2001-2002-world-tour.html | publisher = Musicafilm.it | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Live 2001\u20132002 World Tour \u2013 Laura Pausini|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120317052059/http://www.musicafilm.it/music-dvds/live-2001-2002-world-tour.html|archivedate=17 March 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2002\u20132003: ''From the Inside'', the English-language debut===\nIn 2001, Pausini started working with producers such as [[Patrick Leonard]] and [[John Shanks]]<ref>{{cite web | url = {{BillboardURLbyName|artist=laura pausini|chart=all}} | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = From the Inside \u2013 Laura Pausini}}</ref> on her first English-language album, ''[[From the Inside (Laura Pausini album)|From the Inside]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2001/ottobre/09/Laura_Pausini_canta_inglese_co_0_0110092619.shtml| work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | author = Mario Luzzatto Fegiz | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Pausini canta in inglese | date = 9 October 2001}}</ref>\nReleased in Canada, Mexico and the United States by [[Atlantic Records]] on 5 November 2002, the album did not get the expected success, selling 50,000 copies in the U.S., according to Nielsen-Soundscan.<ref name=\"BillboardUSSales\">{{cite journal | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=MQ8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA50#v=onepage&q&f=false | journal = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | title = Primed for the U.S | author = Chuck Taylor | accessdate =27 July 2011 | date = 15 March 2011 | page = 50}}</ref>\nThe album singles \"[[Surrender (Laura Pausini song)|Surrender]]\" and \"If That's Love\" reached the top spot on the [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] Chart,<ref>{{cite web | url = {{BillboardURLbyName|artist=laura pausini|chart=Dance/Club Play Songs}} | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate =29 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini Album & Song Chart History \u2013 Dance/Club Play Songs}}</ref> but Pausini, disappointed at her English-language debut being ignored in the U.S. outside the club scene, abandoned the promotion for ''From the Inside'' due to her label promoting it as a dance album instead of a pop album as she requested.<ref name=Corriere>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2003/gennaio/08/Pausini_americana_studiato_inglese_per_co_0_0301081590.shtml | title = Pausini l'americana: ho studiato inglese per scalare la classifica | accessdate =30 July 2011 | author = Sandra Cesarale | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | date = 8 January 2003}}</ref>\nThe album was later released in Europe too, selling 800,000 copies worldwide.<ref name=\"Sales\"/>\n\nIn 2003 Luciano Pavarotti invited her for the second time to the \"Pavarotti and Friends\" concert, where they duetted again in \"Tu che m'hai preso il cuor\".<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.rockol.it/musicaitaliana.com/news/it/2003/03042903.html | publisher = Rockol.it | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Pavarotti & Friends, decima edizione: ecco il cast 2003 | language = Italian | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110716033221/http://www.rockol.it/musicaitaliana.com/news/it/2003/03042903.html | archivedate = 16 July 2011 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===2004\u20132005: ''Resta in ascolto'' / ''Escucha'' and the Grammy===\n[[File:LauraPausini.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Laura Pausini during the presentation of her album [[Resta in ascolto|''Resta in ascolto'' / ''Escucha'']] in 2004.]]\n\nIn October 2004 Pausini released her eight studio album, ''[[Resta in ascolto]]'', and its Spanish-language counterpart, ''Escucha''. Influenced by international artists including [[Phil Collins]] and [[Celine Dion]],<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.billboard.com/album/laura-pausini/resta-in-ascolto/654563/review#/album/laura-pausini/resta-in-ascolto/654563/review | publisher = www.billboard.com | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Resta in Ascolto \u2013 Laura Pausini | author = Alex Henderson}}</ref> the recording is on the subject of a break-up and was written in 2002, during her separation from her ex-boyfriend and producer Alfredo Cerruti.<ref name=\"Repubblica5February05\">{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2005/02/05/pausini-che-grinta-non-posso-tacere-canto.html | work  = [[La Repubblica]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Pausini, che grinta 'Non posso tacere canto anche l'Iraq' | author = Lucia Marchio | date = 5 February 2005}}</ref>\n\nThe album features the song \"Mi abbandono a te\", co-written by Pausini, [[Rick Nowels]] and [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]. It also includes the [[Biagio Antonacci]]-written ballad \"[[Vivimi]]\", whose Spanish-language version, \"Viveme\", won a [[Billboard Latin Music Award]] in 2006 for Female Latin Pop Airplay Song of the Year,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/billboardlatinmusic/2006/index.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061022042549/http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/billboardlatinmusic/2006/index.html|archivedate=22 October 2006|accessdate=7 September 2013|title=ASCAP Presents... at 17th Annual Billboard Latin Music Conference & Awards|publisher=[[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers]]}}</ref> and the single \"Benedetta passione\", penned by Italian rock-star [[Vasco Rossi]].<ref name=\"Corriere23Sept04\">{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2004/settembre/23/per_Laura_Pausini_inno_alla_co_9_040923072.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | date = 23 September 2004 | language = Italian | author = Andrea Laffranchi | title = E per Laura Pausini inno alla pace scritto a quattro mani con Madonna}}</ref> Well received by music critics,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.musicaedischi.it/recensioni.php?genere=0&id=2046| publisher = Musica e dischi | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 Resta in ascolto  **** |author = Mario De Luigi | date = October 2010 | language = Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/resta-in-ascolto-r714662 | author = Alex Henderson | title = Resta in Ascolto \u2013 Laura Pausini | work = [[Allmusic]] | accessdate =30 July 2011}}</ref> the album is mainly focused on themes of anger, bitterness,<ref name=\"Repubblica5February05\"/> desire for independence<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.mtv.it/news/news-detail.asp?idnews=15629 | publisher = MTV | language = Italian | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = La Prospettiva Di Laura \u2013 Nuovo singolo e DVD Live in Paris per Miss Pausini | date = 3 November 2005}}</ref> and interior peace,<ref name=\"Corriere23Sept04\"/> but also features a song about the [[Iraq War]], in which Pausini sings about [[Ali Ismail Abbas]], a boy who was severely injured in a nighttime rocket attack near [[Baghdad]] in 2003.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2005/01/30/pausini-che-delusione-il-mio-sogno-americano.html | work = [[La Repubblica]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Pausini: Che delusione il mio sogno americano | date = 30 January 2005 | language = Italian | author = Carlo Moretti}}</ref>\n\nThe album debuted at number one on the [[Italian Albums Chart]]<ref>{{cite web  |url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2004/11/03/laura-pausini-prima-in-classifica.html | work = [[La Repubblica]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | language = Italian | date = 3 November 2004 | title = Laura Pausini prima in classifica}}</ref> and sold 350,000 copies in Italy.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ilvaltrompianews.it/det_articolo.php?IdEd=19&IdArt=634 | publisher = www.ilvaltrompianews.it | language = Italian | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Word tour '05 con Laura Pausini | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120328091133/http://www.ilvaltrompianews.it/det_articolo.php?IdEd=19&IdArt=634 | archivedate = 28 March 2012 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> Its Spanish version later won [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Female Pop Vocal Album|Best Female Pop Vocal Album]] at the [[Latin Grammy Awards of 2005]]<ref name=\"LatinGrammy2005\">{{cite web | url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/60804/2005-latin-grammy-awards-winners | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate =29 July 2011 | title = 2005 Latin Grammy Awards Winners}}</ref> and [[Grammy Award for Best Latin Pop Album|Best Latin Pop Album]] at the [[48th Grammy Awards]],<ref name=\"GrammyAward\"/> making Pausini the first Italian female artist to win a [[Grammy Award]].<ref name=\"RepubblicaGrammy\"/>\nIn January 2005, Pausini started [[World Tour '05|a new tour to promote the album]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.all4show.it/vis_dettaglio.php?primo_livello=menu&id_livello=235 |publisher=All4show.it |accessdate=30 July 2011 |language=Italian |title=Date Tour Pausini 2005 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120720152726/http://www.all4show.it/vis_dettaglio.php?primo_livello=menu&id_livello=235 |archivedate=20 July 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> The concerts she gave at the [[Z\u00e9nith de Paris]] on 22 and 23 March 2005 were filmed and released as a live album in November 2005, titled ''[[Live in Paris 05]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockol.it/news-74656/Cd-e-DVD-live-per-Laura-Pausini |publisher=Rockol.it |language=Italian |accessdate=8 September 2013 |title=Cd e DVD live per Laura Pausini |date=4 November 2005 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130908154436/http://www.rockol.it/news-74656/cd-e-dvd-live-per-laura-pausini |archivedate= 8 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\nPausini made a guest appearance on [[Michael Bubl\u00e9]]'s 2005 live album ''[[Caught in the Act (Michael Bubl\u00e9 album)|Caught in the Act]]'', singing a duet with Bubl\u00e9 of [[Lou Rawls]]' hit \"[[You'll Never Find Another Love Like Mine]]\". The duet was placed on both the [[Compact Disc|audio CD]], and the full concert DVD that aired on [[Public Broadcasting Service|PBS]] as an episode of ''[[Great Performances]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockol.it/recensione-3124/Michael-Bubl%C3%A9-CAUGHT-IN-THE-ACT|publisher=Rockol.it|language=Italian|accessdate=15 November 2014|title=Michael Bubl\u00e9 - Caught in the Act - Recensione|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091108203835/http://www.rockol.it/recensione-3124/Michael-Bubl%C3%A9-CAUGHT-IN-THE-ACT|date=13 December 2005|archivedate=8 November 2009}}</ref>\n\nAt the [[Premios Lo Nuestro 2006|2006 Lo Nuestro Award]], Pausini was nominated in the sections Album of the Year for ''Escucha'', Song of the Year and Video of the Year for \"Viveme\"<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.hispanicbusiness.com/hispanicprwire/2005/12/13/univision_announces_premio_lo_nuestro_2006.htm| work = Hispanic Business | accessdate =8 September 2013 | date = 13 December 2005 | title = Univision Announces 'Premio Lo Nuestro' 2006 Nominees|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120806013814/http://www.hispanicbusiness.com/2005/12/13/univision_announces_premio_lo_nuestro_2006.htm|archivedate=6 August 2012}}</ref> and won the award for Best Female Pop Artist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.terra.com/musica/noticias/premios_lo_nuestro_2006_los_preferidos_de_los_usuarios_de_terra/oci74944 |publisher=[[Terra Networks]] |language=Spanish |accessdate=8 September 2013 |title=Premios Lo Nuestro 2006: Los Preferidos de los Usuarios de Terra |date=1 February 2006 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120911125828/http://www.terra.com/musica/noticias/premios_lo_nuestro_2006_los_preferidos_de_los_usuarios_de_terra/oci74944 |archivedate=11 September 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\n===2006\u20132007: ''Io canto'' and the concert in San Siro===\n[[File:Laura Pausini1 adjusted.jpg|thumb|right|180px|Pausini performing during the Festival Teatro-Canzone, in memory of Italian singer [[Giorgio Gaber]], on 21 July 2007.]]\nIn November 2006, Pausini released the album [[Io canto|''Io canto'' / ''Yo canto'']], consisting of covers of Italian [[pop rock]] songs.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.mtv.com/music/artist/pausini_laura/artist.jhtml#biographyEnd | publisher = MTV | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 Full Biography}}</ref> On the album liner notes, Pausini wrote:\n\"here is the music I listen to when I'm at my saddest, or when I feel a moment is special, the songs I used to sing as a young girl when I first started performing, and above all those which taught me to love music, and how music can move you so deeply, regardless of its genre or style\".<ref>{{cite web | url = https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/io-canto-spanish-premium-version/id203047936 | publisher = [[iTunes]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Io canto (Spanish Premium Version) by Laura Pausini}}</ref>\n\nThe album also features duets with [[Tiziano Ferro]], [[Juanes]] and [[Johnny Hallyday]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B000IY04OU | publisher = www.amazon.co.uk | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Io Canto \u2013 Laura Pausini}}</ref> It debuted at number one on the [[Italian Albums Chart]] and held the top spot for 8 non-consecutive weeks.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://italiancharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Laura+Pausini&titel=Io+canto&cat=a | publisher = italiancharts.com | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 Io canto (album)}}</ref> It also became the best-selling album of 2006 in Italy, selling 500,000 copies in less than two months.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/global/homegrown-acts-dominate-2006-italy-record-1003530295.story | publisher = www.billboard.biz | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Homegrown Acts Dominate 2006 Italy Record Sales | author = Mark Worden | date = 10 January 2007}}</ref> On 8 November 2007, the album won [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album, Female|Best Female Pop Vocal Album]] at the [[Latin Grammy Awards]].<ref name=\"LatinGrammy2007\">{{cite web | url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1047366/juan-luis-guerra-dominates-latin-grammy-awards | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | title = Juan Luis Guerra Dominates Latin Grammy Awards}}</ref>\nLaura dedicated the award to the memory of Italian tenor [[Luciano Pavarotti]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=8080733 | work = [[La Stampa]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Latin Grammy Award Pausini vince e dedica il premio a Pavarotti | date = 10 November 2007 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120314004221/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=8080733 | archivedate = 14 March 2012 | df = dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/09/arts/music/09grammy.html?scp=11&sq=laura%20pausini&st=cse | work = [[The New York Times]] | accessdate =13 August 2011 | date = 9 November 2007 | title = For One Dominican Songwriter, Top Music Honors | author = Jon Pareles}}</ref> Later on during the show she sang \"[[Vivere (Dare to Live)]]\" alongside Italian singer [[Andrea Bocelli]].<ref name=\"LatinGrammy2007\"/>\n\nIn Summer 2006, Pausini played a [[Juntos en concierto 2006|Juntos en concierto tour]] with [[Marc Anthony]] and [[Marco Antonio Sol\u00eds]],<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/news/e3i7b7c9db010011fac34dca14062def7c8 | publisher = www.billboard.biz | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Marc Anthony Plans Third Juntos Concert Series | date = 28 May 2008 | author = Leila Cobo}}</ref> consisting of 20 concerts throughout the United States.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.adnkronos.com/Archivio/AdnAgenzia/2006/10/11/Spettacolo/Musica/MUSICA-LAURA-PAUSINI-ARRIVA-IL-NUOVO-SINGOLO-IO-CANTO-2_110450.php | publisher = [[Adnkronos]] | language = Italian | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Musica: Laura Pausini, arriva il nuovo singolo Io canto | date = 11 October 2006}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 June 2007, Laura Pausini was the first female artist to play at the [[San Siro Stadium]] in Milan,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.mtv.it/news/news-detail.asp?idnews=19488 | publisher = MTV | language = Italian | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini a San Siro | date = 25 January 2007}}</ref> in front of a crowd of 70,000 spectators.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2007/06/04/un-trionfo-per-laura-pausini-settantamila-in.html | work = [[La Repubblica]] | language = Italian | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Un trionfo per Laura Pausini settantamila in delirio a S.Siro | author = Gino Castaldo | date = 4 June 2007}}</ref> On 30 November 2007, the concert was released on CD and DVD, under the title ''[[San Siro 2007]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.mtv.it/news/news-detail.asp?idnews=21877 | publisher = MTV | language = Italian | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini in DVD | date = 20 November 2007}}</ref>\n\n===2008\u20132010: ''Primavera in anticipo'', ''Amiche per l'Abruzzo'' and ''Laura Live''===\n[[File:AmicheXlAbruzzo.jpg|thumb|left|250px|thumb|Concert of ''Amiche per l'Abruzzo''.]]\n\nPausini spent the first months of 2008 recording her tenth studio album, [[Primavera in anticipo|''Primavera in anticipo'' / ''Primavera anticipada'']]. The Spanish language edition of the album was released on 11 November 2008,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.eventosonline.cl/laura-pausino-lanza-primavera-anticipada-su-decimo-album-en-espanol/537.htm | publisher = www.eventosonline.cl | language = Spanish | title = Laura Pausini lanza \"Primavera Anticipada\" su decimo album en espa\u00f1ol | date = 10 November 2008 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090102064543/http://www.eventosonline.cl/laura-pausino-lanza-primavera-anticipada-su-decimo-album-en-espanol/537.htm | archivedate = 2 January 2009 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> while the Italian language edition was released in Italy on 14 November 2008.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.lastampa.it/cmstp/rubriche/stampa.asp?ID_blog=37&ID_articolo=1163 | archive-url = https://archive.today/20120904193917/http://www.lastampa.it/cmstp/rubriche/stampa.asp?ID_blog=37&ID_articolo=1163 | url-status = dead | archive-date = 4 September 2012 | work = [[La Stampa]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Il nuovo singolo della Pausini da venerd\u00ec in radio | date = 22 October 2008 }}</ref>\nThe album was preceded by the single [[Invece no|\"Invece no\" / \"En cambio no\"]], released on 24 October 2008<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.musicalnews.com/articolo.php?codice=13878&sz=5 | publisher = www.musicalnews.com | language = Italian | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini: Invece, no \u2013 il nuovo singolo in radio dal 24 ottobre | author = Laura Gorini | date = 21 October 2008 | archive-url = https://archive.today/20120911173120/http://www.musicalnews.com/articolo.php?codice=13878&sz=5 | archive-date = 11 September 2012 | url-status = dead }}</ref> and promoted with an appearance in [[Spanish Steps|Piazza Trinit\u00e0 dei Monti]] in Rome on 14 November 2008.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://roma.repubblica.it/multimedia/home/3687367/21 | newspaper = [[La Repubblica]] | language = Italian| accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Piazza di Spagna, il concerto a sorpresa della Pausini | date = 14 November 2008}}</ref>\nThe album also features the single [[Primavera in anticipo (It Is My Song)|\"Primavera in anticipo (It Is My Song)\" / Primavera anticipada (It Is My Song)\"]], a duet with British singer-songwriter [[James Blunt]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.amazon.com/dp/B001KQG4WQ | publisher = www.amazon.com | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Primavera anticipada (Spanish Version)}}</ref> Also in late 2008, French chansonnier [[Charles Aznavour]] and Pausini recorded Aznavour's 1965 song \"Paris au mois d'ao\u00fbt\" for Aznavour's ''Duos'' album, both in French as well as the Italian version \"Parigi in agosto\". Pausini grew up listening to Aznavour's songs, and in a January 2009 interview on France 2's Vivement Dimanche hosted by [[Michel Drucker]], Aznavour said of Pausini, seated by his side after a live duet performance of \"Paris au mois d'ao\u00fbt,\" that \"she knows the lyrics [to my songs] better than me.\"<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wmU1RSrtjcE | publisher = [[France 2]] | language = French| accessdate = 16 March 2014 | title = Laura PAUSINI & Charles AZNAVOUR Vivement Dimanche France 2 (18-01-2009) Paris au mois d'Ao\u00fbt | date = 18 January 2009}}</ref> In November 2009 ''Primavera in anticipo'' went on to win Best Female Pop Vocal Album at the [[Latin Grammy Awards of 2009|Latin Grammy Awards]].<ref name=\"LatinGrammy2009\">{{cite web | url = http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/1263237/juan-gabriel-steals-show-calle-13-sweep-latin-grammys | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate =29 July 2011 | title = Juan Gabriel Steals Show, Calle 13 Sweep Latin Grammys | date = 5 November 2009 | author = Leila Cobo}}</ref> In 2010 Pausini also won the [[Premio Lo Nuestro 2010|Lo Nuestro Award]] for Female Artist of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.univision.com/content/content.jhtml?chid=10383&schid=10646&secid=10649&cid=1794888 |publisher=www.univision.com |accessdate=30 July 2011 |title=Premio Lo Nuestro \u2013 Premiados POP \u2013 Ganadores de Premio Lo Nuestro 2010 |language=Spanish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714060805/http://www.univision.com/content/content.jhtml?chid=10383&schid=10646&secid=10649&cid=1794888 |archivedate=14 July 2011 }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Laura Pausini 2009.04.30 025.jpg|thumb|Pausini performing during the World Tour 2009]]\nOn 21 June 2009, Pausini organized a mega-concert in the [[San Siro Stadium]] in Milan, raising money to support the victims of the [[2009 L'Aquila earthquake]]. The concert, named ''Amiche per l'Abruzzo'', involved 43 Italian female singers<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.repubblica.it/2009/05/sezioni/spettacoli_e_cultura/musica-per-abruzzo/concerto-san-siro/concerto-san-siro.html | work = [[La Repubblica]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Voci di donne, festa a San Siro. 57mila dalle 'Amiche per l'Abruzzo' | author = Luigi Bolognini | date = 22 June 2009}}</ref> and was later released on a DVD, which sold 250,000 copies in Italy.<ref name=\"AXA\">{{cite web | url = http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo504983.shtml | publisher = [[Mediaset]] | work = [[TGCOM]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Amiche per l'Abruzzo con le donne | date = 7 March 2011 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110508113313/http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo504983.shtml | archive-date = 8 May 2011 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\nIn the meanwhile, on 5 March 2009, Pausini began her [[World Tour 2009]] in [[Turin]],<ref name=\"WorldTour09\">{{cite web | url = http://www.musicalnews.com/articolo.php?codice=14725&sz=6 | publisher = Musicalnews.com | author = Laura Gorini | title = Boom per il Laura Pausini World Tour. Triplicano le date di Roma e Milano e raddoppiano quelle di Torino, Caserta e Treviso | date = 16 January 2009 | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111001200230/http://www.musicalnews.com/articolo.php?codice=14725&sz=6 | archive-date = 1 October 2011 | url-status = dead }}</ref> which reached Europe in May 2009<ref name=\"WorldTour09\"/> and then South America and the United States in autumn 2009.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/1269207/laura-pausini-takes-tour-to-the-americas | work = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini Takes Tour to the Americas | author = Leila Cobo | date = 17 June 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Laura Pausini: dopo il trionfo in America arriva il nuovo CD |url=http://www.sorrisi.com/2009/10/16/laura-pausini-dopo-il-trionfo-in-america-arriva-il-nuovo-cd/ |work=Sorrisi & Canzoni TV |language=Italian |accessdate=30 July 2011 |date=16 October 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005012855/http://www.sorrisi.com/2009/10/16/laura-pausini-dopo-il-trionfo-in-america-arriva-il-nuovo-cd/ |archivedate=5 October 2011 }}</ref> The last leg of the tour took place in Italy in November 2009.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo463140.shtml | publisher = [[TGCOM]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini regina d'America | date = 15 October 2009 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100224041732/http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo463140.shtml | archive-date = 24 February 2010 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\nA CD of the tour, along with a DVD, was released on 27 November 2009 with the title [[Laura Live World Tour 09|''Laura Live World Tour 09'' / ''Laura Live Gira Mundial 09'']].<ref name=\"LauraLive\">{{cite web | url = http://rockol.it/news-104319/Laura-Pausini,-Laura-Live--E-ci%C3%B2-che-pi%C3%B9-mi-rappresenta.-E-ora-mi-fermo... | publisher = Rockol.it | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini, 'Laura Live': 'E' ci\u00f2 che pi\u00f9 mi rappresenta. E ora mi fermo...' | date = 23 November 2009 | language = Italian}}</ref> The album also includes three new song, the singles [[Con la musica alla radio|\"Con la musica alla radio\" / \"Con la musica en la radio\"]], \"Non sono lei\" / \"Ella no soy\" and \"Casomai\" / \"Menos mal\".<ref name=\"LauraLive\"/>\n\n===2011\u20132012: ''Inedito'' and the Inedito World Tour===\n[[File:Laura Pausini 11 - Bercy - Avril 2012 (7076256823).jpg|thumb|left|170px|Laura Pausini performing in [[Bercy]], in April 2012, during the [[Inedito World Tour]]]]\nOn 30 December 2010, Pausini announced her new studio album,<ref name=\"EleventhStudioAlbum\">{{cite web | url = http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo499488.shtml | publisher = [[Mediaset]] | work = [[TGCOM]] | language = Italian | accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Il grande ritorno di Laura Pausini | date = 30 December 2010}}</ref> [[Inedito|''Inedito'' / ''In\u00e9dito'']], released both in Italian and Spanish on 11 November 2011.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo502819.shtml | publisher = [[TGCOM]] | title = Laura, la regina del pop \u00e8 tornata | date = 10 February 2011 | language = Italian | access-date = 30 July 2011 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110317001011/http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo502819.shtml | archive-date = 17 March 2011 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\nThe title and the track list of the album were announced through Pausini's website on 10 September 2011. The first single from the album, [[Benvenuto (song)|\"Benvenuto\" / \"Bienvenido\"]], was released on 12 September 2011.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.mtv.it/news/news-detail.asp?idnews=31568 | publisher = [[MTV Italy]]| language = Italian | accessdate =12 August 2011 | title = Laura Pausini: Benvenuto | date = 11 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://musica.univision.com/noticias/article/2011-08-11/laura-pausini-nuevo-sencillo-bienvenido | publisher = [[Univision]] | language = Spanish | accessdate =12 August 2011 | title = 'Bienvenido' lo nuevo de Laura Pausini | date = 11 August 2011}}</ref>\nIn order to promote the album, Pausini engaged the [[Inedito World Tour]], starting with 11 shows in Italy in late December 2011.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo504403.shtml | publisher = [[TGCOM]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Pausini, 11 live tra Roma e Milano | date = 28 February 2011 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110302051015/http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/articolo504403.shtml | archive-date = 2 March 2011 | url-status = dead }}</ref> The tour reached Latin America in January and February 2012.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.fepgroup.it/news/laura-pausini/ecco-la-prima-parte-del-latin-american-tour-2012 | publisher = www.fepgroup.it | language = Italian | accessdate = 30 July 2011 | title = Ecco la prima parte del Latin American Tour 2012! | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20111030054551/http://www.fepgroup.it/news/laura-pausini/ecco-la-prima-parte-del-latin-american-tour-2012 | archivedate = 30 October 2011 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> The European leg of her tour visited the principle arenas of France, [[Switzerland]], Spain, Germany, [[Belgium]] and the [[Netherlands]], and concluded at the [[Royal Albert Hall]] in London.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://musica.excite.it/laura-pausini-tour-europeo-2011-tutte-le-N70779.html | publisher = musica.excite.it | language = Italian|  accessdate =30 July 2011 | title = Laura Pausini, le date del tour europeo | date = 11 April 2011}}</ref>\n[[File:Laura Pausini Inedito World Tour.jpg|thumb|170px|Pausini on 22 December 2011, performing in [[Milan]]]]\nThe album also spawned the singles \"[[Non ho mai smesso]]\"<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.rockol.it/news-310559/Laura-Pausini-torna-con--Inedito----Non-riuscivo-a-stare-lontana-dalla-musica- | publisher = Rockol.it | language = Italian | accessdate =8 February 2012 | title = Laura Pausini torna con Inedito: Non riuscivo a stare lontana dalla musica | date = 10 November 2012}}</ref> / \"Jam\u00e1s abandon\u00e9\",<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/notas/822150.html | work = [[El Universal (Mexico City)|El Universal]] | language = Spanish | accessdate =8 February 2012 | title = Pausini retomar\u00e1 su gira mundial en Brasil | date = 12 January 2012}}</ref> \"[[Bastava]]\" / \"Bastaba\",<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ansa.it/web/notizie/rubriche/cultura/2012/01/18/visualizza_new.html_46170740.html | publisher = [[Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata]] | language = Italian | accessdate =8 February 2012 | title = Pausini, arriva nuovo singolo Bastava | date = 18 January 2012}}</ref> \"[[Mi tengo]]\", \"[[Le cose che non-mi aspetto]]\" / \"Las cosas que no me espero\" and \"[[Celeste (song)|Celeste]]\". The song \"[[Troppo tempo]]\" was originally chosen as the sixth and last single of the album, but when Pausini discovered her pregnancy she changed her mind to \"Celeste\".\nThe album has sold 1,000,000 copies worldwide.<ref name=Inedito>{{cite web|url=http://www.irispress.it/211927/musica-laura-pausini-da-venerdi-il-nuovo-singolo-le-nuove-date-del-tour |publisher=irispress.it |language=Italian |accessdate=19 January 2014 |archivedate=2 December 2013 |title=MUSICA, LAURA PAUSINI: DA VENERD\u00cc IL NUOVO SINGOLO. LE NUOVE DATE DEL TOUR |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202223944/http://www.irispress.it/211927/musica-laura-pausini-da-venerdi-il-nuovo-singolo-le-nuove-date-del-tour |df=dmy }}</ref>\nOn 25 June 2012, Pausini took part in the mega-concert Concerto per l'Emilia, organized to raise funds in support of the people affected by the [[2012 Northern Italy earthquakes]]. During the show, Pausini duetted with [[Cesare Cremonini (singer-songwriter)|Cesare Cremonini]], performing a cover of [[Lucio Dalla]]'s \"L'anno che verr\u00e0\".<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.unita.it/culture/liga-nomadi-guccini-ecco-br-il-concerto-per-l-emilia-1.424130 | work = [[L'Unit\u00e0]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 26 January 2012 | title = I big della musica per l'Emilia. Liga: Niente alibi per lo Stato | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120629045614/http://www.unita.it/culture/liga-nomadi-guccini-ecco-br-il-concerto-per-l-emilia-1.424130 | archivedate = 29 June 2012 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn 27 November 2012, a special edition of ''Inedito'', in both Italian and Spanish, was released, featuring a live DVD recorded during the 2012 Inedito World Tour.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.donna10.it/laura-pausini-inedito-world-tour-2012-26460.html. | work = Donna.It | language = Italian | accessdate = 7 September 2012 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 Inedito World Tour}}</ref> The Italian-language version and the Spanish-language version of the DVD were recorded in [[Bologna]] on 17 April 2012 and in [[Madrid]] on 20 April 2012, respectively. The CD included in the new edition of ''Inedito'' also features a live medley performed by Pausini on New Year's Eve 2012, as well as a duet with Venezuelan singer [[Carlos Baute]] on the track \"[[Le cose che non mi aspetto|Las cosas que no me espero]]\", released as a single in Spain and the Americas.\n\nIn 2012 Pausini also recorded an Italian-language duet with [[Josh Groban]], \"E ti prometter\u00f2\", included in his album ''[[All That Echoes]]'', released in February 2013.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.radioitalia.it/news/nuova_uscita/5216_%22e_ti_prometter%C3%B2%22%3A_laura_pausini_duetta_con_josh_groban.php | work = Radio Italia | language = Italian | accessdate = 10 January 2013 | title = E ti prometter\u00f2: Laura Pausini duetta con Josh Groban | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130111092147/http://www.radioitalia.it/news/nuova_uscita/5216_%22e_ti_prometter%C3%B2%22%3A_laura_pausini_duetta_con_josh_groban.php | archivedate = 11 January 2013 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===2013\u20132014: ''20 \u2013 The Greatest Hits'' and World Tour===\nOn 26 February 2013, in order to celebrate the twentieth anniversary of her career, Pausini released a medley including the original versions in Italian, Spanish and English of the song which launched her career in 1993, \"[[La solitudine]]\". The track was launched as a limited-edition digital single, available for purchase for a week only.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockol.it/news-466116/Laura-Pausini,-edizione-speciale-di-'La-solitudine'-per-i-vent'anni-di-carriera |publisher=Rockol.it |language=Italian |accessdate=7 September 2013 |title=Laura Pausini, edizione speciale di 'La solitudine' per i vent'anni di carriera |date=1 February 2013 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130907200854/http://www.rockol.it/news-466116/laura-pausini-edizione-speciale-di-la-solitudine-per-i-vent-anni-di-carriera |archivedate= 7 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> \nOn 1 June 2013 Pausini took part in the [[Gucci#Chime For Change|Chime for Change]] concert at [[Twickenham Stadium]] in London, supporting the global campaign of the same name for girls' and women's empowerment. Pausini performed the songs \"[[Io canto (song)|Io canto]]\" and \"[[In assenza di te|It's Not Goodbye]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/musica/2013/06/01/news/the_sound_of_change-60160777/ |work=[[la Repubblica]] |language=Italian |accessdate=7 September 2013 |title=Londra, 50mila persone e tante star per dire no alla violenza sulle donne |author=Giuseppe Videtti |archivedate= 7 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130907201944/http://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/musica/2013/06/01/news/the_sound_of_change-60160777/ |date=1 June 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\nDuring the same year, she appeared as a featured artist on the track \"[[Smile (Charlie Chaplin song)|Sonr\u00ede (Smile)]]\", included in American singer [[Gloria Estefan]]'s album ''[[The Standards]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2013-05-22/elsentinel/fl-es-gloria-estefan-standards-20130522_1_la-venta-el-gloria-estefan-el-sentinel |work=[[Sun-Sentinel]] |accessdate=1 June 2013 |archivedate= 1 June 2013 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130601193847/http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2013-05-22/elsentinel/fl-es-gloria-estefan-standards-20130522_1_la-venta-el-gloria-estefan-el-sentinel |title=Gloria Estefan canta 'The Standards' con sabor latino |date=22 May 2013 |author=Deborah Ram\u00edrez |language=Spanish |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\nIn November 2013, Pausini also released a greatest hits album, titled ''[[20 \u2013 The Greatest Hits (Laura Pausini album)|20 - The Greatest Hits]]'' in Italian and ''20 \u2013 Grandes \u00e9xitos'' in Spanish.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sorrisi.com/2013/05/21/laura-pausini-il-ritorno-dopo-la-maternita-una-serata-di-beneficenza-con-beyonce-un-album/ |work=[[TV Sorrisi e Canzoni]] |language=Italian |accessdate=21 May 2013 |title=Laura Pausini, il ritorno dopo la maternit\u00e0: una serata con Beyonc\u00e9 e un album |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413215242/http://www.sorrisi.com/2013/05/21/laura-pausini-il-ritorno-dopo-la-maternita-una-serata-di-beneficenza-con-beyonce-un-album/ |archivedate=13 April 2014 }}</ref>  The album was preceded by the single \"[[Limpido]]\"\u2014\"Limpio\" in Spanish\u2014recorded with Australian singer [[Kylie Minogue]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.mtv.it/musica/laura-pausini-duetta-con-kylie-minogue-in-limpido/|publisher=[[MTV News]]|language=Italian|accessdate=1 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131114081437/http://news.mtv.it/musica/laura-pausini-duetta-con-kylie-minogue-in-limpido/|archivedate=14 November 2013 |date=10 September 2013|title=Laura Pausini duetta con Kylie Minogue in Limpido}}</ref>\nOther singles from the album include the new tracks \"[[Se non te]]\" and \"Dove resto solo io\", released for the Italian market, and the revamped versions of \"[[Vivimi|V\u00edveme]]\" and \"[[Non c'\u00e8|Se fue]]\", featuring [[Alejandro Sanz]] and [[Marc Anthony]], respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockol.it/news-549347/se-non-te-e-il-nuovo-singolo-della-pausini|publisher=Rockol.it|language=Italian|accessdate=1 January 2015|title=Laura Pausini: si intitola 'Se non te' il nuovo singolo inedito|date=3 November 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141107172450/http://www.rockol.it/news-549347/se-non-te-e-il-nuovo-singolo-della-pausini|archivedate=7 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panorama.it/musica/laura-pausini-dove-resto-solo-io-virginio-simonelli/|work=[[Panorama (magazine)|Panorama]]|accessdate=1 January 2015|title=Laura Pausini: Dove resto solo io raccontato dall'autore Virginio Simonelli|date=24 January 2014|author=Alessandro Alicandri}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://elespecial.com/news/2013/dec/12/laura-pausini-dueto-con-ale-sanz/ |publisher=ElEspecial.com |language=Spanish |accessdate=26 December 2013 |date=12 December 2013 |archivedate=26 December 2013 |title=Laura Pausini a dueto con Ale Sanz |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20131226150257/http://elespecial.com/news/2013/dec/12/laura-pausini-dueto-con-ale-sanz/ |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/cultura/musica/2014/04/28/laura-pausini-nuovo-singolo-se-fue_0fe1cc39-fe59-441c-a3ed-8fd9b87fdd8e.html|publisher=[[Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata]]|language=Italian|title=Laura Pausini, nuovo singolo Se Fue|date=28 April 2014|accessdate=28 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429140827/http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/cultura/musica/2014/04/28/laura-pausini-nuovo-singolo-se-fue_0fe1cc39-fe59-441c-a3ed-8fd9b87fdd8e.html|archivedate=29 April 2014}}</ref>\n\nStarting from December 2013, Pausini promoted her greatest hits album through [[The Greatest Hits World Tour]], giving concerts in her native Italy, as well as in other [[European countries]], in Latin America, in the United States and in Canada. The tour also included performances during the [[Vi\u00f1a del Mar International Song Festival]] in Chile and the Feria del Hogar in Peru.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laurapausini.com/eng/tour |publisher=Laurapausini.com |title=Laura Pausini \u2013 The Greatest Hits World Tour |archivedate= 7 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130907202716/http://www.laurapausini.com/eng/tour |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.larepublica.pe/05-07-2014/laura-pausini-invito-a-sus-fanaticos-a-la-feria-del-hogar-2014-video|publisher=LaRepublica.pe|title=Laura Pausini invit\u00f3 a sus fan\u00e1ticos a la Feria del Hogar 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140724083439/http://www.larepublica.pe/05-07-2014/laura-pausini-invito-a-sus-fanaticos-a-la-feria-del-hogar-2014-video|archivedate=24 July 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The concert she gave in [[Taormina]], featuring several guests, was conceived as the first Italian \"one woman show\", and it was broadcast by [[Rai Uno]] in May 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lastampa.it/2014/05/20/spettacoli/musica/pausini-stasera-in-tv-uno-show-tutto-mio-un-sogno-che-savvera-6fUAFs7sz7HY8XDK6PAL0L/pagina.html|work=[[La Stampa]]|language=Italian|date=20 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140524063315/http://www.lastampa.it/2014/05/20/spettacoli/musica/pausini-stasera-in-tv-uno-show-tutto-mio-un-sogno-che-savvera-6fUAFs7sz7HY8XDK6PAL0L/pagina.html|archivedate=24 May 2014|accessdate=2 January 2015|title=Pausini stasera in tv \u00c8 uno show tutto mio un sogno che s\u2019avvera|author=Luca Dondoni}}</ref>\nA new version of the album was released in November 2014 for the hispanophone market. The new edition includes a duet with [[Thal\u00eda]] in \"[[Se non te|Sino a ti]]\", a new version of \"[[Tra te e il mare (song)|Entre tu y mil mares]]\", featuring [[Melendi]], and a re-recording of \"[[Dove resto solo io|Donde quedo solo yo]]\", performed with [[Alex Ubago]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cadenadial.com/2014/laura-pausini-35580.html|publisher= [[Cadena Dial]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=2 January 2015|title=Laura Pausini a d\u00fao con Melendi, Thalia y Alex Ubago|date=17 November 2014|author=Nuria Serena|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102125746/http://www.cadenadial.com/2014/laura-pausini-35580.html|archivedate=2 January 2015}}</ref> The latter was also recorded under the title \"Jo sempre hi ser\u00e9\", becoming Pausini's first [[Catalan language|Catalan]] song. This version was included in ''El disc de La Marat\u00f3 2014'', a compilation album related to the [[telethon]] organized by Catalan channel [[TV3 (Catalonia)|TV3]], with the purpose to raise money against [[cardiovascular diseases]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pernodirres.cat/2014/11/el-disc-de-la-marato-2014.html|publisher=Per no dir res|language=Catalan|accessdate=2 January 2015|title=El disc de La Marat\u00f3 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102131455/http://www.pernodirres.cat/2014/11/el-disc-de-la-marato-2014.html|archivedate=2 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elpuntavui.cat/noticia/article/5-cultura/19-cultura/795253-musica-per-al-cor-i-del-cor.html|work=[[El Punt Avui]]|language=Catalan|accessdate=2 January 2015|archivedate=2 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102131414/http://www.elpuntavui.cat/noticia/article/5-cultura/19-cultura/795253-musica-per-al-cor-i-del-cor.html|title=M\u00fasica per al cor i del cor|date=14 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 November 2014, Pausini was the first artist to be inducted in the newly created Paseo de las Estrellas in [[Tijuana, Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.el-mexicano.com.mx/informacion/noticias/1/3/estatal/2014/11/12/803169/confirman-inauguracion-de-paseo-de-la-fama-en-tijuana|work=El Mexicano|language=Spanish|date=12 November 2014|title=Confirman inauguraci\u00f3n de Paseo de la Fama en Tijuana|author=Ad\u00e1n Mondrag\u00f3n}}</ref>\nIn Autumn 2014, Pausini was one of the four coaches of the fourth season of the [[Mexico|Mexican]] reality show and singing competition ''[[La Voz... M\u00e9xico|La Voz]]''.<ref name=\"La Voz Mexico\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/televisione/2014/notizia/laura-pausini-sara-coach-a-la-voz-mexico-_2058857.shtml|publisher=[[Mediaset]]|work=[[TGCOM]]|language=Italian|title=Laura Pausini sar\u00e0 coach a La voz... M\u00e9xico|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141020081108/http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/televisione/2014/notizia/laura-pausini-sara-coach-a-la-voz-mexico-_2058857.shtml|archivedate=20 October 2014}}</ref> Pausini also served as a coach for the third series of the Spanish version of the competition, ''[[La Voz (Spanish TV series)|La Voz]]'', which debuted on [[Telecinco]] in January 2015.<ref name=\"La Voz Spain\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lastampa.it/2014/12/30/spettacoli/musica/laura-pausini-far-the-voice-ma-in-spagna-urNaqZRuHVCf1sFHWP4tQI/pagina.html|work=[[La Stampa]]|language=Italian|date=30 December 2014|title=Laura Pausini: Far\u00f2 The Voice ma in Spagna|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150101214019/http://www.lastampa.it/2014/12/30/spettacoli/musica/laura-pausini-far-the-voice-ma-in-spagna-urNaqZRuHVCf1sFHWP4tQI/pagina.html|archivedate=1 January 2015}}</ref>\nDuring the same year, she continued her tour, which reached Australia and Russia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxmusica.it/artisti/pausini-2015-la-vox-spagna-e-tour-australia-e-russia/|publisher=Boxmusica.it|language=Italian|accessdate=2 January 2015|title=Pausini 2015: La Vox Spagna e tour in Australia e Russia!|date=31 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102133242/http://www.boxmusica.it/artisti/pausini-2015-la-vox-spagna-e-tour-australia-e-russia/|archivedate=2 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===2015\u20132016: ''Simili'', TV shows and ''Laura Xmas''===\n[[File:Laura Pausini live @ Rio de Janeiro, 14 Sep 2016.jpg|thumb|left|Pausini during a show of the Latin American leg of the ''Simili'' World Tour, September 2016]]\nAt the [[Premio Lo Nuestro 2015|27th Lo Nuestro Awards]], Pausini received a special award in recognition of her music career trajectory.<ref name=\"lonuestro-winners\">{{cite news|url=http://musica.terra.com.mx/lista-completa-de-ganadores-de-premio-lo-nuestro-2015,b4fd66a7135ab410VgnVCM4000009bcceb0aRCRD.html|title=Lista completa de ganadores de Premio Lo Nuestro 2015|work=[[Terra Networks]]|publisher=[[Telef\u00f3nica]]|date=20 February 2015|accessdate= 11 March 2015}}</ref> After performing a medley of songs including the salsa version of \"[[Non c'\u00e8|Se fu\u00e9]]\" with [[Marc Anthony]], she stated that although she is Italian, \"half of my heart beats Latino\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Romeo Santos, el gran ganador de Premios Lo Nuestro 2015|url=http://elespecial.com/news/2015/feb/21/romeo-santos-el-gran-ganador-de-premios-lo-nuestro/?page=2|accessdate=10 October 2015|work=El Especial|date=21 February 2015}}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, Pausini co-wrote the song \"Como yo sabr\u00eda\", with fellow Italian singer-songwriter [[Virginio Simonelli]]. The song was recorded by Maverick Lopes, a runner-up in the third season of ''[[La Voz (Spanish TV series)|La Voz Spain]]'', mentored by Pausini herself during the competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.optimaitalia.com/blog/2015/08/07/laura-pausini-e-virginio-simonelli-scrivono-per-maverick-lopez-di-the-voice/215744|publisher=OptimaItalia.it|language=Italian|accessdate=7 September 2015|title=Laura Pausini e Virginio Simonelli scrivono per Maverick Lopez di The Voice|date=7 August 2015}}</ref>\nIn September of the same year, Pausini, together with singers [[Alejandro Sanz]] and [[Ricky Martin]], was a judge in the [[Univision]] talent show ''[[La Banda (TV series)|La banda]]'', created by [[Simon Cowell]].<ref name=\"La Banda\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/6554100/alejandro-sanz-la-banda|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=14 May 2015|title=Alejandro Sanz Joins 'La Banda' as Judge|date=6 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nPausini's eleventh studio album, ''[[Simili (album)|Simili]]'', was released on 6 November 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sorrisi.com/musica/dischi-in-uscita/laura-pausini-presenta-simili-tutto-sul-nuovo-album/|work=[[TV Sorrisi e Canzoni]]|language=Italian|accessdate=6 October 2017|title=Laura Pausini presenta Simili: tutto sul nuovo album e la video intervista|author=Alessandro Alicandri|date=4 November 2015}}</ref> The first single from the album, \"Lato destro del cuore\"\u2014\"Lado derecho del coraz\u00f3n\" in Spanish\u2014was written by [[Biagio Antonacci]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockol.it/news-646873/laura-pausini-nuovo-singolo-lato-destro-del-cuore-scritto-antonacci|publisher=Rockol.it|language=Italian|accessdate=6 October 2017|title=Laura Pausini, Biagio Antonacci firma il singolo Lato destro del cuore|date=24 September 2015}}</ref>\nThe album's title-track, after being released as its second single, was chosen as the opening song of the third season of Italian TV series ''[[Braccialetti rossi]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusicitalia.it/news/simili-di-laura-pausini-sara-la-sigla-della-terza-stagione-di-braccialetti-rossi.html|publisher=AllMusicItalia.it|language=Italian|accessdate=6 October 2017|title=Simili di Laura Pausini aar\u00e0 la sigla della terza stagione di Braccialetti rossi|date=7 November 2017}}</ref> The album also spawned the singles \"En la puerta de al lado\", \"Innamorata\" / \"Enamorada\", \"Ho creduto a me\" / \"He cre\u00eddo en mi\" and \"200 note\". \nThe Spanish-language version of the album, ''Similares'', received a nomination for a [[Grammy Award for Best Latin Pop Album]].<ref name=\"Grammy2017\">{{cite news|title=Here Is the Complete List of Nominees for the 2017 Grammys|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7597556/grammys-nominees-complete-list-2017|accessdate=December 8, 2016|date=December 6, 2016|last=Unterberger|first=Andrew|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2016, Pausini hosted with [[Paola Cortellesi]] the [[variety show]] ''Laura e Paola'', broadcast in Italy by [[Rai 1]]. The show included three episodes.<ref name=\"Laura e Paola\">{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/tv-radio/2016/03/30/news/pausini_cortellesi-136558436/|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=Italian|accessdate=4 April 2016|title=Laura e Paola, strana coppia e gran variet\u00e0: la televisione \u00e8 roba da donne|date=30 April 2016|author=Silvia Fumarola}}</ref> Thanks to the show, Pausini received an award at the Premio TV 2016 as TV Personality Revelation of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/spettacoli/premio-tv-2016-chi-sono-i-vincitori-questanno-1274009.html|work=[[Il Giornale]]|language=Italian|accessdate=6 October 2017|title=Premio Tv 2016: chi sono i vincitori quest'anno|author=Elisabetta Esposito|date=20 June 2016}}</ref> In June 2016, Pausini became the first Italian female artist to perform a tour in Italian stadiums. Her [[Pausini Stadi Tour 2016]] included concerts at the [[San Siro Stadium]] in Milan, at the [[Stadio Olimpico]] in Rome, and at the [[Stadio della Vittoria]] in Bari. The second and third legs of the tour consisted of shows in Latin America and Europe, respectively, and concluded in October 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/people/2016/06/05/foto/_pausinistadi_parte_da_san_siro_il_concerto_contro_la_violenza_sulle_donne-141312228/1/#1|work=[[la Repubblica]]|date=5 June 2016|title=#Pausinistadi parte da San Siro, il concerto contro la violenza sulle donne|accessdate=1 October 2017}}</ref>\nIn late 2016, Pausini was also confirmed as a judge on the second series of ''La banda''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7617743/mix5-la-banda-second-season-winners|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|language=Italian|accessdate=7 October 2017|title=Meet MIX5: 'La Banda' Wraps Second Season With New Band|author=Griselda Flores|date=12 December 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 November 2016, Pausini released her first Christmas album, ''[[Laura Xmas]]'', titled ''Laura Navidad'' in its Spanish version. The album, produced by [[Patrick Williams (composer)|Patrick Williams]] and recorded with his orchestra, was launched with a performance at [[Disneyland Paris]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/spettacolo/per-laura-pausini-e-gia-natale-svelata-copertina-nuovo-album-laura-xmas-_3030179-201602a.shtml|publisher=Mediaset.it|language=Italian|accessdate=8 September 2016|title=Per Laura Pausini \u00e8 gi\u00e0... Natale: svelata copertina nuovo album \"Laura Xmas\"|date=8 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adnkronos.com/intrattenimento/spettacolo/2016/11/25/laura-pausini-regina-natale-disneyland-paris-video_oq85lNEyrpTO57ba0844mL.html|publisher=[[Adnkronos]]|language=Italian|title=Laura Pausini regina del Natale a Disneyland Paris|date=25 November 2016|accessdate=6 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u2013present: ''Fatti sentire''===\nIn Autumn 2017, Pausini returned as a coach on the sixth series of ''La Voz... M\u00e9xico''.<ref name=\"La Voz Mexico 6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/televisione/laura-pausini-di-nuovo-giudice-di-la-voz-mexico-e-il-17-settembre-grande-party-a-rimini_3091110-201702a.shtml|work=[[TGCOM]]|language=Italian|publisher=[[Mediaset]]|title=Laura Pausini di nuovo giudice di La Voz Mexico e il 17 settembre grande party a Rimini|date=27 August 2017|accessdate=6 October 2017}}</ref> \nHer new studio album, ''Fatti sentire'', will be released on 16 March 2018, both in its Italian-language version and in its Spanish-language counterpart, titled ''Hazte sentir''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.it/musica/pop/laura-pausini-il-disco-fatti-sentire-esce-il-16-marzo/2018/01/243233/|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|language=Italian|accessdate=26 February 2018|title=Laura Pausini: il disco Fatti Sentire esce il 16 marzo|date=24 January 2018}}</ref> The lead single \"Non \u00e8 detto\"\u2014\"Nadie ha dicho\" in Spanish\u2014was released on 16 January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.it/musica/pop/laura-pausini-non-e-detto/2018/01/102727/|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|language=Italian|title=Laura Pausini: il nuovo singolo \u00e8 Non \u00e8 Detto|author=Giovanni Ferrari|date=10 January 2018}}</ref> The single was performed during the final night of the [[Sanremo Music Festival 2018|68th Sanremo Music Festival]], where Pausini appeared as a special guest.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.it/show/tv/2018/02/10/festival-sanremo-2018-laura-pausini-ospite|work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|language=Italian|accessdate=26 February 2018|date=10 February 2018|title=Sanremo 2018: il grande show di Laura Pausini (dentro e fuori l'Ariston)|author=Raffaella Serini}}</ref> \"Nadie ha dicho\" premiered in the United States with a performance during the [[Lo Nuestro Awards]] gala on 22 February 2018, which were co-hosted by Pausini herself.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8214820/premio-lo-nuestro-2018-top-performances|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=26 February 2018|title=Premio Lo Nuestro 2018: Daddy Yankee, Pitbull, J Balvin & Other Top Performances|date=22 February 2018|author=Marjua Estevez}}</ref><ref name=\"Lo Nuestro 2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/veronicavillafane/2018/02/15/univisions-star-studded-30th-premio-lo-nuestro-honors-latino-musical-legends/2/#|title=Pitbull, Daddy Yankee Join Univision's 30th 'Premio Lo Nuestro' Honoring Latino Music Legends|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=26 February 2018|author=Veronica Villafa\u00f1e|date=15 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn Spring 2018, Laura Pausini also appeared as a judge on the third series of Spanish talent show ''[[Factor X (Spanish TV series)|Factor X]]'',<ref name=\"Factor X\">{{cite web|url=http://www.elmundo.es/television/2017/12/19/5a3953e4ca4741d70a8b459f.html|work=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=26 February 2018|title=Laura Pausini y Risto Mejide, juntos en Factor X|author=Surien Gasparyan|date=19 December 2018}}</ref> which was won by Pol Granch, one of the contestants she mentored as part of the Boys category.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pol Granch, ganador contra todo pron\u00f3stico de \u2018Factor X Espa\u00f1a\u2019|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/television/20180706/45708199487/factor-x-final-ganador-pol-granch-laura-pausini.html |website=La Vanguardia |accessdate=6 July 2018 |language=Spanish |date=6 July 2018}}</ref> To promote ''Fatti sentire'', she will embark on a worldwide tour, starting with two concerts at the [[Circus Maximus]] in [[Rome]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.corriere.it/spettacoli/18_gennaio_15/laura-pausini-annuncia-fatti-sentire-nuovo-album-instagram-cd01c458-fa12-11e7-b7a0-515b75eef21a.shtml |title=Laura Pausini annuncia \"Fatti sentire\", il nuovo album, su Instagram |work=[[Corriere della sera]] |language=Italian |date=15 January 2018 |accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Artistry==\nLaura Pausini is described as a [[mezzo-soprano]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hardrocklivehollywoodfl.com/release-176.html |title=International Singing Sensation Laura Pausini Launches North American Tour at Hard Rock Live on October 14 |publisher=Hardrocklivehollywoodfl.com |accessdate=1 September 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318050752/http://www.hardrocklivehollywoodfl.com/release-176.html |archivedate=18 March 2012 |url-status=bot: unknown |df=dmy }}</ref> with a classic and powerful voice.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1060103 | title = Secondo De Andr\u00e8, terze Casale-Di Michele, la Pausini vince tra i giovani. Il pubblico contesta. Il rock di Ruggeri val pi\u00f9 di una preghiera. Zero sconfitto, rovesciati i pronostici | work = [[La Stampa]] | language = Italian | author = Marinella Venegoni | accessdate = 13 August 2011 | date = 28 February 1993 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120328215454/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1060103 | archivedate = 28 March 2012 | df = dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2005/06/30/la-regina-della-canzone-amore.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | title = La regina della canzone d'amore | author = Giusy La Piana | date = 30 June 2005}}</ref> Due to her voice, Pausini has been compared by music critics to various female artists, including [[Milva]],<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1060485 | work = [[La Stampa]] | author = Curzio Maltese | date = 1 March 2003 | title = IL DIARIO Sanremo da serie B meglio voltar pagina | language = Italian | accessdate = 13 August 2011 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120328215502/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1060485 | archivedate = 28 March 2012 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> [[Celine Dion]],<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/from-the-inside-r612348 | work = [[AllMusic]] | accessdate =13 August 2011 | author = Christina Fuoco | title = From the Inside \u2013 Laura Pausini}}</ref><ref name=\"MusicaedischiFTI\"/> [[Mariah Carey]]<ref name=\"MusicaedischiFTI\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicaedischi.it/recensioni.php?genere=0&id=1056 |work=[[Musica e dischi]] |language=Italian |accessdate=1 September 2012 |title=Laura Pausini \u2013 From the Inside \u2013 Recensione |author=Antonio Orlando |date=February 2003 |archivedate= 1 September 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120901194725/http://www.musicaedischi.it/recensioni.php?genere=0&id=1056 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and [[Barbra Streisand]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elpais.com/articulo/madrid/MADRID/MADRID_/MUNICIPIO/Lluis/Llach/presenta/durante/noches/nuevo/disco/Centro/Cultural/Villa/elpepiespmad/19990405elpmad_19/Tes?print=1 |title=Llu\u00eds Llach presenta durante cinco noches su nuevo disco en el Centro Cultural de la Villa |language=Spanish |accessdate=1 September 2012 |work=[[El Pa\u00eds]] |author=F. \u00cd\u00f1iguez |date=5 April 1999 |archivedate= 20 October 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020221138/http://elpais.com/diario/1999/04/05/madrid/923311472_850215.html |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\nAt the beginning of her career, she was considered by music critics as a [[teen idol]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1994/maggio/28/Laura_milione_fans_co_0_940528053.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]]| language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011 | title = Laura, un milione di fans | date = 28 May 1994 | author = Elia Perboni}}</ref> mainly singing about adolescent love affairs and problems.<ref name=\"Corriere15121998\">{{cite web| url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1998/ottobre/15/Pausini_canta_versi_Madre_Teresa_co_0_9810153755.shtml | title = La Pausini canta i versi di Madre Teresa | author = Mario Luzzatto Fegiz | date = 15 October 2008 | language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1994/maggio/31/Laura_cosi_elementare_cosi_disarmante_co_0_9405319728.shtml | title = Laura, cos\u00ec elementare cos\u00ec disarmante | language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011 | date = 31 May 1994 | author = Mario Luzzatto Fegiz}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1994/02/23/amore-amore-amore-ma-pure-che-guevara.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | author = Gino Castaldo | language = Italian | title = Amore amore amore, ma pure Che Guevara | date = 23 February 1994}}</ref> She was also strongly criticized for her songs, described as too melancholic<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1207254 |work=[[La Stampa]] |language=Italian |accessdate=13 August 2011 |title=I guai della celebrit\u00e0: pettegolezzi, bugie e persino la contro-propaganda di una radio Pausini, la favorita: Vincere non conta, ma mi piace che la gente canti quello che canto io |author=Marinella Venegoni |date=9 February 1994 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120328215522/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1207254 |archivedate=28 March 2012 }}</ref> and trivial.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1213628 |work=[[La Stampa]] |date=23 February 1994 |language=Italian |accessdate=13 August 2011 |title=SANREMO '94, che la festa cominci |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120328215527/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1213628 |archivedate=28 March 2012 }}</ref>\nStarting from her 1998's ''La mia risposta'' / ''Mi respuesta'', Italian music critics considered her as a more mature singer<ref name=\"Corriere15121998\"/> and later praised her simplicity<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.lastampa.it/cmstp/rubriche/stampa.asp?ID_blog=132&ID_articolo=689 | author = Luca Dondoni | date = 13 November 2009 | title = Nelle stanze di Laura. Ha appena vinto due premi al Latin Grammy Award Amata in Italia e nel mondo ora vuole una famiglia | language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011}}</ref> and her voice,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2009/03/14/laura-pausini-primavera-show-di-una-semplice.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011 | date = 14 March 2009 | title = Laura Pausini. Primavera show di una semplice star | author = Ernesto Assante}}</ref> describing Pausini as an interpreter of her years.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.musicaedischi.it/recensioni.php?genere=0&id=3503 | work = Musica e dischi | language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 Io canto  **** | author = Mario De Luigi | date = November 2006}}</ref>\n\nAlthough Pausini is mainly a melodic pop singer,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1084006 | work = [[La Stampa]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 13 August 2011 | title = Senza passaggi in tv n\u00e8 promozione discografica, nascono le nuove star eredi di Vasco e Baglioni. Saranno famosi, anzi lo sono. Cos\u00ec i ragazzi cambiano musica. Varie tendenze. Dalle cantanti melodiche perbene agli arrabbiati | date = 23 April 1993 | author = Gabriele Ferrari | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120328215543/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1084006 | archivedate = 28 March 2012 | df = dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.allbusiness.com/retail-trade/miscellaneous-retail-retail-stores-not/4630372-1.html | author = Mark Dezzani | date = 20 June 1998 | publisher = [[Allbusiness.com]] | title = Billboard Spotlights Italy: The Changing Face Of Italian Talent}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | journal = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | url = https://books.google.com/?id=DBEEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA61&dq=billboard+pausini#v=onepage&q=billboard%20pausini&f=false | title = Exports Pay Off For Italian Labels | date = 15 June 2002 | author = Mark Worden | page = 61 | accessdate =13 August 2011}}</ref> her musical style evolved during her career, with influences from various genres, including [[Latin music (genre)|Latin music]],<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.rockol.it/news-5266/Intervista-a-Laura-Pausini?idartista=1712&pag=12 | publisher = Rockol.it | language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011 | title = Intervista a Laura Pausini | date = 24 January 1999}}</ref> [[soul music]]<ref name=\"RepubblicaArticle\"/><ref name=\"StampaMiaRisposta\"/> and rock music.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2004/ottobre/21/rock_guerra_per_Laura_Pausini_co_9_041021092.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011 | title = Un po' di rock (e guerra) per Laura Pausini| date = 21 October 2004 | author = Mario Luzzatto Fegiz}}</ref> In 2001, David Cazares of the ''[[South Florida Sun-Sentinel]]'' described Pausini's music as \"an assortment of glossy and sentimental pop ballads backed by light rock instrumentation and synthesized strings\".<ref>{{cite web | url = http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2001-10-12/entertainment/0110100555_1_eddie-palmieri-latin-jazz-jazz-musicians | work = [[South Florida Sun-Sentinel]] | accessdate = 1 September 2012 | title = Jazz-salsa Pioneer Palmieri Still Going Strong | date = 12 October 2001 | author = David Cazares}}</ref> In 2006, ''[[The Washington Post]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s Achy Obejas wrote that Pausini is distinguished from other Latin pop singer by her sophistication and her European sensibilities.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/12/01/AR2006120100260.html |work=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=1 September 2012 |title=Recording: Quick Snips |author=Achy Obejas |date=3 December 2006 |archivedate= 10 October 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010063533/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/12/01/AR2006120100260.html |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> According to ''Musica e dischi'''s Antonio Orlando, the key elements in Pausini's style are romanticism, optimism, melancholy and surrounding melodies.<ref name=\"MusicaedischiPrimaveraInAnticipo\">{{cite web | url = http://www.musicaedischi.it/recensioni.php?genere=0&id=5101 | work = Musica e dischi | language = Italian | accessdate =13 October 2011 | title = Laura Pausini \u2013 Primavera in anticipo  ****1/2 | author = Antonio Orlando | date = December 2008}}</ref>\n\nStarting from her 1996's album ''Le cose che vivi'' / ''Las cosas que vives'', Pausini has also co-written most of her songs<ref name=\"MusicaedischiPrimaveraInAnticipo\"/><ref>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1996/09/12/canto-le-vite-come-la-mia.html| work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011 | title = Canto le vite come la mia | date = 12 September 1996}}</ref> and starting from her 1998's ''La mia risposta'' / ''Mi respuesta'' she has been involved in the production of her albums.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/mi-respuesta-r378432/credits | website = [[Allmusic]] | accessdate =13 August 2011 | title = Mi Respuesta \u2013 Laura Pausini \u2013 Credits}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nPausini left her hometown in 1995, when she moved to [[Milan]] with her partner, manager and producer Alfredo Cerruti Jr.<ref name=laRepubblica14Dec1995>{{cite web | url = http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1995/12/24/la-favola-di-laura-stella-dei-due.html | work = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011 | title = La favola di Laura, stella dei due mondi | author = Laura Putti | date = 24 December 1995}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2001/01/27/pausini-pensa-allamerica.html |work=[[la Repubblica]] |language=Italian |accessdate=13 August 2011 |title=Pausini pensa all'America |date=27 January 2001 |author=Laura Putti |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120518050444/http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2001/01/27/pausini-pensa-allamerica.html |archivedate=18 May 2012 }}</ref> Their relationship ended in 2002. Between 2002 and 2005 Pausini was romantically involved with her new manager, Gabriele Parisi.<ref name=\"Repubblica5February05\"/>\nShe is currently engaged with the Italian guitarist, composer, music producer and former singer Paolo Carta.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/gossip/articoli/articolo284865.shtml | work = [[TGCOM]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 13 August 2011 | title = Pausini torna dal suo chitarrista | date = 23 November 2005 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101108221024/http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/gossip/articoli/articolo284865.shtml | archive-date = 8 November 2010 | url-status = dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.tgcom.mediaset.it/spettacolo/articoli/1017053/pausini-paparazzata-sul-set-del-nuovo-video.shtml | work = [[TGCOM]] | language = Italian | accessdate =13 August 2011 | title = Pausini paparazzata sul set del nuovo video | date = 29 July 2011}}</ref> On 15 September 2012, Pausini confirmed through her official Facebook page that she was expecting her first child with her partner Paolo Carta.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Il Secolo XIX]] |url=http://www.ilsecoloxix.it/p/magazine/2012/09/15/APL084RD-pausini_incinta_facebook.shtml |language=Italian |title=Pausini incinta, la foto su Facebook |date=15 September 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120918025859/http://www.ilsecoloxix.it/p/magazine/2012/09/15/APL084RD-pausini_incinta_facebook.shtml |archivedate=18 September 2012 |accessdate=15 September 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> Their daughter, Paola, was born on 8 February 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/ravenna/cronaca/2013/02/08/842942-laura-pausini-mamma-piccola-paola.shtml |work=[[Il Resto del Carlino]] |language=Italian |accessdate=8 February 2013 |date=8 February 2013 |title=Laura Pausini \u00e8 diventata mamma E' nata la piccola Paola |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130208210028/http://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/ravenna/cronaca/2013/02/08/842942-laura-pausini-mamma-piccola-paola.shtml |archivedate= 8 February 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\nPausini describes herself as a [[Roman Catholic]] woman,<ref name=\"Repubblica15092000\"/><ref>{{cite web | url = http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1084008 | work = [[La Stampa]] | language = Italian | accessdate = 13 August 2011 | title = Laura Pausini. Maturit\u00e0 e poi tournee: Son studiosa e devota | date = 23 April 1993 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20111005080709/http://archivio.lastampa.it/LaStampaArchivio/main/History/tmpl_viewObj.jsp?objid=1084008 | archivedate = 5 October 2011 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> but expressed doubts about Roman Church's position on various themes, including [[contraception]], abortion, [[premarital sex]] and gay rights.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1996/settembre/12/Pausini_svelo_mio_mondo_co_0_9609129662.shtml | work = [[Corriere della Sera]] | language = Italian | title = La Pausini: vi svelo il mio mondo | author = Gloria Pozzi | date = 12 September 1996}}</ref> In September 2000 she explained her position during an interview to the Italian newspaper ''[[la Repubblica]]'':<ref name=\"Repubblica15092000\"/>\n\n{{quote|I really believe in God, and the Pope is the man that I most want to meet again in the world. I already met him in 1996. I just have a few doubts about the Catholic Church, such as the discrimination against homosexuals. I don't understand how they condemn racism, but at the same time take issue with gay people.}}\n\n==Honours==\n[[File:Commendatore OMRI BAR.svg|100px]] \u2013 [[Order of Merit of the Italian Republic|Commander Order of Merit of the Italian Republic]]: Awarded the third highest civil honour in Italy, by President [[Carlo Azeglio Ciampi]] on 6 February 2006.<ref name=Commander/>\n\n==Discography==\n[[File:Laura Pausini 2009.04.30 001.jpg|thumb|right|170px|Laura Pausini]]\n{{Main|Laura Pausini discography}}\n\n===Studio albums===\n*''[[Laura Pausini (1993 album)|Laura Pausini]]'' (1993)\n*''[[Laura (Laura Pausini album)|Laura]]'' (1994)\n*''[[Laura Pausini (1994 album)|Laura Pausini]]'' (1994)\n*[[Le cose che vivi|''Le cose che vivi'' / ''Las cosas que vives'']] (1996)\n*[[La mia risposta|''La mia risposta'' / ''Mi respuesta'']] (1998)\n*[[Tra te e il mare|''Tra te e il mare'' / ''Entre t\u00fa y mil mares'']] (2000)\n*''[[From the Inside (Laura Pausini album)|From the Inside]]'' (2002)\n*[[Resta in ascolto|''Resta in ascolto'' / ''Escucha'']] (2004)\n*[[Io canto|''Io canto'' / ''Yo canto'']] (2006)\n*[[Primavera in anticipo|''Primavera in anticipo'' / ''Primavera anticipada'']] (2008)\n*[[Inedito|''Inedito'' / ''In\u00e9dito'']] (2011)\n*[[Simili (album)|''Simili'' / ''Similares'']] (2015)\n*[[Laura Xmas|''Laura Xmas'' / ''Laura Navidad'']] (2016)\n*[[Fatti sentire|''Fatti sentire'' / ''Hazte sentir'']] (2018)\n\n===Compilations, duets and live albums===\n*''[[Laura Pausini (1995 album)|Laura Pausini]]'' (1995)\n*''[[The Best of Laura Pausini: E ritorno da te]]'' (2001)\n*''[[Live in Paris 05]]'' (2005)\n*''[[San Siro 2007]]'' (2007)\n*''[[Laura Live World Tour 09]]'' (2009)\n*''[[20 \u2013 The Greatest Hits (Laura Pausini album)|20 \u2013 The Greatest Hits]]'' (2013)\n\n==Tours==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!Tour\n!Year(s)\n!Releases\n!Format(s)\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Laura Pausini on Tour\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|1993-94\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Laura Pausini in Concerto\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|1997\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[La Mia Risposta World Tour]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|1999\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Laura Pausini 2001/2002 World Tour|E ritorno da te World Tour]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2001\u201302\n|''[[Live 2001-2002 World Tour]]''\n|DVD\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[World Tour '05|Laura Pausini Live]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2005\n|''[[Live in Paris 05]]''\n|CD+DVD, 2\u00d7 DVD, CD\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Juntos en concierto 2006]]<br/><small>(with [[Marc Anthony]] and [[Marco Antonio Sol\u00eds]])</small>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2006\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Io canto\u2013Yo canto\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007\n|''[[San Siro 2007]]''\n|CD+DVD, CD, DVD\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[World Tour 2009|LP World Tour]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2009\n|''[[Laura Live World Tour 09]]''\n|CD+DVD\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Inedito World Tour]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2011\u201312\n|''[[Inedito#Special Edition|Inedito (Special Edition)]]'' <small>(includes a live bonus track and a live DVD)</small>\n|CD+DVD\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[The Greatest Hits World Tour]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2013\u201315\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Simili Tour]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2016\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Fatti Sentire World Tour]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2018\n|''[[Fatti Sentire Ancora]]'' <small></small>\n|DVD\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n;Television\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Series\n!Role\n!Network\n!Notes\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2009\n!scope=\"row\"|''Due''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.style.it/vanitypeople/show/musica/2010/10/04/tiziano-ferro-fa-due-con-laura-pausini.aspx#?refresh_ce|publisher=Style.it|language=Italian|accessdate=4 April 2016|date=8 December 2009|title=Tiziano Ferro fa Due con Laura Pausini|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160805230646/http://www.style.it/vanitypeople/show/musica/2010/10/04/tiziano-ferro-fa-due-con-laura-pausini.aspx#?refresh_ce|archivedate=5 August 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[Rai Due]]\n|Music TV show \u2013 1 episode as main performer and presenter, shared with [[Tiziano Ferro]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2014\n!scope=\"row\"|''Laura Pausini 20 \u2013 My Story''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://skyuno.sky.it/skyuno/news/2013/12/12/laura_pausini_vent_anni_carriera_sky_uno_intervista.html|publisher=[[Sky Uno]]|language=Italian|accessdate=4 April 2016|title=Vent'anni di Laura Pausini, una storia speciale|author=Fabrizio Basso|date=10 January 2010}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[Sky Italia]]\n|Autobiographical documentary \u2013 1 episode\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Stasera Laura: ho creduto in un sogno''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panorama.it/musica/stasera-laura-pausini-raiuno/|work=[[Panorama (magazine)|Panorama]]|language=Italian|accessdate=5 April 2016|title=Stasera Laura su Raiuno. La Pausini, le emozioni|author=Alessandro Alicandri|date=21 May 2014}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[Rai Uno]]\n|Music TV show & concert \u2013 1 episode, main performer and presenter\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2014, 2017\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[La Voz... M\u00e9xico]]''<ref name=\"La Voz Mexico\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/espectaculos/television/la-voz-mexico-se-va-la-segura-y-retoma-viejos-coaches|work=[[El Universal (M\u00e9xico)|El Universal]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=6 October 2017|title=La voz M\u00e9xico se va a la segura y retoma a viejos coaches|date=26 August 2017|author=Ariel Le\u00f3n}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[Canal de las Estrellas]]\n|[[Talent show]] \u2013 series 4 and series 6 judge and coach\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2015\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[La Voz (Spanish TV series)|La Voz]]''<ref name=\"La Voz Spain\"/>\n|Herself\n|[[Telecinco]]\n|Talent show \u2013 series 3 judge and coach\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''La meraviglia di essere simili''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sorrisi.com/tv/news-e-anticipazioni/laura-pausini-la-meraviglia-di-essere-simili-in-onda-21-novembre-2015/|work=[[TV Sorrisi e Canzoni]]|language=Italian|accessdate=5 April 2016|title=Laura Pausini, \"La meraviglia di essere Simili\" in onda il 21/11|author=Antonio Mustara|date=17 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170929044355/http://www.sorrisi.com/tv/news-e-anticipazioni/laura-pausini-la-meraviglia-di-essere-simili-in-onda-21-novembre-2015/|archive-date=29 September 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|Rai Uno\n|Documentary \u2013 1 episode, TV special documenting her twelfth studio album, ''[[Simili (album)|Simili]]''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2015\u20132016\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[La Banda (TV series)|La Banda]]''<ref name=\"La Banda\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latintimes.com/la-banda-2-judges-univision-reveals-which-two-artists-join-laura-pausini-reality-show-392403|work=[[Latin Times]]|accessdate=26 November 2016|title=La Banda 2 Judges: Univision Reveals Which Two Artists Join Laura Pausini In Reality Show|author=Jessica Lucia Roiz|date=30 June 2016}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[Univision]]\n|Talent show \u2013 series 1 and series 2 judge\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2016\n!scope=\"row\"|''Laura & Paola''<ref name=\"Laura e Paola\"/>\n|Herself\n|Rai Uno\n|[[Variety show]] \u2013 3 episodes, main presenter and performer, shared with [[Paola Cortellesi]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|2018\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Lo Nuestro Awards]]<ref name=\"Lo Nuestro 2018\"/>\n|Herself\n|Univision\n|Music gala \u2013 co-host and performer\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Factor X (Spanish TV series)|Factor X]]''<ref name=\"Factor X\"/>\n|Herself\n|Telecinco\n|Talent show \u2013 series 3 judge\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Laura Pausini}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n|- style=\"background:#ddd;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[Grammy Awards]]'''\n{{s-bef|before= [[Marc Anthony]]<br />for ''[[Amar Sin Mentiras|Amar sin mentiras]]''}}\n{{s-ttl|title = [[Grammy Award for Best Latin Pop Album]]|years = 2006<br />'''for ''[[Resta in ascolto|Escucha]]'' '''}}\n{{s-aft|after = [[Ricardo Arjona]] for ''[[Adentro]]''<br/>joint with<br/>[[Julieta Venegas]] for ''[[Lim\u00f3n y sal]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#ddd;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[Latin Grammy Awards]]'''\n{{succession box\n| title  = [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album, Female]]\n| years  = 2005<br/>'''for ''[[Resta in ascolto|Escucha]]'' '''\n| before = [[Rosario Flores]]<br/>for ''[[De mil colores (Rosario Flores album)|De mil colores]]''\n| after  = [[Shakira]]<br/>for ''[[Fijaci\u00f3n Oral Vol. 1]]''\n}}\n{{succession box\n| title  = Latin Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album, Female\n| years  = 2007<br/>'''for ''[[Io canto|Yo canto]]'' '''\n| before = Shakira<br/>for ''Fijaci\u00f3n Oral Vol. 1''\n| after  = [[Kany Garc\u00eda]]<br/>for ''[[Cualquier D\u00eda]]''