e Creek, Michigan]] and began wanting to be an actor at the age of 7, after seeing a performance of ''[[Grease (musical)|Grease]]'' at the Barn Theatre.<ref name=battle/> He acted at [[Pennfield High School]], from which he graduated in 1991, and performed in school productions from [[Kellogg Community College]]<ref name=battle/> while earning his associate degree.\n\n==Career==\nAfter a year at the Barn Theatre, alongside [[Jennifer Garner]], he moved to [[Chicago]] and spent five years working his way up in [[The Second City]] [[improvisational comedy]] troupe.<ref name=battle/> He then moved to [[Los Angeles]] and had his first television role in [[On the Spot (2003 TV series)|''On the Spot'']], an improv sketch show which ran for five episodes on [[The WB]] in 2003.<ref name=battle/> He credits his breakthrough to the 2005 [[HBO]] series ''[[The Comeback (TV series)|The Comeback]]'' with [[Lisa Kudrow]], in which he played Paulie G., a television writer who he describes as an \"asshole\".<ref name=battle/> In 2010, he landed the recurring role of [[List of It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia characters#Bill Ponderosa|Bill Ponderosa]] on [[FX (TV channel)|FX]]'s ''[[It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia]]''.<ref name=battle/> He reprised his role as Paulie G. when HBO brought back ''The Comeback'' in 2014.<ref>{{cite news| title=Lance Barber on his long-awaited 'Comeback'| url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/tv/ct-chicago-closeup-lance-barber-20141211-column.html| accessdate=September 27, 2017| work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=December 11, 2014| first=Nina| last=Metz}}</ref> He also starred in episodes of ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]'', ''[[Gilmore Girls]]'', ''[[Californication (TV series)|Californication]]'', ''[[Monk (TV series)|Monk]]'', [[The Mentalist]], and ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''.\n\nBarber played [[Jimmy Speckerman]], who bullied [[Leonard Hofstadter]] at high school, in [[The Speckerman Recurrence|one episode]] of ''[[The Big Bang Theory]]''.<ref name=carter>{{cite news| title=Young Sheldon interview: Lance Barber on playing Sheldon's father George Cooper Sr.| url=http://cartermatt.com/268270/young-sheldon-interview-lance-barber-sheldon-father-george/| accessdate=September 26, 2017| journal=CarterMatt| date=September 22, 2017}}</ref> He was cast as George Cooper Sr., father of [[Sheldon Cooper]], in the spin-off ''[[Young Sheldon]]'' that premiered in 2017, and mentioned in an interview that some fans were confused by his different roles in the two related series.<ref name=carter/>\n\n==Personal life==\nBarber lives in [[Los Angeles]] with his wife Aliza, who is a chef, and their two young children.<ref name=battle/>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n{{anchor|films}}{{anchor|movies}}\n\n=== Film ===\nActing roles in film productions:&nbsp;<ref name=imdb-nm1115741>{{cite web| url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1115741/?ref_=nv_sr_1| title=Lance Barber \u2013 Filmography| access-date=January 2, 2019| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102103256/https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1115741/?ref_=nv_sr_1| archive-date=January 2, 2019| website=[[IMDb]]| url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=tvguide>{{cite web| url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/lance-barber/credits/193696/| title=Lance Barber|  accessdate=February 1, 2019| journal=[[TV Guide]]| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180425195549/https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/lance-barber/credits/193696/| archivedate=April 25, 2018| url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<!-- TABLE FOR MOVIE/FILMS (ALL NON-TV WORK), AS ACTOR: \"Barber, Lance\" -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| TBA || ''[[El Tonto]]'' || Side Kick || \n|-\n| 2019 || ''Raunch and Roll'' || Crash || In [[post-production]] <!-- on 2-Jan-2019; pls update upon release -->\n|-\n| 2017 || ''Never Seen You Shine So Bright'' || Neil || [[Short film]]\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Gangster Squad (film)|Gangster Squad]]'' || Comanche || \n|-\n| 2010 || ''Dead Cat'' || \u2013 || Short film\n|-\n| 2